{"_id":"species-advozse","name":"Advozse","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Advozse.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, +2 Wis, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Low-Light Vision","Natural Armor"],"languages":["Advb","Basic"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"The Advozsec come from the tectonically tortured world of Riflor. Three suns exert tremendous gravitational stress on the planet, which has baffled planetologists as to why the planet hasn't been destroyed yet. The Advozsec evolved on Riflor to become both survivors and tremendous pessimists. Although much of their fame comes from their reputation as bureaucrats, Advozse engineers have also been responsible for many advances in building materials and construction techniques. Advozsec are strict vegetarians and become violently ill if they consume animal protein.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Advozse","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"An Advozse can choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Advozsec ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Advozsec have a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, +2 Wis, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Advozsec receive a +2 bonus to both their Constitution and Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Advozsec are cynical and hardy, though they lack a certain grace possessed by others.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Advb","Basic"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Low-Light Vision","Natural Armor"],"traits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"An Advozse can choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Advozsec ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Advozsec have a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1399},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-aing-tii","name":"Aing-Tii","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Aing-Tii.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Use the Force"],"special":["Force-Sensitive Species","Sanctuary Teleportation"],"languages":["Aing-Tii Pheromone"],"source":"Unknown Regions","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Aing-Tii","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-aleena","name":"Aleena","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Aleena.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Energy Surge","Heightened Agility"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"energy-surge","name":"Energy Surge","description":"Once per encounter, an Aleena can gain a temporary boost to quickness and reflexes. When this ability is activated as a Swift Action, an Aleena gains a +2 bonus on Dexterity-based Skill Checks, and increases its base speed to 8 squares. The energy lasts for a number of rounds equal to the Aleena's Constitution modifier (minimum 1 round). When the energy is expended, the Aleena moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this condition persist until the Aleena takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the creature can't engage in any strenuous activity."},{"id":"heightened-agility","name":"Heightened Agility","description":"Aleena are quite adept at avoiding danger in combat when they can see it coming. An Aleena can choose to reroll any Acrobatics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"languages":["Aleena","Basic Caamasi in: Species","Caamasi","Medium","6 more Caamasi 1 Edit"],"description":"Aleena are quick and agile. Their metabolism allows them to burn a lot of energy in a short amount of time, giving them a significant boost to their speed and reflexes. Some Aleena use these natural skills as Podracers and pilots.","canonicalName":"Aleena","canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Aleena receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Aleena are extremely quick, but they have difficulty relating to other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Aleena","Basic Caamasi in: Species","Caamasi","Medium","6 more Caamasi 1 Edit"],"special":["Energy Surge","Heightened Agility"],"traits":[{"id":"energy-surge","name":"Energy Surge","description":"Once per encounter, an Aleena can gain a temporary boost to quickness and reflexes. When this ability is activated as a Swift Action, an Aleena gains a +2 bonus on Dexterity-based Skill Checks, and increases its base speed to 8 squares. The energy lasts for a number of rounds equal to the Aleena's Constitution modifier (minimum 1 round). When the energy is expended, the Aleena moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this condition persist until the Aleena takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the creature can't engage in any strenuous activity."},{"id":"heightened-agility","name":"Heightened Agility","description":"Aleena are quite adept at avoiding danger in combat when they can see it coming. An Aleena can choose to reroll any Acrobatics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":759},"tags":["small"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-altiri","name":"Altiri","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Altiri.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Trained Skill","Visually Striking"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Altiri are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. An Altiri chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."},{"id":"visually-striking","name":"Visually Striking","description":"Altiri have a visually surprising or stunning appearance. An Altiri's Charisma bonus is doubled when they use the Persuasion skill on Humans and Near-Humans."}],"languages":["Altirish","Basic"],"description":"Altiri are a Near-Human Species that evolved on the eastern continent of the planet they call Altiria. Originally wandering nomads, Altiri developed a society that places great importance on individual development of one's intellect and spirituality. Through artistic expression and cultural awareness, Altiri focus on expanding their knowledge of the universe by peaceful, scientific means. Their perpetual war with the Anarrians is a glaring exception to this lofty goal. Most Altiri unite under the banner of The Altirian Republic, a representative democracy that rules most of the eastern continent and several island chains around it.","canonicalName":"Altiri","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Altiri have no Ability Score adjustments.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Altirish","Basic"],"special":["Bonus Trained Skill","Visually Striking"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Altiri are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. An Altiri chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."},{"id":"visually-striking","name":"Visually Striking","description":"Altiri have a visually surprising or stunning appearance. An Altiri's Charisma bonus is doubled when they use the Persuasion skill on Humans and Near-Humans."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2086},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-amani","name":"Amani","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Amani.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Acceleration","Expert Climber","Primitive","Reach","Resilient"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"acceleration","name":"Acceleration","description":"When using the Run Action, Amanin may roll into a ball to move at greater speed. When Running, Amanin may take a -5 penalty on Perception checks, and have their Speed doubled."},{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Due to their arboreal background, Amanin may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Amanin do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"reach","name":"Reach","description":"Unlike most Medium-sized Species, Amanin have a natural Reach of 2 squares."},{"id":"resilient","name":"Resilient","description":"Amanin gain a +1 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense due to their natural resilience."}],"languages":["Amanese"],"description":"These arboreal humanoids live in small tribes that each lay claim to one of the many sparse forests of Maridun, their homeworld. When a tribe grows too large, the younger adults set out to claim a new forest. The arrival of the Empire on Maridun went largely unnoticed, until one Amanin lorekeeper agreed to turn over prisoners from rival tribes as slaves. Not long after the Battle of Endor, operations on Maridun were taken over by The Hutt Kajidics and various criminal syndicates, which constructed spaceports to support the growth of several small cities populated by crime lords, scoundrels, consortiums, mining companies, and Amanin slaves. As their society becomes more and more integrated with the rest of the galaxy, Amanin become more comfortable with space travel and technology, though they lack the scientific knowledge to build technology of their own.","canonicalName":"Amani","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Amanin receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Charisma. Amanin are a muscular Species, but their nomadic lifestyles make them difficult to connect with.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Amanese"],"special":["Acceleration","Expert Climber","Primitive","Reach","Resilient"],"traits":[{"id":"acceleration","name":"Acceleration","description":"When using the Run Action, Amanin may roll into a ball to move at greater speed. When Running, Amanin may take a -5 penalty on Perception checks, and have their Speed doubled."},{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Due to their arboreal background, Amanin may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Amanin do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"reach","name":"Reach","description":"Unlike most Medium-sized Species, Amanin have a natural Reach of 2 squares."},{"id":"resilient","name":"Resilient","description":"Amanin gain a +1 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense due to their natural resilience."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2490},"tags":["medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-anarrian","name":"Anarrian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Anarrian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Feat","Strength Surge"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Anarrians gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"strength-surge","name":"Strength Surge","description":"Once per encounter, an Anarrian can perform one of the following actions: Reroll one Strength-based Ability Check or Skill Check using a doubled Strength modifier (minimum +1) Add +2 to one damage roll when making a successful melee attack to which a Strength bonus is normally added (this benefit does not apply when the Weapon Finesse feat is used)"}],"languages":["Anarrese","Basic"],"description":"Most Anarrians are citizens of The Anarrian Empire, the government that reigns over the planet's western continent and many of the islands nearby. Since its inception around the time of The Mandalorian Wars, the Empire has fought to gain dominance over the Altiri and establish its rule over the world. Thanks to their perpetual state of military readiness and training, the Anarrians are prepared to launch an assault on any who stand in their way, including rogue cells of Anarrians who choose other philosophies and goals.","canonicalName":"Anarrian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Anarrians have no Ability Score adjustments.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Anarrese","Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Strength Surge"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Anarrians gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"strength-surge","name":"Strength Surge","description":"Once per encounter, an Anarrian can perform one of the following actions: Reroll one Strength-based Ability Check or Skill Check using a doubled Strength modifier (minimum +1) Add +2 to one damage roll when making a successful melee attack to which a Strength bonus is normally added (this benefit does not apply when the Weapon Finesse feat is used)"}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2118},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-anomid","name":"Anomid","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Anomid.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Mechanics","+2 Use Computer"],"special":["Tech Savant"],"languages":["Anomid","Basic"],"source":"Scum & Villainy","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Anomid","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-anx","name":"Anx","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Anx.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Powerful Build"],"languages":["Anx","Basic"],"source":"FU","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":4,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Anx","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-anzati","name":"Anzati","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Anzati.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Class Skills","Energy Drain","Low-Light Vision","Mesmerize","Presence Sense"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skills","name":"Bonus Class Skills","description":"Stealth and Survival are always Class Skills for Anzati."},{"id":"energy-drain","name":"Energy Drain","description":"As a Swift Action once per round, an Anzati can use its proboscis to drain energy from a Grabbed target, moving the target -1 step on the Condition Track as a Persistent Condition, and granting the Anzati Bonus Hit Points equal to 5 + half the Anzati's Character Level. The Anzati can repeat this action each round until the target escapes the Grab, or until the target is rendered unconscious. If the target survives the feeding attempt, the Persistent Condition is removed after the target rests for 8 hours."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Anzati ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"mesmerize","name":"Mesmerize","description":"As a Standard Action, an Anzati can make a special attack against the Will Defense of a single target within 6 squares of the Anzati. The attack modifier is equal to the Anzati's Character Level plus his or her Charisma modifier. If the attack is successful, the target loses its Standard Action for its next turn. If the attack fails, the target is immune to this effect for 24 hours. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"presence-sense","name":"Presence Sense","description":"The Anzati's acute senses enable them to sense a person's luck. When making a Survival check to Track a living creature, an Anzati gains a Species bonus equal to the quarry's Force Point total."}],"languages":["Anzat","Basic"],"description":"","canonicalName":"Anzati","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Anzati have no Ability Score adjustments.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Anzat","Basic"],"special":["Bonus Class Skills","Energy Drain","Low-Light Vision","Mesmerize","Presence Sense"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skills","name":"Bonus Class Skills","description":"Stealth and Survival are always Class Skills for Anzati."},{"id":"energy-drain","name":"Energy Drain","description":"As a Swift Action once per round, an Anzati can use its proboscis to drain energy from a Grabbed target, moving the target -1 step on the Condition Track as a Persistent Condition, and granting the Anzati Bonus Hit Points equal to 5 + half the Anzati's Character Level. The Anzati can repeat this action each round until the target escapes the Grab, or until the target is rendered unconscious. If the target survives the feeding attempt, the Persistent Condition is removed after the target rests for 8 hours."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Anzati ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"mesmerize","name":"Mesmerize","description":"As a Standard Action, an Anzati can make a special attack against the Will Defense of a single target within 6 squares of the Anzati. The attack modifier is equal to the Anzati's Character Level plus his or her Charisma modifier. If the attack is successful, the target loses its Standard Action for its next turn. If the attack fails, the target is immune to this effect for 24 hours. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"presence-sense","name":"Presence Sense","description":"The Anzati's acute senses enable them to sense a person's luck. When making a Survival check to Track a living creature, an Anzati gains a Species bonus equal to the quarry's Force Point total."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2097},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-aqualish","name":"Aqualish","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Aqualish.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Climb"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Breathe Underwater","Expert Swimmer"],"languages":["Aqualish","Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"he Aqualish are amphibious humanoids native to The Mid Rim world of Ando. Three breeds of Aqualish exist- the Aquala (widely considered the \"Baseline\" Aqualish), the Quara, and the Ualaq. The three strains are generally similar in appearance and in all their traits, but the Quara and Ualaq have claw-like hands with five digits whereas the Aquala have fins. The Ualaq are set apart by the fact that they have four eyes instead of two. The Aqualish hold no beings in greater contempt than those who belong to a different subspecies than themselves- Aquala hate the Quara and the Ualaq, the Quara hate the Aquala and Ualaq, and the Ualaq hate the Aquala and the Quara.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Aqualish","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Rugged and resilient, Aqualish gain Toughness as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Aqualish can't drown in water."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"An Aqualish may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Aqualish may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Aqualish receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both Wisdom and Charisma. Aqualish are hardy and fit, but are brash and brutish compared to others.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Aqualish","Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Breathe Underwater","Expert Swimmer"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Rugged and resilient, Aqualish gain Toughness as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Aqualish can't drown in water."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"An Aqualish may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Aqualish may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":18},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-arcona","name":"Arcona","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Arcona.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative","+2 Perception"],"special":["Great Fortitude","Scent"],"languages":["Arconese","Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"When it was discovered the Arcona can easily and hopelessly become addicted to sodium chloride (salt) by ingesting even a gram or two of the substance, unscrupulous merchants almost destroyed Arcona society by creating several generations of salt addicts. Salt induces vivid, colorful hallucinations in Arcona, but repeated use damages their body's ability to absorb life-giving ammonia. Only the intervention of the Republic saved the Arcona. The Senate passed draconian laws that punished the importation of salt to the Teke Ro System or to Arcona communities elsewhere in the galaxy, and the Arcona themselves zealously police their communities. Arcona addicted to salt are easily identifiable; their multifaceted eyes turn from green to gold.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Arcona","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Arcona gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense. Arcona have adapted to the harsh environment of Cona and can convert many different toxins into harmless chemicals."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Arcona have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Arcona ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Arcona receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Arcona aren't as perceptive as many other beings, but they are known for their ability to socially adapt to life in the galaxy at large.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Arconese","Basic"],"special":["Great Fortitude","Scent"],"traits":[{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Arcona gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense. Arcona have adapted to the harsh environment of Cona and can convert many different toxins into harmless chemicals."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Arcona have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Arcona ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2513},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-arkanian","name":"Arkanian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Arkanian.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Use Computer","+2 Mechanics"],"special":["Darkvision","Flash of Genius","Intellectual Reputation"],"languages":["Arkanian","Basic"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"Arkanian society and history are among the most complex in the Old Republic. At different times in its history, Arkanian has belonged to both the Republic and the Sith Empire, and played important roles in each. Knowledge and research are extremely important to the Arkanians, and they are highly skilled academicians and scientists. It is therefore not surprising that Arkania would become a main repository of the history of the Sith Empire, as well as home to vast libraries of information from across the galaxy. Arkanians are not afraid to profit from their research and high intelligence.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Arkanian","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Arkanians ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"flash-of-genius","name":"Flash of Genius","description":"Arkanians have moments of brilliance. Once per encounter, an Arkanian can add a +5 circumstance bonus to to the result of one Knowledge, Mechanics, or Use Computer skill check."},{"id":"intellectual-reputation","name":"Intellectual Reputation","description":"Arkanian prominence in the galaxy makes many individuals more willing to go along with their ideas. An Arkanian can use their Intelligence modifier in place of their Charisma modifier on Persuasion checks."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Arkanians receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Arkanians are well learned and value knowledge above all else, but their arrogant attitudes tends to grate on people nerves very quickly.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Arkanian","Basic"],"special":["Darkvision","Flash of Genius","Intellectual Reputation"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Arkanians ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"flash-of-genius","name":"Flash of Genius","description":"Arkanians have moments of brilliance. Once per encounter, an Arkanian can add a +5 circumstance bonus to to the result of one Knowledge, Mechanics, or Use Computer skill check."},{"id":"intellectual-reputation","name":"Intellectual Reputation","description":"Arkanian prominence in the galaxy makes many individuals more willing to go along with their ideas. An Arkanian can use their Intelligence modifier in place of their Charisma modifier on Persuasion checks."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":530},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-arkanian-offshoot","name":"Arkanian Offshoot","type":"species","img":"assets/species/arkanian_offshoot.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex or Str, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Determination"],"languages":["Basic","Arkanian (albeit with a distinct accent"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"Developed in the era surrounding The Great Sith War, the Arkanian Offshoots were bred as an answer to the need for laborers to mine the vast diamond stores of Arkania. This subspecies was especially vulnerable to minor Arkanian illnesses. The Arkanian Offshoots were treated as second-class or non-citizens by the Pureblooded Arkanians, and the question over what to do with them was termed the \"Offshoot Question.\" Arkoh Adasca planned to use Adascorp's genetic engineering expertise to solve the problem in a generation. Indeed his grandfather, Argaloh Adasca, attempted to exterminate the Arkanian Offshoots with a plague that ravaged those of advanced age. Nearing the end of the Mandalorian Wars, Arkanian Offshoots died out and became mostly extinct due to their rather weak immune systems, along with the Arkanians halting the experiments that created more of the genetically altered subspecies.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Arkanian Offshoot","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityChoice":{"type":"choice","label":"Genetic Engineering","chooseOne":[{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0}],"fixed":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"description":"All Arkanian Offshoots either have a +2 bonus to their Dexterity or Strength depending on their genetic engineering, but all suffer from a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Arkanian Offshoots have been genetically modified to excel at physical task, but that genetic tampering was weakened their physique, making them frail and sickly."},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Arkanian Offshoots are typically engineered for specific industrial tasks. They gain the Skill Focus Feat for one of the following Skills in which they are Trained: Endurance, Mechanics, Pilot, Survival, or Treat Injury."},{"id":"determination","name":"Determination","description":"Arkanian Offshoots are particularly determined and driven. Once per encounter, an Arkanian Offshoot can reroll one failed Skill Check with a Trained Skill. This reroll can be declared after the success or failure of the roll is known. The Arkanian Offshoot must take the result of the reroll, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex or Str, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Arkanian Offshoots either have a +2 bonus to their Dexterity or Strength depending on their genetic engineering, but all suffer from a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Arkanian Offshoots have been genetically modified to excel at physical task, but that genetic tampering was weakened their physique, making them frail and sickly.","abilityChoice":{"type":"choice","chooseOne":[{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0}],"fixed":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"description":"All Arkanian Offshoots either have a +2 bonus to their Dexterity or Strength depending on their genetic engineering, but all suffer from a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Arkanian Offshoots have been genetically modified to excel at physical task, but that genetic tampering was weakened their physique, making them frail and sickly."},"languages":["Basic","Arkanian (albeit with a distinct accent"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Determination"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Arkanian Offshoots are typically engineered for specific industrial tasks. They gain the Skill Focus Feat for one of the following Skills in which they are Trained: Endurance, Mechanics, Pilot, Survival, or Treat Injury."},{"id":"determination","name":"Determination","description":"Arkanian Offshoots are particularly determined and driven. Once per encounter, an Arkanian Offshoot can reroll one failed Skill Check with a Trained Skill. This reroll can be declared after the success or failure of the roll is known. The Arkanian Offshoot must take the result of the reroll, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":551},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-balosar","name":"Balosar","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Balosar.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Cha, -2 Con, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Deception"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Mental Fortitude","Toxic Resistance"],"languages":["Basic","Balosar"],"source":"Scum & Villainy","description":"Balosars are humanoids with a shady reputation throughout the Core Worlds. They can easily pass for Human (when their antennapalps are retracted) and tend to live among the lowest echelons of society, preying on the vices of the weak-willed or impoverished. Relief agencies have been trying to end the vicious circle of poverty, pollution, and corruption on Balosar for years, but the planet's government offers little assistance. Offworld corporations regularly line Balosar bureaucrats' pockets with credits in exchange for state-owned real estate on which they build sweatshop factories. Balosar offers no shortage of manual labor.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Balosar","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"While their Antennapalps are extended, a Balosar may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. A Balosar may choose to retract their Antennapalps as a Free Action (extending them is likewise a Free Action) to pass as Human (no Deception check required)."},{"id":"mental-fortitude","name":"Mental Fortitude","description":"Balosars gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks, as they are extremely savvy in a variety of illicit fields."},{"id":"toxic-resistance","name":"Toxic Resistance","description":"Growing up on a polluted homeworld has given Balosars resistance to toxic substances. Balosars receive a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against Poisons and Toxic Atmospheres."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Cha, -2 Con, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Balosars receive a +2 bonus to both their Dexterity and Charisma, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Constitution and Wisdom. Balosars are nimble and attentive, but are often in despair and a state of malnutrition.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Balosar"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Mental Fortitude","Toxic Resistance"],"traits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"While their Antennapalps are extended, a Balosar may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. A Balosar may choose to retract their Antennapalps as a Free Action (extending them is likewise a Free Action) to pass as Human (no Deception check required)."},{"id":"mental-fortitude","name":"Mental Fortitude","description":"Balosars gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Deception and Persuasion checks, as they are extremely savvy in a variety of illicit fields."},{"id":"toxic-resistance","name":"Toxic Resistance","description":"Growing up on a polluted homeworld has given Balosars resistance to toxic substances. Balosars receive a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against Poisons and Toxic Atmospheres."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":975},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-barabel","name":"Barabel","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Barabel.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Darkvision","Intimidating Presence","Natural Armor","Natural Weapons","Primitive","Radiation Resistance","Stun Resistance"],"languages":["Barabel"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"A towering reptilian Species, the Barabel are relative newcomers to the galactic community. Having evolved from nocturnal predators, Barabels are well-suited to cope with prolonged period of darkness, and they retain much of their ancestor's ferocity. Several centuries prior to the formation of the Empire- at least according to Barabel legend- an Ithorian Jedi explorer named Noga-ta came to their world and peacefully settled a millennium-long civil war stemming from a dispute over prime hunting grounds. This instills a high regard for the Jedi in all Barabel for centuries to follow, even in the wake of the Galactic Empire's anti-Jedi propaganda. For a short time, the Barabels are hunted by illegal safaris set up by Imperial-backed Planetary Safaris, but a massed uprising by the Barabels compels the Empire to intervene and put a stop to the hunts.","tags":["medium","primitive"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[{"name":"Claws","damage":"1d4","type":"slashing"},{"name":"Bite","damage":"1d6","type":"piercing"}],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":1,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Barabel","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Barabels ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"intimidating-presence","name":"Intimidating Presence","description":"A Barabel may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate others, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Barabel's thick scaly hide provides a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor Bonus."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Barabel has Natural Weapons in the form of sharp claws, needle-sharp teeth, and a thick tail. When making an Unarmed attack, a Barabel can choose to use Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage (Claws), piercing damage (Bite), or bludgeoning damage (Tail) with that attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Barabels are always considered armed when attacking with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Barabels do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"radiation-resistance","name":"Radiation Resistance","description":"A Barabel's armored hide protects them from hazardous Radiation, granting the Barabel a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense to resist the effects of Radiation. In addition, Barabels never gain a Persistent Condition from the effects of Radiation."},{"id":"stun-resistance","name":"Stun Resistance","description":"A Barabel's reflective scales defuse the effects of Stun weapons, granting them a +5 Species bonus to their Damage Threshold to resist the effects of Stun Damage."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Barabels receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Dexterity and Wisdom. Barabels are tough and physically gifted, but lack grace and tend to be rather gullible.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Barabel"],"special":["Darkvision","Intimidating Presence","Natural Armor","Natural Weapons","Primitive","Radiation Resistance","Stun Resistance"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Barabels ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"intimidating-presence","name":"Intimidating Presence","description":"A Barabel may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate others, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Barabel's thick scaly hide provides a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor Bonus."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Barabel has Natural Weapons in the form of sharp claws, needle-sharp teeth, and a thick tail. When making an Unarmed attack, a Barabel can choose to use Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage (Claws), piercing damage (Bite), or bludgeoning damage (Tail) with that attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Barabels are always considered armed when attacking with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Barabels do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"radiation-resistance","name":"Radiation Resistance","description":"A Barabel's armored hide protects them from hazardous Radiation, granting the Barabel a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense to resist the effects of Radiation. In addition, Barabels never gain a Persistent Condition from the effects of Radiation."},{"id":"stun-resistance","name":"Stun Resistance","description":"A Barabel's reflective scales defuse the effects of Stun weapons, granting them a +5 Species bonus to their Damage Threshold to resist the effects of Stun Damage."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1660},"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-bardottan","name":"Bardottan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Bardottan.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Use the Force"],"special":["Force-Attuned"],"languages":["Bardottan","Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Bardottan","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-besalisk","name":"Besalisk","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Besalisk.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Multiarmed"],"languages":["Basic","Besalisk"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Besalisk","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-bith","name":"Bith","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Bith.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"special":["Evolved Intellect","Meditative Trance","Scent"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"evolved-intellect","name":"Evolved Intellect","description":"Whenever a Bith spends a Force Point for any reason, the Bith gains a temporary Force Point, that can only be spent to add to an Intelligence-based Skill Check. If the temporary Force Point has not been used by the end of the encounter, it is lost."},{"id":"meditative-trance","name":"Meditative Trance","description":"Bith can enter into a Trance that lasts for four consecutive hours. At the end of the Trance, they gain the benefits of having rested for eight consecutive hours."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Bith have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Bith ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"languages":["Basic","Bith"],"description":"Bith have been part of The Galactic Republic for thousands of years. Intellectually advanced humanoids, Bith have over-sized brains evolved to handle abstract skills such as language, mathematics, music, and scientific analysis. This fundamental shift to the intellect has caused brain functions related to instinct and biological drives to diminish. Their greater brainpower also means that Bith need to spend only four hours in a meditative trance to regain the energy that most Species require eight hours to recover. As a culture, Bith find the concept of warfare abhorrent, and most are pacifists.","canonicalName":"Bith","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Bith receive a +2 bonus to both their Intelligence and their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Bith bodily processes are not very efficient, but members of the Species are bright and personable.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Bith"],"special":["Evolved Intellect","Meditative Trance","Scent"],"traits":[{"id":"evolved-intellect","name":"Evolved Intellect","description":"Whenever a Bith spends a Force Point for any reason, the Bith gains a temporary Force Point, that can only be spent to add to an Intelligence-based Skill Check. If the temporary Force Point has not been used by the end of the encounter, it is lost."},{"id":"meditative-trance","name":"Meditative Trance","description":"Bith can enter into a Trance that lasts for four consecutive hours. At the end of the Trance, they gain the benefits of having rested for eight consecutive hours."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Bith have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Bith ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"variants":[{"id":"bith-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"int":2,"con":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Evolved Intellect","Heightened Awareness","Meditative Trance"],"languages":["Basic","Bith"],"description":"Alternate Bith trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"evolved-intellect","name":"Evolved Intellect","description":"Once per encounter, a Bith can treat any single Intelligence-based skill check as though it were a natural 20 on the die."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Bith can choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."},{"id":"meditative-trance","name":"Meditative Trance","description":"Bith gain all of the benefits of resting for 8 hours after 4 hours of meditation, including natural healing and removing persistent conditions."}]}],"sourceLine":1816},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[{"id":"bith-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Evolved Intellect","Heightened Awareness","Meditative Trance"],"languages":["Basic","Bith"],"description":"Alternate Bith trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"evolved-intellect","name":"Evolved Intellect","description":"Once per encounter, a Bith can treat any single Intelligence-based skill check as though it were a natural 20 on the die."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Bith can choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."},{"id":"meditative-trance","name":"Meditative Trance","description":"Bith gain all of the benefits of resting for 8 hours after 4 hours of meditation, including natural healing and removing persistent conditions."}]}],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-blood-carver","name":"Blood Carver","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Blood Carver.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Deathstrike"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Blood Carver with Acrobatics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Acrobatics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"deathstrike","name":"Deathstrike","description":"Whenever a Blood Carver makes a melee attack against an opponent that is denied its Dexterity bonus to its Reflex Defense, the Blood Carver's attack, if successful, deals +1 die of damage."}],"languages":["Basic","Batorese"],"description":"Blood Carvers are a mysterious Species rarely seen outside their homeworld of Batorine. Those that leave, however, do so because they have been exiled. They gravitate toward the fringes of society, finding it more appealing to operate outside the law. Additionally, Blood Carvers feel shunned by galactic society because of the Blood Carvers' reputation for being fearsome assassins. Except for exiles, Blood Carvers rarely act alone, and exiles find new tribes (often like-minded members of other Species) to associate with.","canonicalName":"Blood Carver","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Blood Carvers receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to both their Wisdom and Charisma. Blood Carvers feel shunned by society due to their reputation as fearsome assassins.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Batorese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Deathstrike"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Blood Carver with Acrobatics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Acrobatics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"deathstrike","name":"Deathstrike","description":"Whenever a Blood Carver makes a melee attack against an opponent that is denied its Dexterity bonus to its Reflex Defense, the Blood Carver's attack, if successful, deals +1 die of damage."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":993},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":1900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-bothan","name":"Bothan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Bothan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth","+2 Perception"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Iron Will"],"languages":["Basic","Bothese"],"source":"Core","description":"Native to Bothawui, these short, fur-covered humanoids have had hyperspace travel for thousands of years. Bothans use information as a measure of wealth and power, even wielding it as a weapon when necessary. The Bothan SpyNet, one of the largest intelligence agencies during most eras, plays an important role in the Galactic Civil War. Culturally, Bothans don't believe in direct conflict because it destroys people, material, and even information. They prefer behind-the-scenes manipulation, watching and waiting for information that they can use to gain status and influence.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Bothan","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Bothans are natural spies and investigators. A Bothan with Gather Information as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Gather Information) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Bothans have above-average willpower and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Bothans receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Bothans are agile but not particularly resilient.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Bothese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Iron Will"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Bothans are natural spies and investigators. A Bothan with Gather Information as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Gather Information) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Bothans have above-average willpower and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":34},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-caamasi","name":"Caamasi","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Caamasi.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Wis, -2 Str, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":4,"cha":0},"special":["Memory Sharing","Pacifism","Silver Tongued"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"memory-sharing","name":"Memory Sharing","description":"Caamasi can create strong, lasting memories and share them with others of their Species through an inborn telepathy. Sharing a memory begins with taking a Full-Round Action to initiate the link between two adjacent Caamasi; transferring a memory requires as much time as the events being recalled. The recipient of a memory must be willing to receive it. Experiencing Memniis not like receiving a photographic memory of those events, but rather a complete, immersive experience. Any character who receives a Memnis from a Caamasi always gains favorable circumstances on Knowledge checks related to that memory. Force-using characters can also receive Memnii from a Caamasi with a successful DC 15 Use the Force check, made as a Reaction."},{"id":"pacifism","name":"Pacifism","description":"As a Standard Action, a Caamasi can make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of a single target within line of sight. If the check is successful, the target moves -1 step along the Condition Track if it makes any attacks before the start of the Caamasi's next turn. The target must be able to hear and understand the Caamasi for this ability to have any effect, and any single target can be affected only once at any given time (meaning that multiple Caamasi may not use this ability on the same target at the same time). This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"silver-tongued","name":"Silver Tongued","description":"Caamasi are skilled negotiators, and patient consulars. A Caamasi can choose to reroll any Persuasion check, using the better result."}],"languages":["Basic","Caamasi"],"description":"All Caamasi can create vivid telepathic memories called Memnii (singular Memnis), which can be shared with others of their Species and with Force-users who possess at least a rudimentary command of telepathy. A Memnis is as vivid to the one who receives it as it is to the one who participated in the event remembered. Caamasi are driven to share Memnii as a form of collected history and ancestral wisdom. After the destruction of Caamas, Memnii take on even greater importance as the only way for young Caamasi to know their lost homeworld.","canonicalName":"Caamasi","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Wis, -2 Str, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":4,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Caamasi receive a +4 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Strength and Constitution. Caamasi are renowned for their insight, not their physical strength.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Caamasi"],"special":["Memory Sharing","Pacifism","Silver Tongued"],"traits":[{"id":"memory-sharing","name":"Memory Sharing","description":"Caamasi can create strong, lasting memories and share them with others of their Species through an inborn telepathy. Sharing a memory begins with taking a Full-Round Action to initiate the link between two adjacent Caamasi; transferring a memory requires as much time as the events being recalled. The recipient of a memory must be willing to receive it. Experiencing Memniis not like receiving a photographic memory of those events, but rather a complete, immersive experience. Any character who receives a Memnis from a Caamasi always gains favorable circumstances on Knowledge checks related to that memory. Force-using characters can also receive Memnii from a Caamasi with a successful DC 15 Use the Force check, made as a Reaction."},{"id":"pacifism","name":"Pacifism","description":"As a Standard Action, a Caamasi can make a Persuasion check against the Will Defense of a single target within line of sight. If the check is successful, the target moves -1 step along the Condition Track if it makes any attacks before the start of the Caamasi's next turn. The target must be able to hear and understand the Caamasi for this ability to have any effect, and any single target can be affected only once at any given time (meaning that multiple Caamasi may not use this ability on the same target at the same time). This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"silver-tongued","name":"Silver Tongued","description":"Caamasi are skilled negotiators, and patient consulars. A Caamasi can choose to reroll any Persuasion check, using the better result."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":783},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-cathar","name":"Cathar","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Cathar.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":8,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Bonus Class Skills","Natural Weapons","Reactive Claw"],"languages":["Basic","Catharese"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"The Cathar are a proud, passionate, and loyal Species of bipedal feline humanoids, well known for their long-standing friendships and ferocity in battle. They dwell in large city-trees, each meticulously carved with friezes depicting the city's heroes and history. The planet Cathar is a wild place, with many ecological niches and huge insect predators. The Cathar easily hold their own, aided by their natural claws and passionate combat ability. Physically, the Cathar vary greatly in size and features.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":["Low-Light Vision"],"naturalWeapons":[{"name":"Claws","damage":"1d4","type":"slashing"}],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Scent: Can detect adjacent hidden creatures"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Cathar","movement":{"walk":8,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skills","name":"Bonus Class Skills","description":"A Cathar's inherent instincts make them naturally agile and silent, even without specialized training. A Cathar treats the Climb and Stealth skills as Class Skills, regardless of Heroic Class."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Cathar has Natural Weapons, in the form of razor-sharp claws. When a Cathar makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Cathar are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"reactive-claw","name":"Reactive Claw","description":"Once per encounter when a Cathar damages an opponent with a melee attack, the Cathar can make a single melee attack with its Natural Weapons against that target as a Swift Action. The Cathar must have one hand free at the time to make this attack (and thus cannot be wielding a two-handed weapon)."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":8,"movement":{"walk":8,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Cathar receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Intelligence. Cathar have fast reflexes and are light on their feet, but often focus less on academics.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Catharese"],"special":["Bonus Class Skills","Natural Weapons","Reactive Claw"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skills","name":"Bonus Class Skills","description":"A Cathar's inherent instincts make them naturally agile and silent, even without specialized training. A Cathar treats the Climb and Stealth skills as Class Skills, regardless of Heroic Class."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Cathar has Natural Weapons, in the form of razor-sharp claws. When a Cathar makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Cathar are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"reactive-claw","name":"Reactive Claw","description":"Once per encounter when a Cathar damages an opponent with a melee attack, the Cathar can make a single melee attack with its Natural Weapons against that target as a Swift Action. The Cathar must have one hand free at the time to make this attack (and thus cannot be wielding a two-handed weapon)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":568},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-celegian","name":"Celegian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Celegian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":10,"fly":6,"climb":null,"hover":6,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":10,"flySpeed":6,"hoverSpeed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Flight","Broadcast Telepath","Expert Swimmer","Special Equipment"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","description":"Celegians are capable of flight, but cannot do so if they are carrying a Heavy Load."},{"id":"broadcast-telepath","name":"Broadcast Telepath","description":"Celegians can use the Telepathy application of the Use the Force skill Untrained, even if they do not possess the Force Sensitivity feat. A Celegian automatically succeeds on this check to communicate with willing targets within 60 squares of it and in its line of sight."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Celegian may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Celegian may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Unless encased in a Celegian Life-Support Chamber, Celegians Suffocate."}],"languages":["Basic"],"description":"Celegians are an ancient Species known for their great intellect and wisdom. Evolved from ocean-dwelling invertebrates, the Celegians' ancestors eventually adapted to living on land. The atmosphere of their homeworld is rich in cyanogen gas, which is poisonous to most sentient beings. Conversely, oxygen is lethal to Celegians. To move their massive jellyfishlike bodies, Celegians evolved a natural form of locomotion similar to a repulsorlift generator.","canonicalName":"Celegian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":10,"fly":6,"climb":null,"hover":6,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Celegians receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Celegians are a thoughtful Species, but their unique physiology makes them less agile than others.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Flight","Broadcast Telepath","Expert Swimmer","Special Equipment"],"traits":[{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","description":"Celegians are capable of flight, but cannot do so if they are carrying a Heavy Load."},{"id":"broadcast-telepath","name":"Broadcast Telepath","description":"Celegians can use the Telepathy application of the Use the Force skill Untrained, even if they do not possess the Force Sensitivity feat. A Celegian automatically succeeds on this check to communicate with willing targets within 60 squares of it and in its line of sight."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Celegian may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Celegian may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Unless encased in a Celegian Life-Support Chamber, Celegians Suffocate."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1601},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-cerean","name":"Cerean","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Cerean.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Wis, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative","+2 Knowledge (Life Sciences)"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Intuitive Initiative"],"languages":["Basic","Cerean"],"source":"Core","description":"ereans are a sophisticated and cultured humanoid Species native to Cerea, a world on the fringes of known space. Their elongated heads distinguish them from most other humanoid Species. Cereans established contact with the rest of the galaxy shortly before the Galactic Republic was transformed into the Empire, swiftly gaining fame as expert astrogators, cryptographers, and economists. Few patterns or trends escape the notice of a Cerean. Cerean society is matriarchal, and the Cerean culture's traditional values emphasize living in harmony with nature and minimizing any impact on the environment from technology.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Cerean","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Cerean with Initiative as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Initiative) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"intuitive-initiative","name":"Intuitive Initiative","description":"Despite their general lack of coordination, Cereans' reaction speed is superior to that of most other Species. A Cerean may choose to reroll any Initiative check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Wis, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Cereans have a +2 bonus to both their Intelligence and their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Cereans are bright and intuitive but less coordinated than most other species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Cerean"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Intuitive Initiative"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Cerean with Initiative as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Initiative) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"intuitive-initiative","name":"Intuitive Initiative","description":"Despite their general lack of coordination, Cereans' reaction speed is superior to that of most other Species. A Cerean may choose to reroll any Initiative check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":61},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-chadra-fan","name":"Chadra-Fan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Chadra-Fan.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Mechanics"],"special":["Darkvision","Heightened Awareness","Quality Repairs"],"languages":["Basic","Chadra-Fan"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Known for being among the most cheerful and friendliest beings of the galaxy, Chadra-Fans are found in many places. On their native world, hurricanes and tsunamis frequently wipe out their homes, so the Chadra-Fans have developed an intense fear of water and choose new homes on arid planets. This experience with frequent destruction also leads them to regard few things as being truly permanent. Chadra-Fans embrace the moment and enjoy themselves as much as they can, living with a contagious zest for life. Chadra-Fans are notorious for their love of tinkering, frequently disassembling and reassembling unattended devices into something different.","tags":["small"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Chadra-Fan","variants":[{"id":"chadra-fan-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Darkvision","Tinkerer"],"languages":["Basic","Chadra-Fan"],"description":"Alternate Chadra-Fan trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Chadra-Fans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"tinkerer","name":"Tinkerer","description":"A Chadra-Fan may reroll any Mechanics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse. Whenever a Chadra-Fan Repairs or Jury-Rigs a droid or a device with a Mechanics check, the droid or device regains an additional 1d8 hit points. Additionally, Mechanics is always a class skill for a Chadra-Fan."}]}],"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Chadra-Fans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Chadra-Fan may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"quality-repairs","name":"Quality Repairs","description":"When a Chadra-Fan uses the Repair or Jury-Rig applications of the Mechanics skill, the target Droid or device regains an additional 1d8 Hit Points."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Chadra-Fans receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Chadra-Fans are quick and precise, but their curiosity often overrides their sense of self-preservation.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Chadra-Fan"],"special":["Darkvision","Heightened Awareness","Quality Repairs"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Chadra-Fans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Chadra-Fan may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"quality-repairs","name":"Quality Repairs","description":"When a Chadra-Fan uses the Repair or Jury-Rig applications of the Mechanics skill, the target Droid or device regains an additional 1d8 Hit Points."}],"variants":[{"id":"chadra-fan-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"cha":2,"wis":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Darkvision","Tinkerer"],"languages":["Basic","Chadra-Fan"],"description":"Alternate Chadra-Fan trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Chadra-Fans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"tinkerer","name":"Tinkerer","description":"A Chadra-Fan may reroll any Mechanics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse. Whenever a Chadra-Fan Repairs or Jury-Rigs a droid or a device with a Mechanics check, the droid or device regains an additional 1d8 hit points. Additionally, Mechanics is always a class skill for a Chadra-Fan."}]}],"sourceLine":2135},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-chagrian","name":"Chagrian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Chagrian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Breath Underwater","Low-Light Vision","Radiation Resistance","All Codru-Ji possess six limbs"],"languages":["Basic","Chagri"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Although juvenile Chagrians possess a weak sense of taste, this sense fades as they mature into adults. The end result is that Chagrians rarely, if ever, enjoy consuming food and drink, and do so solely to fuel their bodies. Dining activities are traditionally viewed as a nuisance, and a waste of time, so most Chagrians choose to consume nutrient capsules in order to maintain bodily health and energy levels. When traveling, most Chagrians carry portable scanners that allow them to determine the relative nutrient value of the food they eat. Although they are unable to taste the food they eat, Chagrians view dining as an opportunity to socialize with members of other Species that do not share their sensory deficiencies.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Chagrian","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"breath-underwater","name":"Breath Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Chagrians can't drown in water."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Chagrians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"radiation-resistance","name":"Radiation Resistance","description":"Chagrians receive a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against Radiation."},{"id":"all-codru-ji-possess-six-limbs","name":"All Codru-Ji possess six limbs","description":"four arms and two legs. In addition, juvenile Codru-Ji hardly resemble their parents as much as they resemble small, furred, hexapedal canines. Referred to as Wyrwulves, Codru-Ji children continue to grow and develop in their six-legged form until puberty, when they pupate in cocoons and emerge as bipedal adults."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Chagrians receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Chagrians are physically strong, but lack grace.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Chagri"],"special":["Breath Underwater","Low-Light Vision","Radiation Resistance","All Codru-Ji possess six limbs"],"traits":[{"id":"breath-underwater","name":"Breath Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Chagrians can't drown in water."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Chagrians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"radiation-resistance","name":"Radiation Resistance","description":"Chagrians receive a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against Radiation."},{"id":"all-codru-ji-possess-six-limbs","name":"All Codru-Ji possess six limbs","description":"four arms and two legs. In addition, juvenile Codru-Ji hardly resemble their parents as much as they resemble small, furred, hexapedal canines. Referred to as Wyrwulves, Codru-Ji children continue to grow and develop in their six-legged form until puberty, when they pupate in cocoons and emerge as bipedal adults."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1420},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-chevin","name":"Chevin","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Chevin.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Persuasion"],"special":[],"languages":["Chevin","Basic"],"source":"FU","description":"","tags":[],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":["Heavy Build: Count as Large for carrying capacity only"]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Chevin","suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-chiss","name":"Chiss","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Chiss.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative"],"special":[],"languages":["Cheunh","Basic"],"source":"Core","description":"","tags":[],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":["Cold Resistance: +5 to Endurance vs cold"],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Chiss","suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-chistori","name":"Chistori","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Chistori.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Cold-Blooded","Damage Reduction","Rage"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"cold-blooded","name":"Cold-Blooded","description":"Chistori are very sensitive to cold climates. A Chistori takes a -5 penalty to their Fortitude Defense to resist Extreme Cold."},{"id":"damage-reduction","name":"Damage Reduction","description":"Chistori have thick scales that provide Damage Reduction 2."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Chistori can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While raging, the Chistori temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Chistori's Constitution modifier. At the end of it's rage, the Chistori moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Chistori takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Chistori can't engage in any strenuous activity."}],"languages":["Chistori"],"description":"The Chistori are a race of obscure saurian humanoids. So scarce is the information of these people that even the Jedi Archives have no information on the Chistori homeworld. What little is known about this Species comes from their interactions with others. Fierce and warlike, they are quick to anger and tend to use excessive force to deal with even the smallest slights. As a result, few spacefaring Species have any reason to seek them out.","canonicalName":"Chistori","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Chistori receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Chistori are strong, but their bodies are slow and sometimes ponderous.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Chistori"],"special":["Cold-Blooded","Damage Reduction","Rage"],"traits":[{"id":"cold-blooded","name":"Cold-Blooded","description":"Chistori are very sensitive to cold climates. A Chistori takes a -5 penalty to their Fortitude Defense to resist Extreme Cold."},{"id":"damage-reduction","name":"Damage Reduction","description":"Chistori have thick scales that provide Damage Reduction 2."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Chistori can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While raging, the Chistori temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Chistori's Constitution modifier. At the end of it's rage, the Chistori moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Chistori takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Chistori can't engage in any strenuous activity."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":456},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":2900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-clawdite","name":"Clawdite","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Clawdite.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Deception","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Shapeshift","Startle"],"languages":["Basic","Clawdite"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Only after the fall of the Empire did the Clawdites finally rise up against the Zolanders, fighting a brutal civil war that consumed the world in violence. The Clawdites eventually gained control of the planet, and in victory, they assert themselves as the dominant Species. Free, the Clawdites courted the New Republic, and threw their support behind Alliance Intelligence organizations, using their unique talents to infiltrate the Yuuzhan Vong, and sabotaged equipment, gathered intelligence, and assassinated critical targets. The Clawdites took on this dangerous work because they are driven to support the cause of liberty, and for them, the end always justifies the means.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Clawdite","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"shapeshift","name":"Shapeshift","description":"Clawdites are shapechangers and can alter their appearance at will (see the Deception skill). While Shapeshifted, a Clawdite gains a +10 Species bonus on Deception checks made to disguise appearance. Additionally, a Clawdite can disguise its appearance as a Full-Round Action at no penalty. Clawdites cannot alter their size without the Metamorph feat."},{"id":"startle","name":"Startle","description":"Once per encounter, as a Reaction to being attacked, a Clawdite can make a Deception check against the target's Will Defense. If successful, the attacker takes a -5 penalty on their attack roll."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Clawdites receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Clawdites are frailer than other Species, but are extremely adept at masking their appearance.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Clawdite"],"special":["Shapeshift","Startle"],"traits":[{"id":"shapeshift","name":"Shapeshift","description":"Clawdites are shapechangers and can alter their appearance at will (see the Deception skill). While Shapeshifted, a Clawdite gains a +10 Species bonus on Deception checks made to disguise appearance. Additionally, a Clawdite can disguise its appearance as a Full-Round Action at no penalty. Clawdites cannot alter their size without the Metamorph feat."},{"id":"startle","name":"Startle","description":"Once per encounter, as a Reaction to being attacked, a Clawdite can make a Deception check against the target's Will Defense. If successful, the attacker takes a -5 penalty on their attack roll."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1011},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-codru-ji","name":"Codru-Ji","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Codru-Ji.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":[],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Extra Arms","Skilled Grappler"],"languages":["Basic","Codruese"],"source":"Core","description":"The Codru-Ji have long been isolated from the rest of the galaxy. Highly xenophobic, they are reluctant to grant members of other Species access to their society. Though they do not fear other cultures, they are concerned that outsiders will somehow \"rub off\" on them and corrupt their own traditions and values. Chdru-Ji Certain aspects of Codru-Ji culture is barbaric by galactic standards. Ritual kidnapping, especially the children of political rivals, is common.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Codru-Ji","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Codru-Ji gains the Dual Weapon Mastery I feat as a bonus Feat provided he or she meets the prerequisites of the Feat (minimum Dexterity of 13 and Base Attack Bonus of +1)."},{"id":"extra-arms","name":"Extra Arms","description":"Codru-Ji can hold up to four items or Weapons at a time. This ability does not grant extra attacks; however, it does mean a Codru-Ji can wield two two-handed weapons at a time."},{"id":"skilled-grappler","name":"Skilled Grappler","description":"Due to their extra arms, Codru-Ji gain a +5 Species bonus to both Grab and Grapple checks."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"None. Codru-Ji are skilled in many crafts, and are widely versatile.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Codruese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Extra Arms","Skilled Grappler"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Codru-Ji gains the Dual Weapon Mastery I feat as a bonus Feat provided he or she meets the prerequisites of the Feat (minimum Dexterity of 13 and Base Attack Bonus of +1)."},{"id":"extra-arms","name":"Extra Arms","description":"Codru-Ji can hold up to four items or Weapons at a time. This ability does not grant extra attacks; however, it does mean a Codru-Ji can wield two two-handed weapons at a time."},{"id":"skilled-grappler","name":"Skilled Grappler","description":"Due to their extra arms, Codru-Ji gain a +5 Species bonus to both Grab and Grapple checks."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1450},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-dashade","name":"Dashade","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Dashade.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth"],"special":["Environmental Adaptation","Force Resistance","Frightening Visage"],"languages":["Dashadi"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"The Dashade work as mercenaries and bodyguards for many groups. Most notably though, Dashade work for the various Sith uprisings; even though the Sith are directly responsible for the Cron Cluster supernova that destroys the Dashade homeworld thousands of years before the Galactic Civil War. Even with the loss of their homeworld, the Dashade avoid extinction. Their exact numbers remain unknown, but reports suggest that the Dashade were able to establish one or more colonies far outside their home system prior to the Cron Cluster disaster.","tags":["force","medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Dashade","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"environmental-adaptation","name":"Environmental Adaptation","description":"Because of the unforgiving nature of their homeworld, Dashade gain a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against the effects of Extreme Temperatures and Radiation."},{"id":"force-resistance","name":"Force Resistance","description":"Dashade receive a +5 bonus to their Will Defense against any use of the Use the Force skill."},{"id":"frightening-visage","name":"Frightening Visage","description":"A Dashade may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate, keeping the better of the two results."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Dashade receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Charisma. Dashade are remarkably agile given their impressive size, but they have difficulty recognizing threats and interacting with others because of their sense of superiority and their secretive nature.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Dashadi"],"special":["Environmental Adaptation","Force Resistance","Frightening Visage"],"traits":[{"id":"environmental-adaptation","name":"Environmental Adaptation","description":"Because of the unforgiving nature of their homeworld, Dashade gain a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against the effects of Extreme Temperatures and Radiation."},{"id":"force-resistance","name":"Force Resistance","description":"Dashade receive a +5 bonus to their Will Defense against any use of the Use the Force skill."},{"id":"frightening-visage","name":"Frightening Visage","description":"A Dashade may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate, keeping the better of the two results."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1680},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-defel","name":"Defel","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Defel.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth","+2 Perception"],"special":["Partial Invisibility","Special Equipment"],"languages":["Basic","Defel"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Defel come from the High Gravity world of Af'El, which orbits the supergiant Ka'Dedus. The planet is unusual in that the atmosphere absorbs all light except that in the ultraviolet spectrum. The Defel, along with every other animal on the planet, have evolved to see perfectly well in ultraviolet, but they are completely Blind when exposed to other wavelengths of light. Defel that leave their homeworld must wear special visors that allow them to see. This evolution also had an interesting effect on Defel fur, making the creatures effectively invisible in the normal light in which most other Species operate.","tags":["small"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Defel","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"partial-invisibility","name":"Partial Invisibility","description":"The fur of a Defel helps bend all but ultraviolet light, rendering him or her nearly invisible. A Defel in shadowy illumination or darker conditions is treated as having Total Concealment. Defel are fully visible and gain no Concealment against opponents with Darkvision."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"The eyes of Defel have evolved in such a way that they can see only in the ultraviolet spectrum. Defel that leave Af'El must wear special ultraviolet visors to see in normal light. Without such a visor, a Defel is considered Blind. An ultraviolet visor costs 2000 credits. A Defel character begins play with this item at no cost."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Defel receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Defel have slight builds but keen, probing minds.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Defel"],"special":["Partial Invisibility","Special Equipment"],"traits":[{"id":"partial-invisibility","name":"Partial Invisibility","description":"The fur of a Defel helps bend all but ultraviolet light, rendering him or her nearly invisible. A Defel in shadowy illumination or darker conditions is treated as having Total Concealment. Defel are fully visible and gain no Concealment against opponents with Darkvision."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"The eyes of Defel have evolved in such a way that they can see only in the ultraviolet spectrum. Defel that leave Af'El must wear special ultraviolet visors to see in normal light. Without such a visor, a Defel is considered Blind. An ultraviolet visor costs 2000 credits. A Defel character begins play with this item at no cost."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1845},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-devaronian","name":"Devaronian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Devaronian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Natural Curiosity"],"languages":["Basic","Devaronese"],"source":"Core","description":"Devaronians are among the first Species in the galaxy to develop interstellar travel, and the males of the species have been common sights in spaceports throughout the galaxy for thousands of years. After reaching middle age, Devaronian males are driven by an urge to wander. As such, they are often found traveling the galaxy as tramp freighter captains and scouts. Female Devaronians, on the other hand, are content to remain in a single location, and as such, raise the young and run the government of Devaron. The males send as much money as they can back to their families on Devaron, but they seldom return to the homeworld.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":["Heat Resistance: +5 to Endurance vs heat"],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"variants":[{"id":"devaronian-female","label":"Female","source":"Clone Wars","size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Persuasion"],"special":[],"languages":["Basic","Devaronese"],"description":"","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}}}],"canonicalName":"Devaronian","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Devaronians are master manipulators. A Devaronian with Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"natural-curiosity","name":"Natural Curiosity","description":"Because of their natural curiosity, Devaronians are very attentive to small details that can reveal weaknesses. Once per encounter as a Standard Action, a Devaronian can make a Perception check against a single target within line of sight (DC 15 or the result of an opposed Stealth check, if the target is actively attempting to hide). If successful, the Devaronian gains a +1 insight bonus on attack rolls against that target."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Male Devaronians tend to be more carefree and less personable than female Devaronians, but they are also more agile. All male Devaronians receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Charisma. All female Devaronians +2 bonuses to both their Intelligence and Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Devaronese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Natural Curiosity"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Devaronians are master manipulators. A Devaronian with Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"natural-curiosity","name":"Natural Curiosity","description":"Because of their natural curiosity, Devaronians are very attentive to small details that can reveal weaknesses. Once per encounter as a Standard Action, a Devaronian can make a Perception check against a single target within line of sight (DC 15 or the result of an opposed Stealth check, if the target is actively attempting to hide). If successful, the Devaronian gains a +1 insight bonus on attack rolls against that target."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2526},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-draethos","name":"Draethos","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Draethos.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision","Natural Armor","Natural Telepath"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Draethos gain Weapon Proficiency (Advanced Melee Weapons) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Draethos ignore Concealment from darkness (but not Total Concealment)."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"The Daethos's tough skin provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense."},{"id":"natural-telepath","name":"Natural Telepath","description":"A Draethos gains a +5 Species bonus using the Telepathy aspect of the Use the Force skill and can make Untrained Use the Force checks to use this application even without the Force Sensitivity feat."}],"languages":["Basic","Draethos"],"description":"Draethos residing offworld are usually exiles who chose not to become warriors, each for his own reason. Thus, they are highly intelligent and pacifistic. Exiled Draethos become enthralled with learning as much as they can, though they might never practically apply their detailed knowledge of a given subject. They dislike debate- even on subject they know extremely well- because Draethos fear overlooking details or being unable to adequately explain what they have learned. Older Draethos eventually overcome this barrier.","canonicalName":"Draethos","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Draethos receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Draethos have a hardy and durable structure, but due to their foreign and alien nature have trouble integrating socially.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Draethos"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision","Natural Armor","Natural Telepath"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Draethos gain Weapon Proficiency (Advanced Melee Weapons) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Draethos ignore Concealment from darkness (but not Total Concealment)."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"The Daethos's tough skin provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense."},{"id":"natural-telepath","name":"Natural Telepath","description":"A Draethos gains a +5 Species bonus using the Telepathy aspect of the Use the Force skill and can make Untrained Use the Force checks to use this application even without the Force Sensitivity feat."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":587},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-drall","name":"Drall","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Drall.jpg","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Knowledge (Bureaucracy)","+2 Use Computer"],"special":["Analytical Sense"],"languages":["Drallese","Basic"],"source":"Corella System","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Drall","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-dressellian","name":"Dressellian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Dressellian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival","+2 Perception"],"special":["Primitive"],"languages":["Dressellese","Basic"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"","tags":["primitive"],"costNumeric":null,"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Dressellian","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-dug","name":"Dug","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Dug.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Athletic"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"athletic","name":"Athletic","description":"A Dug can reroll any Climb or Jump check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Dug can Take 10 on Climb and Jump checks even when distracted or threatened."}],"languages":["Dug"],"description":"Dugs are an arboreal Species from the Republic world of Malastare. They are strong and agile for their size, and climb and jump exceptionally well. Dugs unwillingly share their homeworld with the Gran, who establish trade colonies on Malastare in 8,000 BBY. The Dugs fight a long, intense war against the Gran. Eventually the Republic interferes and sides with the Gran, negotiating a truce that essentially demilitarizes the Dugs.","canonicalName":"Dug","canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Dugs receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Dugs possess excellent reflexes and hand-eye coordination, but they rarely think before they act and are known for their crude demeanor.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Dug"],"special":["Athletic"],"traits":[{"id":"athletic","name":"Athletic","description":"A Dug can reroll any Climb or Jump check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Dug can Take 10 on Climb and Jump checks even when distracted or threatened."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1190},"tags":["small"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-duros","name":"Duros","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Duros.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Int, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Pilot","+2 Knowledge (Galactic Lore)"],"special":["Expert Pilot"],"languages":["Basic","Durese"],"source":"Core","description":"Tall, hairless humanoids from the Duro System, Duros were one of the first Species to become a major influence in the Galactic Republic, and many respected scholars credited the Duros with creating the first hyperdrive. The Duros have a natural affinity for space travel, possessing an innate grasp of the mathematical underpinnings of astrogational computations. Many tales are swapped in cantinas about Duros astrogators calculating the coordinates for supposedly impossible jumps in their heads. Although not as numerous as Humans, the Duros are almost as omnipresent; all but the smallest settlements in known space feature Duros populations. The Duros Species has existed on other worlds in isolation from the rest of their kind, evolving in slight different directions from the baseline Species.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Duros","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"expert-pilot","name":"Expert Pilot","description":"As natural spacers, a Duros may choose to reroll any Pilot check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Int, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Duros have a +2 bonus to both Dexterity and Intelligence, and suffer a -2 penalty to Constitution. Duros are agile in mind and body but they aren't physically hardy people.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Durese"],"special":["Expert Pilot"],"traits":[{"id":"expert-pilot","name":"Expert Pilot","description":"As natural spacers, a Duros may choose to reroll any Pilot check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":77},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":3900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ebruchi","name":"Ebruchi","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ebruchi.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"special":["Bonus Feat","Iron Will","Unsettling"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Ebruchi are naturally tough and resilient. Ebruchi gain Improved Damage Threshold as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Ebruchi are headstrong and stubborn. They gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"unsettling","name":"Unsettling","description":"Most Species find Ebruchi physical traits and habits unsettling. Once per encounter, when an Ebruchi successfully uses the Persuasion skill to Intimidate a target, the Ebruchi can move the target -1 step on the Condition Track instead of applying one of the standard Intimidation effects. The target must be within 6 squares of the Ebruchi, and the effect lasts until the end of the encounter. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."}],"languages":["Ebruchese"],"description":"The Ebruchi style of dress matches their stereotype as uncivilized, opportunistic pirates. A typical outfit consists of layers of animal skins topped with shiny medallions, rings, or crowns. But those who think that an Ebruchi's appearance is lazily haphazard are mistaken. The Ebruchi put great thought into the placement of each item and layer, and all clothing is tended with exquisite care. Patches, scarves, necklaces, and intentional holes and tears are all signs of rank and achievement, although the nuances of the arrangements are lost on non-Ebruchi.","canonicalName":"Ebruchi","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Ebruchi receive +2 bonuses to both their Strength and Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to their Wisdom and Charisma. Ebruchi are strong and physically resilient but arrogant and repulsive to most other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Ebruchese"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Iron Will","Unsettling"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Ebruchi are naturally tough and resilient. Ebruchi gain Improved Damage Threshold as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Ebruchi are headstrong and stubborn. They gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"unsettling","name":"Unsettling","description":"Most Species find Ebruchi physical traits and habits unsettling. Once per encounter, when an Ebruchi successfully uses the Persuasion skill to Intimidate a target, the Ebruchi can move the target -1 step on the Condition Track instead of applying one of the standard Intimidation effects. The target must be within 6 squares of the Ebruchi, and the effect lasts until the end of the encounter. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2165},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-elom","name":"Elom","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Elom.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Burrowing Claws"],"languages":["Elom","Basic"],"source":"FU","description":"Culturally, the Elomin try to discover or create order in all things. They view the universe as a logical, organized puzzle, and endeavor to find the pieces and bring them to their logical places. When confronted with something that doesn't fit into the pattern they have defined, they may try to redefine the pattern, but are just as likely to attempt to ignore the discordant details. Such was the case when the Elomin first discovered the existence of the underground-dwelling Eloms, another sentient Species native to their world. The Elomin first denied the existence of the Eloms, and then later denied they were sentient.","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Elom","variants":[{"id":"elomite-variant","label":"Elomite Variant","source":"Rebellion","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"languages":["Elom","Basic"],"special":["Burrowing"],"traits":[{"id":"burrowing","name":"Burrowing","description":"This alternate Elom profile uses the variant burrowing trait package."}],"description":"Culturally, the Elomin try to discover or create order in all things. They view the universe as a logical, organized puzzle, and endeavor to find the pieces and bring them to their logical places. When confronted with something that doesn't fit into the pattern they have defined, they may try to redefine the pattern, but are just as likely to attempt to ignore the discordant details. Such was the case when the Elomin first discovered the existence of the underground-dwelling Eloms, another sentient Species native to their world. The Elomin first denied the existence of the Eloms, and then later denied they were sentient.","notes":"Collapsed from the former separate Elomite (Variant) species row."}],"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-elomin","name":"Elomin","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Elomin.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Knowledge (Galactic Lore)"],"special":["Driven","Impose Order"],"languages":["Basic","Elomin"],"source":"FU","description":"Culturally, the Elomin try to discover or create order in all things. They view the universe as a logical, organized puzzle, and endeavor to find the pieces and bring them to their logical places. When confronted with something that doesn't fit into the pattern they have defined, they may try to redefine the pattern, but are just as likely to attempt to ignore the discordant details. Such was the case when the Elomin first discovered the existence of the underground-dwelling Eloms, another sentient Species native to their world. The Elomin first denied the existence of the Eloms, and then later denied they were sentient.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Elomin","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"driven","name":"Driven","description":"Elomin gain a +5 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Mind-Affecting effects."},{"id":"impose-order","name":"Impose Order","description":"Elomin are exceptionally focused on order, and strive to ensure that their chaotic companions are in the place where they are supposed to be. Once per encounter, an Elomin can spend a Swift Action to allow each ally within 12 squares to move up to half that ally's Speed as a Reaction. This movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Elomin receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Elomin have trouble relating to other Species, but they are exceptionally good at a number of intellectual pursuits.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Elomin"],"special":["Driven","Impose Order"],"traits":[{"id":"driven","name":"Driven","description":"Elomin gain a +5 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Mind-Affecting effects."},{"id":"impose-order","name":"Impose Order","description":"Elomin are exceptionally focused on order, and strive to ensure that their chaotic companions are in the place where they are supposed to be. Once per encounter, an Elomin can spend a Swift Action to allow each ally within 12 squares to move up to half that ally's Speed as a Reaction. This movement does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1863},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ewok","name":"Ewok","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ewok.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth","+2 Survival"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Primitive","Scent","Sneaky"],"languages":["Ewokese"],"source":"Core","description":"Intelligent omnivores native to one of the moons orbiting Endor, Ewoks are almost unknown prior to the battle of Endor. Ewoks live in tree-dwelling tribes with gender-based division of labor; males hunt, forage, and make weapons, while females raise young and handle other domestic tasks. Ewok culture revolves around complex animistic beliefs involving the giant trees of the forest moon. Although technologically primitive, Ewoks are clever, inquisitive, and inventive. Skittish and wary when first introduced to machines, their curiosity soon overcomes fear.","tags":["primitive","small"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":["Primitive: –5 penalty on Use Computer, Mechanics, and attack rolls with modern weapons"],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Ewok","movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ewoks are skilled foragers. An Ewok with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Ewoks do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Ewoks have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Ewoks ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."},{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"An Ewok may choose to reroll any Stealth check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Ewoks receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Ewoks are very agile but somewhat weak.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Ewokese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Primitive","Scent","Sneaky"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ewoks are skilled foragers. An Ewok with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Ewoks do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Ewoks have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Ewoks ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."},{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"An Ewok may choose to reroll any Stealth check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":93},"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-falleen","name":"Falleen","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Falleen.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Hold Breath","Pheromones","Pheromone Acclimation"],"languages":["Basic","Falleen"],"source":"Scum & Villainy","description":"Of all the Species to populate the galaxy, none are better known for their intoxicating appearance than the Falleen. An exotic reptilian people, they are favored for their chiseled physiques and entrancing features. These qualities alone would solidify their place among the more handsome Species, but their pheromones make them irresistible to other Species. Their gifts and allure enable the Falleen to move through other cultures with ease, but despite their advantages, Falleen prefer to remain mysterious, withdrawing to their own world in their own system. They do not lack the technology or wherewithal to venture out into the stars, but their cultural predilections make such ventures undesirable.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Pheromones: +5 to Persuasion checks once per encounter"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Falleen","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"hold-breath","name":"Hold Breath","description":"Falleen are at home in air or water. A Falleen can hold their breath for a number of rounds equal to 25 times their Constitution score before they need to start making Endurance checks."},{"id":"pheromones","name":"Pheromones","description":"As a Standard Action, a Falleen can make a special attack against any adjacent creature. The attack modifier is equal to the Falleen's Character Level plus their Charisma modifier. If the attack equals or exceeds the target's Fortitude Defense, that target moves -1 step along the Condition Track. If the attack fails to beat the target's Fortitude Defense, the target is immune to the Falleen's Pheromones for 24 hours. When the target is reduced to a total of -5 steps, instead of Falling Unconscious, the target's Attitude improves to Friendly. Pheromones function as an Inhaled Poison. Any creature holding its breath is unaffected (see Endurance for more details). A creature can be affected by Falleen Pheromones only once per round. Multiple exposures to Pheromones from different Falleen in the same round produce no additional effects. A Hostile creature cannot be targeted by this effect."},{"id":"pheromone-acclimation","name":"Pheromone Acclimation","description":"Falleen gain a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against the Pheromones of other Falleen."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Falleen receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Falleen posses uncommon magnetism and great interpersonal skills.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Falleen"],"special":["Hold Breath","Pheromones","Pheromone Acclimation"],"traits":[{"id":"hold-breath","name":"Hold Breath","description":"Falleen are at home in air or water. A Falleen can hold their breath for a number of rounds equal to 25 times their Constitution score before they need to start making Endurance checks."},{"id":"pheromones","name":"Pheromones","description":"As a Standard Action, a Falleen can make a special attack against any adjacent creature. The attack modifier is equal to the Falleen's Character Level plus their Charisma modifier. If the attack equals or exceeds the target's Fortitude Defense, that target moves -1 step along the Condition Track. If the attack fails to beat the target's Fortitude Defense, the target is immune to the Falleen's Pheromones for 24 hours. When the target is reduced to a total of -5 steps, instead of Falling Unconscious, the target's Attitude improves to Friendly. Pheromones function as an Inhaled Poison. Any creature holding its breath is unaffected (see Endurance for more details). A creature can be affected by Falleen Pheromones only once per round. Multiple exposures to Pheromones from different Falleen in the same round produce no additional effects. A Hostile creature cannot be targeted by this effect."},{"id":"pheromone-acclimation","name":"Pheromone Acclimation","description":"Falleen gain a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against the Pheromones of other Falleen."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1030},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-feeorin","name":"Feeorin","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Feeorin.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Brutal","Great Fortitude","Inborn Resilience","Low-Light Vision","Stronger by Age"],"languages":["Basic"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"In The Old Republic Era, the Feeorin are known to come from the planet Odryn, a planet of severe climatic extremes. Little else is known about the world, given the closed nature of Feeorin society. Few Feeorin venture from their homeworld, and those few outsiders who have survived a visit there tell of a world well suited for the Feeorin, but nobody else. Feeorin are massive humanoids whose aging process allows them to grow stronger and more powerful until they die, dropping dead suddenly of old age. Because they are long-lived, they have ample time to gather and use their strength.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Feeorin","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"brutal","name":"Brutal","description":"Feeorin are vicious combatants who do not hesitate to strike vulnerable areas or fight dirty. Once per encounter, after making a successful melee attack, a Feeorin may treat its opponent's Damage Threshold as though it were 5 points lower when determining the result of the attack."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Feeorin gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense, accounting for their great physical condition."},{"id":"inborn-resilience","name":"Inborn Resilience","description":"Feeorin are highly resilient to physical attack. A Feeorin can catch a Second Wind even when unconscious (no Action required, but the Second Wind can only be taken when the Feeorin would normally get a turn). Catching a Second Wind while unconscious also move the Feeorin +3 steps on the Condition Track."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Feeorin ignore Concealment from darkness (but not Total Concealment)."},{"id":"stronger-by-age","name":"Stronger by Age","description":"At Middle Age, a Feeorin adds a +1 Species bonus to their Strength and Constitution scores. At Old, this bonus increases to +2. Feeorin do not increase their Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma; nor decrease their Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution as they Age."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Feeorin receive a +2 bonus to both their Strength and Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to their Dexterity, Wisdom, and Charisma. Feeorin are big and brawny, but tend to be blunt and short-tempered.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Brutal","Great Fortitude","Inborn Resilience","Low-Light Vision","Stronger by Age"],"traits":[{"id":"brutal","name":"Brutal","description":"Feeorin are vicious combatants who do not hesitate to strike vulnerable areas or fight dirty. Once per encounter, after making a successful melee attack, a Feeorin may treat its opponent's Damage Threshold as though it were 5 points lower when determining the result of the attack."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Feeorin gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense, accounting for their great physical condition."},{"id":"inborn-resilience","name":"Inborn Resilience","description":"Feeorin are highly resilient to physical attack. A Feeorin can catch a Second Wind even when unconscious (no Action required, but the Second Wind can only be taken when the Feeorin would normally get a turn). Catching a Second Wind while unconscious also move the Feeorin +3 steps on the Condition Track."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Feeorin ignore Concealment from darkness (but not Total Concealment)."},{"id":"stronger-by-age","name":"Stronger by Age","description":"At Middle Age, a Feeorin adds a +1 Species bonus to their Strength and Constitution scores. At Old, this bonus increases to +2. Feeorin do not increase their Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma; nor decrease their Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution as they Age."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":604},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-felucian","name":"Felucian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Felucian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Feat","Breathe Underwater","Low-Light Vision","Natural Camouflage","Force Blast","Primitive","Weapon Familiarity"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Felucians receive the Force Sensitivity feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Felucians can't drown in water."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Felucians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-camouflage","name":"Natural Camouflage","description":"A Felucian can choose to reroll any Stealth check to Sneak, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"force-blast","name":"Force Blast","description":"Once per encounter a Felucian can make an Untrained Use the Force check to activate the Force Blast Force Power. A Felucian who takes the Force Training feat automatically adds a single use of the Force Blast Force Power to his or her Force Power Suite (for free) instead of this ability."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Felucians do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Felucians treat the Felucian Skullblade as a Simple Weapon (Melee) instead of an Exotic Weapon (Melee)."}],"languages":["Felucianese"],"description":"The Felucians are an unusual, amphibious Species. They are highly adapted to surviving the wilds of their home planet, and fade easily into its confusing mass of plant life. They are equally at home on land or in water, and they traverse the swamps with ease. All Felucians are part of a single, planetwide tribe that is broken down into smaller villages and communities, each one led by Felucian Shamans and chieftains. These Felucian Shamans are very strong in The Force, using it to their own ends with incredible skill.","canonicalName":"Felucian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Felucians receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Intelligence. Felucians must be tough to compete with the dangerous plants and animals of their homeworld, but they live in a relatively primitive state.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Felucianese"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Breathe Underwater","Low-Light Vision","Natural Camouflage","Force Blast","Primitive","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Felucians receive the Force Sensitivity feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Felucians can't drown in water."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Felucians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-camouflage","name":"Natural Camouflage","description":"A Felucian can choose to reroll any Stealth check to Sneak, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"force-blast","name":"Force Blast","description":"Once per encounter a Felucian can make an Untrained Use the Force check to activate the Force Blast Force Power. A Felucian who takes the Force Training feat automatically adds a single use of the Force Blast Force Power to his or her Force Power Suite (for free) instead of this ability."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Felucians do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Felucians treat the Felucian Skullblade as a Simple Weapon (Melee) instead of an Exotic Weapon (Melee)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":807},"tags":["force","medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-fosh","name":"Fosh","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Fosh.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Cha, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Acrobatics","+2 Perception"],"special":["Deceptive","Healing Glands"],"languages":["Basic","Fosh"],"source":"Legacy","description":"Almost completely unknown by the rest of the galaxy, Fosh are an avianlike Species that hail from an unknown planet. Outwardly quiet, reserved, and thoughtful, in truth Fosh are contemptuous of other Species and consider all non-Fosh to be inferior. Fosh keep this condescension and bigotry to themselves, however. They are remarkably manipulative and are masters of intrigue, deal making, and deception. Only Bothans are more skilled at pulling the strings of others.","tags":["small"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Fosh","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"A Fosh may reroll any Deception check, but must accept the result of the reroll, even if it is worse."},{"id":"healing-glands","name":"Healing Glands","description":"Fosh can exude a powerful fluid from their tear ducts that can aid in the healing process for most Species. A Fosh is always considered to have a Medpac or Medical Kit for the purposes of making Treat Injury checks, and can perform Trained Only applications of the Treat Injury skill even when Untrained."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Fosh receive +2 bonuses to their Dexterity and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Fosh are nimble and persuasive, but they possess frail and delicate bones.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Fosh"],"special":["Deceptive","Healing Glands"],"traits":[{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"A Fosh may reroll any Deception check, but must accept the result of the reroll, even if it is worse."},{"id":"healing-glands","name":"Healing Glands","description":"Fosh can exude a powerful fluid from their tear ducts that can aid in the healing process for most Species. A Fosh is always considered to have a Medpac or Medical Kit for the purposes of making Treat Injury checks, and can perform Trained Only applications of the Treat Injury skill even when Untrained."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1880},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-gamorrean","name":"Gamorrean","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gamorrean.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Feat","Great Fortitude","Primitive","Weapon Familiarity (Arg'garok)"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Gamorreans gain Improved Damage Threshold as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Gamorreans gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense, accounting for their great physical resistance."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Gamorreans do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity-arg-garok","name":"Weapon Familiarity (Arg'garok)","description":"Gamorreans treat the Arg'garok as an Advanced Melee Weapon, instead of an Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"languages":["Gamorrean","Basic"],"description":"Gamorreans are green-skinned, porcine creatures native to Gamorr. Their tendency toward violence makes them valued as criminal enforcers; though viewed as mindless brutes, they don't care so long as they are paid to fight. Gamorrean civilization revolves around the never-ending wars between their clans. Preferring large melee weapon in combat, many see ranged weapons as cowardly. Males live to fight; females farm, hunt, and manufacture weapons.","canonicalName":"Gamorrean","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Gamorreans have a +2 bonus to Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to both their Dexterity and Intelligence. Gamorreans possess greater physical power, but have limited agility and intelligence.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Gamorrean","Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Great Fortitude","Primitive","Weapon Familiarity (Arg'garok)"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Gamorreans gain Improved Damage Threshold as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Gamorreans gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense, accounting for their great physical resistance."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Gamorreans do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity-arg-garok","name":"Weapon Familiarity (Arg'garok)","description":"Gamorreans treat the Arg'garok as an Advanced Melee Weapon, instead of an Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":120},"tags":["medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":4900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-gand","name":"Gand","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gand.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"special":["Darkvision","Hardy","Limb Regeneration","Special Equipment","Weapon Familiarity"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Gand ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"hardy","name":"Hardy","description":"Gand are tough and resilient, capable of shrugging off injuries that would cripple other Species. Whenever a Gand uses their Second Wind, they regain a number of additional Hit Points equal to 5 + its Character Level."},{"id":"limb-regeneration","name":"Limb Regeneration","description":"A Gand can regrow a lost limb in 1d10 days. At the end of this time, all Persistent penalties associated with the loss of the limb are removed."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"The dependence of Gand on the atmosphere of their homeworld restricts their ability to leave without use of specialized equipment. Without a Breathing Apparatus, a Gand would Suffocate. Without a Transliterator, a Gand cannot communicate in any language other than Gand. A Breathing Apparatus costs 2000 credits, and a year's supply of breathing filters cost 200 credits (50 credits on Gand). A Transliterator costs 100 credits. A Gand character begins play with these items at no cost."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Gand do not treat Gand Weapons as Exotic Weapons, instead treating them as a base item (for instance, a Gand Blaster Rifle would still be treated as a Rifle)."}],"languages":["Gand"],"description":"A strange Species of insect creatures, the Gand have evolved in response to the toxic atmosphere of their homeworld. In fact, two distinct types of Gand exist. The more common has features typical of other Species- lungs and the usual assortment of internal organs. The other type- rarely found outside Gand- has no lungs, and takes in the nutrients it needs through the materials it consumes. Since the Gand cannot tolerate other atmospheres, and outsiders cannot breathe Gand's atmosphere, the Species of this far-flung world developed without outside interference, resulting in a rich culture with particularities.","canonicalName":"Gand","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Gand receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Gand society values wisdom and cunning, but their off-putting appearance and strange manner make them difficult to understand.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Gand"],"special":["Darkvision","Hardy","Limb Regeneration","Special Equipment","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Gand ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"hardy","name":"Hardy","description":"Gand are tough and resilient, capable of shrugging off injuries that would cripple other Species. Whenever a Gand uses their Second Wind, they regain a number of additional Hit Points equal to 5 + its Character Level."},{"id":"limb-regeneration","name":"Limb Regeneration","description":"A Gand can regrow a lost limb in 1d10 days. At the end of this time, all Persistent penalties associated with the loss of the limb are removed."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"The dependence of Gand on the atmosphere of their homeworld restricts their ability to leave without use of specialized equipment. Without a Breathing Apparatus, a Gand would Suffocate. Without a Transliterator, a Gand cannot communicate in any language other than Gand. A Breathing Apparatus costs 2000 credits, and a year's supply of breathing filters cost 200 credits (50 credits on Gand). A Transliterator costs 100 credits. A Gand character begins play with these items at no cost."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Gand do not treat Gand Weapons as Exotic Weapons, instead treating them as a base item (for instance, a Gand Blaster Rifle would still be treated as a Rifle)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1051},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[{"id":"gand-force-sensitive","label":"Force-Sensitive","source":"KOTOR","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"skillBonuses":["+2 Perception"],"special":[],"languages":["Gand"],"description":"A strange Species of insect creatures, the Gand have evolved in response to the toxic atmosphere of their homeworld. In fact, two distinct types of Gand exist. The more common has features typical of other Species- lungs and the usual assortment of internal organs. The other type- rarely found outside Gand- has no lungs, and takes in the nutrients it needs through the materials it consumes. Since the Gand cannot tolerate other atmospheres, and outsiders cannot breathe Gand's atmosphere, the Species of this far-flung world developed without outside interference, resulting in a rich culture with particularities.","traits":[]},{"id":"gand-non-force-sensitive","label":"Non-Force-Sensitive","source":"KOTOR","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"skillBonuses":["+2 Perception"],"special":[],"languages":["Gand"],"description":"A strange Species of insect creatures, the Gand have evolved in response to the toxic atmosphere of their homeworld. In fact, two distinct types of Gand exist. The more common has features typical of other Species- lungs and the usual assortment of internal organs. The other type- rarely found outside Gand- has no lungs, and takes in the nutrients it needs through the materials it consumes. Since the Gand cannot tolerate other atmospheres, and outsiders cannot breathe Gand's atmosphere, the Species of this far-flung world developed without outside interference, resulting in a rich culture with particularities.","traits":[]}],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-gen-dai","name":"Gen'Dai","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gen'Dai.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":8,"movement":{"walk":8,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":4,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"special":["Fast Healing","Hibernation","Mental Instability","Regeneration","Resilient Physiology"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"fast-healing","name":"Fast Healing","description":"Whenever a Gen'Dai takes its Second Wind, it regains 5 Hit Points every round at the end of its turn until killed, the end of the encounter, or until reaching one-half Hit Points (whichever comes first)."},{"id":"hibernation","name":"Hibernation","description":"A Gen'Dai can enter a state similar to a Hibernation Trance. A Gen'Dai can use the Force Trance application of the Use the Force skill Untrained (and even if not Force-sensitive) and can remain in the trance indefinitely. A Gen'Dai in such a state ceases to Age, and needs no food, water, or air until it emerges from Hibernation."},{"id":"mental-instability","name":"Mental Instability","description":"As they Age, Gen'Dai begin to lose touch with reality. For each Age Category a Gen'Dai advances past Adult, it takes an additional loss of -1 Wisdom. Gen'Dai characters never gain increased Wisdom due to Age, though they can increase their Wisdom scores as their Character Level increases."},{"id":"regeneration","name":"Regeneration","description":"A Gen'Dai can regrow lost body parts- including significant portions of its physical structure and individual limbs- in 1d10 minutes. At the end of that time, all Persistent penalties associated with the loss of one or more limbs are removed."},{"id":"resilient-physiology","name":"Resilient Physiology","description":"Because of their unique physiology, the Gen'Dai can shrug off the effect of wounds that would be fatal to any other Species. Because of this, a Gen'Dai's Damage Threshold is doubled after adding bonuses for Feats and size when determining whether the Gen'Dai is killed by an attack (but not for any other purpose)."}],"languages":["Basic","Gen'Dai"],"description":"The Gen'Dai benefit from extremely long life spans. Accounts of Gen'Dai living to be over four thousand standard years old are common. They are a hardy Species, thanks in part to their unique physiology. The Gen'Dai have no centralized vital organs, and their elaborate nervous and vascular systems allow them to act quickly and withstand wounds that would kill nearly any other creature. The Gen'Dai are intergalactic nomads, constantly traversing the galaxy.","canonicalName":"Gen'Dai","canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":8,"movement":{"walk":8,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":4,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Gen'Dai receive a +4 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Charisma. Gen'Dai are incredibly resistant to damage, but their long life spans cause them to be mentally unstable.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Gen'Dai"],"special":["Fast Healing","Hibernation","Mental Instability","Regeneration","Resilient Physiology"],"traits":[{"id":"fast-healing","name":"Fast Healing","description":"Whenever a Gen'Dai takes its Second Wind, it regains 5 Hit Points every round at the end of its turn until killed, the end of the encounter, or until reaching one-half Hit Points (whichever comes first)."},{"id":"hibernation","name":"Hibernation","description":"A Gen'Dai can enter a state similar to a Hibernation Trance. A Gen'Dai can use the Force Trance application of the Use the Force skill Untrained (and even if not Force-sensitive) and can remain in the trance indefinitely. A Gen'Dai in such a state ceases to Age, and needs no food, water, or air until it emerges from Hibernation."},{"id":"mental-instability","name":"Mental Instability","description":"As they Age, Gen'Dai begin to lose touch with reality. For each Age Category a Gen'Dai advances past Adult, it takes an additional loss of -1 Wisdom. Gen'Dai characters never gain increased Wisdom due to Age, though they can increase their Wisdom scores as their Character Level increases."},{"id":"regeneration","name":"Regeneration","description":"A Gen'Dai can regrow lost body parts- including significant portions of its physical structure and individual limbs- in 1d10 minutes. At the end of that time, all Persistent penalties associated with the loss of one or more limbs are removed."},{"id":"resilient-physiology","name":"Resilient Physiology","description":"Because of their unique physiology, the Gen'Dai can shrug off the effect of wounds that would be fatal to any other Species. Because of this, a Gen'Dai's Damage Threshold is doubled after adding bonuses for Feats and size when determining whether the Gen'Dai is killed by an attack (but not for any other purpose)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1204},"tags":["large"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-geonosian","name":"Geonosian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Geonosian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":6,"climb":3,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"flySpeed":6,"climbSpeed":3,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Flight","Low-Light Vision","Radiation Resistance"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","description":"Geonosians are capable of flight, but cannot do so if they are carrying a Heavy Load."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Geonosians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"radiation-resistance","name":"Radiation Resistance","description":"Geonosians receive a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against Radiation. In addition, Geonosians never gain a Persistent Condition from the effects of Radiation."}],"languages":["Basic","Geonosian"],"description":"The Geonosians are a caste-dominated Species from the world of Geonosis, in the system of the same name. They dwell in a spectacular architectural realm carved from the soaring, rocky spires that dot the planet's landscape. They are somewhat resistant to the Radiation that occasionally showers their world, though Geonosians actually live underground to escape that phenomenon. Geonosians are born into specific castes divided along the lines of their physical attributes, and though most Geonosians are content to remain within their caste until they die, some develop ambition. The life of a low-ranking Geonosian Worker is ordinarily one of ongoing toil, laboring to fulfill the whims of a Geonosian Aristocracy that sometimes makes spectacular demands.","canonicalName":"Geonosian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":6,"climb":3,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Geonosians receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Charisma. Geonosians are deceptively strong, but their hive-like mentality makes it difficult for them to act on their own.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Geonosian"],"special":["Flight","Low-Light Vision","Radiation Resistance"],"traits":[{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","description":"Geonosians are capable of flight, but cannot do so if they are carrying a Heavy Load."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Geonosians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"radiation-resistance","name":"Radiation Resistance","description":"Geonosians receive a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense against Radiation. In addition, Geonosians never gain a Persistent Condition from the effects of Radiation."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1228},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-givin","name":"Givin","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Givin.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Mechanics"],"special":["Damage Reduction","Deductive Reasoning","Great Fortitude","Vacuum Immunity"],"languages":["Basic","Givin"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"The shipyards that circle Yag'Duhl, the Givin homeworld, produce sturdy and elegant starships and compete on a level matched only by the Duros and Verpine, the only Species that receive grudging respect from the Givin. However, Givin designers do not equip their ships with Navicomputers, since most Givin can calculate hyperspace jumps in their heads, and they often overlook life-support systems. Members of other Species that purchase Givin built ships must add these components.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Givin","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"damage-reduction","name":"Damage Reduction","description":"The hard shells of Givin provides a Species bonus of Damage Reduction 2."},{"id":"deductive-reasoning","name":"Deductive Reasoning","description":"Givin constantly evaluate data, discarding inconclusive results. A Givin can reroll any Knowledge check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Givin gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense."},{"id":"vacuum-immunity","name":"Vacuum Immunity","description":"Givin have sealed exoskeletons and do not breathe in a conventional sense. They are immune to the effects of Vacuum and to the effects of inhaled chemicals and Poisons."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Givin receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Givin lack physical strength, but they are extremely analytical.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Givin"],"special":["Damage Reduction","Deductive Reasoning","Great Fortitude","Vacuum Immunity"],"traits":[{"id":"damage-reduction","name":"Damage Reduction","description":"The hard shells of Givin provides a Species bonus of Damage Reduction 2."},{"id":"deductive-reasoning","name":"Deductive Reasoning","description":"Givin constantly evaluate data, discarding inconclusive results. A Givin can reroll any Knowledge check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Givin gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense."},{"id":"vacuum-immunity","name":"Vacuum Immunity","description":"Givin have sealed exoskeletons and do not breathe in a conventional sense. They are immune to the effects of Vacuum and to the effects of inhaled chemicals and Poisons."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1898},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-gotal","name":"Gotal","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gotal.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Survival"],"special":["Energy Reading","Low-Light Vision","Sensor Cones"],"languages":["Basic","Gotal"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Emotions are an important part of Gotal culture. Young Gotals live in a constant state of confusion as they are bombarded by the emotions of others. Learning to handle this input is what pushes a Gotal toward adulthood and maturity. Adult Gotals are calm, almost serene beings, but despite their outward appearance, they feel the full breadth of emotions. Because they are so sensitive to emotions, Gotals quickly form meaningful relationships with one another.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Gotal","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"energy-reading","name":"Energy Reading","description":"Gotals can read the emotions of any sentient being within 6 squares. As a Standard Action, a Gotal can make a Perception check against a target's Will Defense. A successful check reveals the target's emotional state (such as happy, sad, nervous, or scared)."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Gotals ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"sensor-cones","name":"Sensor Cones","description":"A Gotal can use the Sense Force and Sense Surroundings applications of the Use the Force skill Untrained."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Gotals have no Ability Score adjustments, having no particular advantage or disadvantage in mentality or physical prowess.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Gotal"],"special":["Energy Reading","Low-Light Vision","Sensor Cones"],"traits":[{"id":"energy-reading","name":"Energy Reading","description":"Gotals can read the emotions of any sentient being within 6 squares. As a Standard Action, a Gotal can make a Perception check against a target's Will Defense. A successful check reveals the target's emotional state (such as happy, sad, nervous, or scared)."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Gotals ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"sensor-cones","name":"Sensor Cones","description":"A Gotal can use the Sense Force and Sense Surroundings applications of the Use the Force skill Untrained."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1918},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-gran","name":"Gran","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gran.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Perception"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Innate Accuracy","Target Awareness"],"languages":["Basic","Gran"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Gran place society over self, and they receive training that complements both their personal talents and society's needs. The desire to maintain balance within society caused the Gran to establish alien-only areas of Kinyen. This was intended to restrict alien influence and avoid trouble between Species, such as what happened on Malastare. During The Dark Times, the Empire has pushed the Gran leadership to grant access to all areas. When the Gran refused, Kinyen was subjected to orbital bombardment.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Three-Eyed Vision: +2 to Perception for sight-based checks"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Gran","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Gran with the Point-Blank Shot feat gains the Precise Shot feat as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Gran ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"innate-accuracy","name":"Innate Accuracy","description":"Once per encounter, a Gran can Aim by taking a single Swift Action instead of two Swift Actions."},{"id":"target-awareness","name":"Target Awareness","description":"A Gran takes no distance penalties on Perception checks made to notice targets for the first 50 squares between the Gran and its targets."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Gran receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Intelligence. Gran are highly social creatures, but tend to value artistic value higher than scientific achievement.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Gran"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Innate Accuracy","Target Awareness"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Gran with the Point-Blank Shot feat gains the Precise Shot feat as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Gran ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"innate-accuracy","name":"Innate Accuracy","description":"Once per encounter, a Gran can Aim by taking a single Swift Action instead of two Swift Actions."},{"id":"target-awareness","name":"Target Awareness","description":"A Gran takes no distance penalties on Perception checks made to notice targets for the first 50 squares between the Gran and its targets."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":829},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
