{"_id":"species-gundark","name":"Gundark","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gundark.jpg","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, +2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Climb","+2 Jump"],"special":["Four Arms","Powerful Build"],"languages":["Gundark"],"source":"Scavenger","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Gundark","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-gungan","name":"Gungan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Gungan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Acrobatics","+2 Swim"],"special":["Expert Swimmer","Hold Breath","Lightning Reflexes","Low-Light Vision","Weapon Familiarity"],"languages":["Gunganese","Basic"],"source":"Core","description":"The Gungans are omnivorous humanoids native to the swamps of Naboo. Technologically advanced, they rely mostly on biotech, growing instead of building their homes and production facilities. While their culture is peaceful, it evolved from a series of long, bloody clan wars, and Gungans still admire strength and cunning. Most communities are devoted to farming or manufacturing goods that are then traded to other Gungan settlements, but they will reluctantly trade with the Humans of Naboo.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":["Amphibious: Can breathe underwater and move normally in water"],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Gungan","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Gungan may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse. In addition, a Gungan may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"hold-breath","name":"Hold Breath","description":"Gungans are at home either in air or in water. A Gungan can hold his or her breath for a number of rounds equal to 25 times their Constitution score before they need to make Endurance checks to hold their breath."},{"id":"lightning-reflexes","name":"Lightning Reflexes","description":"Gungans gain a +2 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense, accounting for their uncanny ability to avoid danger."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Gungans ignore Concealment (But not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Gungans treat the Atlatl, Cesta, and Electropole as Simple Weapons (Melee) instead of Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Gungans have a natural +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer -2 penalties to their Intelligence and Charisma. Gungans are agile, but aren't particularly witty or astute.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Gunganese","Basic"],"special":["Expert Swimmer","Hold Breath","Lightning Reflexes","Low-Light Vision","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Gungan may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse. In addition, a Gungan may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"hold-breath","name":"Hold Breath","description":"Gungans are at home either in air or in water. A Gungan can hold his or her breath for a number of rounds equal to 25 times their Constitution score before they need to make Endurance checks to hold their breath."},{"id":"lightning-reflexes","name":"Lightning Reflexes","description":"Gungans gain a +2 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense, accounting for their uncanny ability to avoid danger."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Gungans ignore Concealment (But not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Gungans treat the Atlatl, Cesta, and Electropole as Simple Weapons (Melee) instead of Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":146},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-hapan","name":"Hapan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Hapan.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Royal Poise"],"languages":["Hapan","Basic"],"source":"Legacy","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Hapan","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":5900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-herglic","name":"Herglic","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Herglic.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, -4 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Sturdy"],"languages":["Basic","Herglic"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Herglics are hulking bipeds that evolved from water-dwelling mammals on the planet Giju. Their ancestors' fins and flukes have been replaced by arms and legs, although Herglics still breathe through blowholes on the tops of their heads. As a whole, Herglics are great believers in fairness and honesty. They are renowned for always being upright traders and for honoring any deal or bargain they make. They assume that others behave in a similar fashion, and few things anger a Herglic more than deceit and cheating.","tags":["large"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Herglic","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-4,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Herglics are gregarious creatures with a gift for inducing others to open up. A Herglic with Gather Information as a Trained Skill receives Skill Focus (Gather Information) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"sturdy","name":"Sturdy","description":"Herglics are solidly built and literally have tough skin. Whenever a Herglic catches a Second Wind, he or she regains a number of additional Hit Points equal to 5 + one-half its level."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -4 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-4,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Herglics receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -4 penalty to their Dexterity. Herglics are large and strong, but they lack grace and manual dexterity.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Herglic"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Sturdy"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Herglics are gregarious creatures with a gift for inducing others to open up. A Herglic with Gather Information as a Trained Skill receives Skill Focus (Gather Information) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"sturdy","name":"Sturdy","description":"Herglics are solidly built and literally have tough skin. Whenever a Herglic catches a Second Wind, he or she regains a number of additional Hit Points equal to 5 + one-half its level."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1941},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-hiss-sssi","name":"Hiss'sssi","type":"species","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth","+2 Acrobatics"],"special":["Serpentine Movement"],"languages":["Hssiss","Basic"],"source":"Legacy","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Hiss'sssi","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-houk","name":"Houk","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Houk.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Natural Armor","Physically Intimidating"],"languages":["Basic","Houkese"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"The Houk have well-earned reputations as bullies, cheaters, and backstabbers. They are often compared to Wookiees because of their great strength and violent disposition, although Wookiees are usually more agreeable and trustworthy. The Houk acquired hyperspace technology several thousand years before the Battle of Yavin and spread across the galaxy, seeding many planets with small colonies. During the Rebellion era, Imperial agents captured and experimented on hundreds of Houk colonists, hoping to create strong yet obedient slaves. The Houk did not submit easily, and most of them were never seen again.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Houk","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Houk are thick-boned and thick-skinned. They gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"physically-intimidating","name":"Physically Intimidating","description":"Houk use their Strength modifier instead of their Charisma modifier for Persuasion checks made to Intimidate others."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Houk receive a +2 bonus to both their Strength and Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Charisma. Houk are huge and muscular, but have a reputation for their brutality and aggravation that is not undeserved.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Houkese"],"special":["Natural Armor","Physically Intimidating"],"traits":[{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Houk are thick-boned and thick-skinned. They gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"physically-intimidating","name":"Physically Intimidating","description":"Houk use their Strength modifier instead of their Charisma modifier for Persuasion checks made to Intimidate others."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1070},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-human","name":"Human","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Human.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":[],"special":["Bonus Feat","Bonus Trained Skill"],"languages":["Basic"],"source":"Core","description":"Humans dominate the Core Worlds and can be found in virtually every corner of the galaxy. They are the ancestors of early spacefaring pioneers, conquerors, traders, travelers, and refugees. Humans have always been people on the move. As a result, they can be found on almost every inhabited planet. As a Species, Humans are physically, culturally, and politically diverse.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":1,"bonusTrainedSkills":1,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Human","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Humans gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Humans are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. A Human character chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"None. Humans are wide spread across the galaxy, and each with their own strengths and weaknesses.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Bonus Trained Skill"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Humans gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Humans are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. A Human character chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":3},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-hutt","name":"Hutt","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Hutt.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":2,"movement":{"walk":2,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, +2 Int, -6 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-6,"con":2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Force Resistance","Supreme Stability","Silver Tongued"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"force-resistance","name":"Force Resistance","description":"A Hutt's sharp mind allows them to resist Force abilities. Hutts receive a +5 bonus to their Will Defense against any use of the Use the Force skill."},{"id":"supreme-stability","name":"Supreme Stability","description":"A Hutt's sluglike body structure and lack of any kind of legs, allows a Hutt to become completely immune to being knocked Prone."},{"id":"silver-tongued","name":"Silver Tongued","description":"Hutts may be known to be heavy handed in their ventures, but they are equally capable in legal negotiations as they are underground business. A Hutt may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, keeping the better of the two results."}],"languages":["Basic","Huttese"],"description":"Hutts are long-lived gastropods who occupy a region known as Hutt Space. They are powerful, ruthless beings who continually seek to expand the boundaries of their dominion and the holdings of their individual clans, or Kajidics. Their appetite for power is as insatiable as their appetite for food. Hutts are often found at the center of business and criminal enterprises. Legality (or lack thereof) does not affect whether a Hutt will pursue a venture.","canonicalName":"Hutt","canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":2,"movement":{"walk":2,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, +2 Int, -6 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-6,"con":2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Hutts receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, Constitution, and Intelligence; but suffer a -6 penalty to their Dexterity. Hutts are strong, hardy, and crafty; but are sluggish and uncoordinated.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Huttese"],"special":["Force Resistance","Supreme Stability","Silver Tongued"],"traits":[{"id":"force-resistance","name":"Force Resistance","description":"A Hutt's sharp mind allows them to resist Force abilities. Hutts receive a +5 bonus to their Will Defense against any use of the Use the Force skill."},{"id":"supreme-stability","name":"Supreme Stability","description":"A Hutt's sluglike body structure and lack of any kind of legs, allows a Hutt to become completely immune to being knocked Prone."},{"id":"silver-tongued","name":"Silver Tongued","description":"Hutts may be known to be heavy handed in their ventures, but they are equally capable in legal negotiations as they are underground business. A Hutt may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, keeping the better of the two results."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":177},"tags":["force","large"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-iktotchi","name":"Iktotchi","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Iktotchi.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Pilot","+2 Initiative"],"special":["Natural Armor","Limited Precognition","Expert Pilot"],"languages":["Basic","Iktotchese"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Hailing from The Expansion Region world of Iktotchon and its moon, Iktotch, the Iktotchi are a race of precognitive humanoids. All Iktotchi possess this precognitive ability, which manifests as vivid dreams, visions, or waking dreams. Few Iktotchi have control of how or when their precognition manifests or of what it reveals to them. As a Species, they know of the Republic's coming long before their world is visited, and they are prepared to welcome the guests that would usher them into a vast galactic society. Iktotchi are famed for their prowess as pilots, and attribute their success at the helm to nearly imperceptible precognitive inclinations.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Iktotchi","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Iktotchi have tough skin that provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"limited-precognition","name":"Limited Precognition","description":"Iktotchi are gifted with limited precognition and are subjected to prophetic dreams. Once per encounter, as a Reaction, an Iktotchi can grant themself or any Vehicle the Iktotchi Pilots a +2 Species bonus to Reflex Defense against any single attack."},{"id":"expert-pilot","name":"Expert Pilot","description":"An Iktotchi can reroll any Pilot check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Iktotchi receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Though they are a hardy Species, the Iktotchi are a quiet and introspective people and have trouble forming friendships.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Iktotchese"],"special":["Natural Armor","Limited Precognition","Expert Pilot"],"traits":[{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Iktotchi have tough skin that provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"limited-precognition","name":"Limited Precognition","description":"Iktotchi are gifted with limited precognition and are subjected to prophetic dreams. Once per encounter, as a Reaction, an Iktotchi can grant themself or any Vehicle the Iktotchi Pilots a +2 Species bonus to Reflex Defense against any single attack."},{"id":"expert-pilot","name":"Expert Pilot","description":"An Iktotchi can reroll any Pilot check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1245},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ishi-tib","name":"Ishi Tib","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ishi_Tib.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Survival"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Ecological Awareness","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision","Natural Weapons"],"languages":["Basic","Tibranese"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Ishi Tib live in schools- communal groups of thousands of individuals, governed by elected representatives who hold office for one-year terms. An Ishi Tib does not know the identity of his or her birth parents, because each Ishi Tib school assumes responsibility for the welfare of its hatchlings, creating a strong sense of community and promoting the needs of the group over those of an individual. Unlike Species that have wrecked environmental havoc upon their homeworlds, Ishi Tib protect their planet, Tibrin, with extensive laws legislating ecological preservation. During the Clone Wars, the Ishi Tib side with The Confederacy of Independent Systems after Count Dooku liberates their world from the Ishi Tib premier Suribran Tu, although Tibrin is still represented in the Galactic Senate. During the Galactic Civil War, Ishi Tib who join The Rebel Alliance plan raids against the Empire, and several Ishi Tib tactical experts are present at the briefing prior to the Battle of Endor.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Ishi Tib","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Ishi Tib can't drown in water."},{"id":"ecological-awareness","name":"Ecological Awareness","description":"Due to their conscientiousness and drive to protect the natural environment of their homeworld, an Ishi Tib can choose to reroll any Knowledge (Life Sciences) check, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"An Ishi Tib may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, an Ishi Tib may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Ishi Tib ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"An Ishi Tib has a Natural Weapon, in the form of a sharp beak. When an Ishi Tib makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of piercing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Ishi Tib are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Ishi Tib receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence. Ishi Tib are problem-solvers, striving to find the most efficient solution, with a minimum drain to their resources.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Tibranese"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Ecological Awareness","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision","Natural Weapons"],"traits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Ishi Tib can't drown in water."},{"id":"ecological-awareness","name":"Ecological Awareness","description":"Due to their conscientiousness and drive to protect the natural environment of their homeworld, an Ishi Tib can choose to reroll any Knowledge (Life Sciences) check, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"An Ishi Tib may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, an Ishi Tib may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Ishi Tib ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"An Ishi Tib has a Natural Weapon, in the form of a sharp beak. When an Ishi Tib makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of piercing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Ishi Tib are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2182},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ithorian","name":"Ithorian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ithorian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion","+2 Survival"],"special":["Bellow","Conditional Bonus Feat","Iron Will","Survival Instinct"],"languages":["Basic","Ithorese"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Ithorians are tall humanoids whose appearance leads many to refer to them colloquially as \"Hammerheads.\" Peaceful and gentle, Ithorians are widely recognized as talented artists, brilliant agricultural engineers, and skilled diplomats. Ithorians are perhaps the greatest ecologists in the galaxy, devoting their technology to preserving the natural beauty of their homeworld's jungles. They live in \"Herds,\" dwelling in cities that hover above the surface of their planet and striving to maintain the ecological balance in the \"Mother Jungle.\" Ithorians also travel the galaxy in massive \"Herd Ships,\" masterpieces of environmental engineering that carry a perfect replica of their native jungle. Many look forward to trading for the exotic wares the Ithorians bring from distant planets.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":["Bellow: Once per encounter, sonic attack in 6-square cone"]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Ithorian","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bellow","name":"Bellow","description":"As a Standard Action, an Ithorian can open all four of its throats and emit a terrible subsonic Bellow. The Ithorian makes a special attack roll (1d20 + its Character Level) and compares the result to the Fortitude Defense of all creatures and unattended objects in a 6-Square Cone. A successful hit deals 3d6 points of Sonic damage; if the attack misses, the target takes half damage instead. Each use of this ability moves the Ithorian -1 step along the Condition Track. An Ithorian can choose to add more dice (d6s) to the damage it deals with its Bellow, but each additional 1d6 of damage moves the Ithorian another -1 step along the Condition Track."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ithorians like to maintain close ties with nature. An Ithorian with Knowledge (Life Sciences) as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Knowledge (Life Sciences)) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Ithorians have above-average willpower and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"An Ithorian may choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Ithorians receive a +2 bonus to both their Wisdom and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Ithorians are wise and deliberate thinkers, whose personable nature allows them to get along well with others, but they are not agile.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Ithorese"],"special":["Bellow","Conditional Bonus Feat","Iron Will","Survival Instinct"],"traits":[{"id":"bellow","name":"Bellow","description":"As a Standard Action, an Ithorian can open all four of its throats and emit a terrible subsonic Bellow. The Ithorian makes a special attack roll (1d20 + its Character Level) and compares the result to the Fortitude Defense of all creatures and unattended objects in a 6-Square Cone. A successful hit deals 3d6 points of Sonic damage; if the attack misses, the target takes half damage instead. Each use of this ability moves the Ithorian -1 step along the Condition Track. An Ithorian can choose to add more dice (d6s) to the damage it deals with its Bellow, but each additional 1d6 of damage moves the Ithorian another -1 step along the Condition Track."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ithorians like to maintain close ties with nature. An Ithorian with Knowledge (Life Sciences) as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Knowledge (Life Sciences)) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Ithorians have above-average willpower and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"An Ithorian may choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":196},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-jawa","name":"Jawa","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Jawa.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Mechanics"],"special":["Darkvision","Desert Dweller","Scavenger","Tinkerer"],"languages":["Jawaese","the Jawa Trade Language"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Jawas are intelligent and have a complex society. Gathering in extended tribes, Jawa life revolves around trade- not for wealth, but for survival. Jawas look for guidance from their shamans, usually a female Jawa with the ability to portent the future and cast vicious hexes. Once a year, the Jawa tribes gather in the Dune Sea to exchange sons and daughters, to swap stories and news, and to mingle among their own kind.","tags":["small"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":["Tech Specialist: +2 to Mechanics when working with salvaged tech"],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Jawa","variants":[{"id":"jawa-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Desert Dweller","Tinkerer","Darkvision"],"languages":["Jawaese","the Jawa Trade Language"],"description":"Alternate Jawa trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"desert-dweller","name":"Desert Dweller","description":"Jawas may Take 10 on Survival checks in desert terrain."},{"id":"tinkerer","name":"Tinkerer","description":"A Jawa can choose to reroll any Mechanics check made to Repair an object, vehicle, or droid, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Jawas ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."}]}],"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Jawas ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"desert-dweller","name":"Desert Dweller","description":"When making Survival checks to resist the effects of Extreme Heat, Jawas can reroll the check, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"scavenger","name":"Scavenger","description":"Whenever a Jawa armed with an Ion weapon successfully damages a Droid or Vehicle, the Jawa adds half their Character Level in Ion damage."},{"id":"tinkerer","name":"Tinkerer","description":"A Jawa can choose to reroll any Mechanics check, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse. In addition, Mechanics is always a Class Skill for Jawas."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Jawas receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Jawas are quick and agile, but they lack the strength of larger creatures.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Jawaese","the Jawa Trade Language"],"special":["Darkvision","Desert Dweller","Scavenger","Tinkerer"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Jawas ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"desert-dweller","name":"Desert Dweller","description":"When making Survival checks to resist the effects of Extreme Heat, Jawas can reroll the check, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"scavenger","name":"Scavenger","description":"Whenever a Jawa armed with an Ion weapon successfully damages a Droid or Vehicle, the Jawa adds half their Character Level in Ion damage."},{"id":"tinkerer","name":"Tinkerer","description":"A Jawa can choose to reroll any Mechanics check, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse. In addition, Mechanics is always a Class Skill for Jawas."}],"variants":[{"id":"jawa-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"dex":2,"str":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Desert Dweller","Tinkerer","Darkvision"],"languages":["Jawaese","the Jawa Trade Language"],"description":"Alternate Jawa trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"desert-dweller","name":"Desert Dweller","description":"Jawas may Take 10 on Survival checks in desert terrain."},{"id":"tinkerer","name":"Tinkerer","description":"A Jawa can choose to reroll any Mechanics check made to Repair an object, vehicle, or droid, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Jawas ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."}]}],"sourceLine":1086},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-jenet","name":"Jenet","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Jenet.jpg","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Rodent Cunning"],"languages":["Jenet","Basic"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Jenet","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":6900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kal-dexar","name":"Kal-Dexar","type":"species","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Ord Radama Adaptation"],"languages":["Dresh","Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Kal-Dexar","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kaleesh","name":"Kaleesh","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kaleesh.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, +2 Cha, -2 Dex, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Driven","Persistent"],"languages":["Basic","Kaleesh"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"The Kaleesh are a nomadic Species with a tribal culture. They are spiritual beings who worship their ancestors as deities, and they consider their ancestral burial grounds to be sacred lands. The Kaleesh believe that anyone who dies in honorable service to their people becomes a god upon death. The Kaleesh come to a momentary prominence in the galaxy when they fight off an invasion by an alien Species known as the Huk. Having already subjugated and exploited the natural resources of several worlds, the Huk capture millions of Kaleesh and sell them into slavery.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":["Low-Light Vision"],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":["Kaleesh War Weapons"],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Kaleesh","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Kaleesh are a nomadic people who have learned to live off the land. A Kaleesh with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Because of the thermoreceptor glands next to their eyes, Kaleesh ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"driven","name":"Driven","description":"Kaleesh are focused individuals who maintain sight of their goals even under adverse conditions. Because of this single-minded drive, they gain a +5 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Mind-Affecting effects."},{"id":"persistent","name":"Persistent","description":"A Kaleesh can reroll any Endurance check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, +2 Cha, -2 Dex, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Kaleesh receive a +2 bonus to both their Constitution and Charisma scores, but suffer a -2 penalty to both their Dexterity and Intelligence scores. Kaleesh are sturdy and work well with others, but lack sophistication and precision.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Kaleesh"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Driven","Persistent"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Kaleesh are a nomadic people who have learned to live off the land. A Kaleesh with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Because of the thermoreceptor glands next to their eyes, Kaleesh ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"driven","name":"Driven","description":"Kaleesh are focused individuals who maintain sight of their goals even under adverse conditions. Because of this single-minded drive, they gain a +5 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Mind-Affecting effects."},{"id":"persistent","name":"Persistent","description":"A Kaleesh can reroll any Endurance check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1262},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kaminoan","name":"Kaminoan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kaminoan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Knowledge (Life Sciences)","+2 Treat Injury"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Resilient"],"languages":["Basic","Kaminoan"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"The watery planet of Kamino is home to a Species of cloners known as Kaminoans. These tall aliens are the result of generations of selective breeding and genetic modification that began when their world suffered a drastic change in climate. These restrictive breeding programs have made Kaminoans an extremely adaptable Species. Apart from gender, Kaminoans have little variation, and to the untrained eye they all look the same. Subtle variations have been introduced into their genetic codes, however, allowing for diversity within a strict set of parameters.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Kaminoan","variants":[{"id":"kaminoan-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Ocean Dweller","Reroll"],"languages":["Basic","Kaminoan"],"description":"Alternate Kaminoan trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"ocean-dweller","name":"Ocean Dweller","description":"Kaminoans may Take 10 on Survival checks in aquatic terrain."},{"id":"reroll","name":"Reroll","description":"Kaminoans can choose to reroll any Treat Injury or Knowledge (Life Sciences) check, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse."}]}],"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Kaminoans are expert cloners and posses remarkable knowledge about the physiologies of Species across the galaxy. A Kaminoan with Treat Injury as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Treat Injury) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"resilient","name":"Resilient","description":"Scientific refinements to their genetic code makes Kaminoans resistant to hazards that target their physiology. Kaminoans gain a +1 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Kaminoans receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Kaminoans are smart, largely emphasizing on education, but their arrogance tends to blind them to their flaws.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Kaminoan"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Resilient"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Kaminoans are expert cloners and posses remarkable knowledge about the physiologies of Species across the galaxy. A Kaminoan with Treat Injury as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Treat Injury) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"resilient","name":"Resilient","description":"Scientific refinements to their genetic code makes Kaminoans resistant to hazards that target their physiology. Kaminoans gain a +1 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense."}],"variants":[{"id":"kaminoan-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"con":2,"wis":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Ocean Dweller","Reroll"],"languages":["Basic","Kaminoan"],"description":"Alternate Kaminoan trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"ocean-dweller","name":"Ocean Dweller","description":"Kaminoans may Take 10 on Survival checks in aquatic terrain."},{"id":"reroll","name":"Reroll","description":"Kaminoans can choose to reroll any Treat Injury or Knowledge (Life Sciences) check, but must keep the second result, even if it is worse."}]}],"sourceLine":1278},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kel-dor","name":"Kel Dor","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kel_Dor.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Wis, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Use the Force"],"special":["Keen Force Sense","Low-Light Vision","Special Equipment"],"languages":["Basic","Kel Dor"],"source":"Core","description":"The Kel Dor evolved on Dorin, a world with an atmosphere consisting mostly of helium and a gas that is unique to that world. As such, Kel Dor cannot breathe on planets with common nitrogen/oxygen atmospheres. Conversely, Dorin's atmosphere is toxic to most nonnative life. On other planets, Kel Dor dwellings provide their native atmosphere (stored in large tanks). When outside, Kel Dor must wear breath masks and goggles.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":["Low-Light Vision"],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":["Atmospheric Dependency: Must wear breathing mask in non-native atmospheres"],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":["Force Intuition: +2 to Use the Force for sensing and detection"],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Kel Dor","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"keen-force-sense","name":"Keen Force Sense","description":"Kel Dor may choose to reroll any Use the Force check made to Search Your Feelings or Sense Force, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Kel Dor ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Kel Dor suffer limitations outside their native atmosphere. Without protective goggles, a Kel Dor is considered Blind. Without an Antiox Breath Mask, a Kel Dor begins to Suffocate. A replacement mask costs 2,000 credits (500 on Dorin), and a year's supply of filters costs 200 credits (50 on Dorin). Kel Dor characters begin play with these items at no cost. An Antiox Breath Mask is poisonous to other Species."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Wis, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Kel Dor receive a +2 bonus to both their Dexterity and Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Kel Dor are quick and wise, but they suffer from weaker constitutions than others.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Kel Dor"],"special":["Keen Force Sense","Low-Light Vision","Special Equipment"],"traits":[{"id":"keen-force-sense","name":"Keen Force Sense","description":"Kel Dor may choose to reroll any Use the Force check made to Search Your Feelings or Sense Force, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Kel Dor ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Kel Dor suffer limitations outside their native atmosphere. Without protective goggles, a Kel Dor is considered Blind. Without an Antiox Breath Mask, a Kel Dor begins to Suffocate. A replacement mask costs 2,000 credits (500 on Dorin), and a year's supply of filters costs 200 credits (50 on Dorin). Kel Dor characters begin play with these items at no cost. An Antiox Breath Mask is poisonous to other Species."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":225},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kerkoiden","name":"Kerkoiden","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kerkoiden.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"special":["Predator's Heritage","Social Cunning"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"predator-s-heritage","name":"Predator's Heritage","description":"Despite their stature, Kerkoiden are descended from predatory beings. Kerkoiden gain a +2 Species bonus on damage rolls against a target that has been damaged since the beginning of the Kerkoiden's last turn."},{"id":"social-cunning","name":"Social Cunning","description":"Kerkoiden may use their Wisdom modifier in place of their Charisma modifier for determining their bonus on Deception and Persuasion checks."}],"languages":["Basic","Kerkoidese"],"description":"A smaller Species from The Expansion Region, the Kerkoiden are aggressive and cunning beings who often have something to prove. Excellent traders, skilled politicians, and creative military commanders, Kerkoiden are known as formidable opponents, a reputation they prove is well-earned during the Clone Wars. Xenobiologists from the University of Sanbra believe that the Kerkoiden Species descended from quadruped predators that hunt on the savannahs and in the jungles of Kerkoidia. Much of Kerkoiden physiology seems to support this claim, including their hunched posture, long snout, and jutting teeth. Additionally, Kerkoiden aggression seems to be consistent with the predatory instinct of their ancestors, lending credence to this theory of Kerkoiden evolution.","canonicalName":"Kerkoiden","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Kerkoiden receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Though less hardy than other Species, Kerkoiden are devious and cunning.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Kerkoidese"],"special":["Predator's Heritage","Social Cunning"],"traits":[{"id":"predator-s-heritage","name":"Predator's Heritage","description":"Despite their stature, Kerkoiden are descended from predatory beings. Kerkoiden gain a +2 Species bonus on damage rolls against a target that has been damaged since the beginning of the Kerkoiden's last turn."},{"id":"social-cunning","name":"Social Cunning","description":"Kerkoiden may use their Wisdom modifier in place of their Charisma modifier for determining their bonus on Deception and Persuasion checks."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1307},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kessurian","name":"Kessurian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kessurian.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion","+2 Initiative"],"special":["Linguistic Talent"],"languages":["Kess","Basic"],"source":"Scum & Villainy","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Kessurian","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-khil","name":"Khil","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Khil.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"special":["Cooperative Spirit","Dependable Worker","Self-Sustaining"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"cooperative-spirit","name":"Cooperative Spirit","description":"Khil work with others easily. They can Aid Another on Skill Checks made by adjacent allies as a Swift Action, and others can likewise aid Khil on Skill Checks as Swift Actions when adjacent to the Khil. This ability only applies to Climb, Endurance, Gather Information, Jump, Knowledge, Mechanics, Pilot, Ride, Survival, Swim, Treat Injury, or Use Computer skill checks."},{"id":"dependable-worker","name":"Dependable Worker","description":"Khil reliably achieve good results. Once per encounter, a Khil can treat one Skill Check with certain Skills (Climb, Endurance, Gather Information, Jump, Knowledge, Mechanics, Pilot, Ride, Survival, Swim, Treat Injury, or Use Computer) as though he or she had Taken 10, even after the roll has been made (but before the result of the check is known)."},{"id":"self-sustaining","name":"Self-Sustaining","description":"Khil are able to absorb nutrition through the tentacles on their faces, called hullepi, drawing nourishment from almost any environment. Khil do not suffer the effect of Starvation, except in sterile environments."}],"languages":["Basic","Khilese"],"description":"Even in The Old Republic Era, the Khil are considered to be one of the oldest Species of the Republic. They are avid travelers and settlers, spreading colonies and settlements throughout the galaxy. During this era, the Khil are particularly active colonizers. They respect planets already inhabited by native sapient Species or other colonists, preferring to use worlds without significant major threats, be they intelligent or highly predatory. However, once a colony is established, the Khil become fully dedicated to its success.","canonicalName":"Khil","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"Khil receive +2 bonuses to their Intelligence and Charisma, but take a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Khil are charming and well-learned, but their endurance leaves much to be desired.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Khilese"],"special":["Cooperative Spirit","Dependable Worker","Self-Sustaining"],"traits":[{"id":"cooperative-spirit","name":"Cooperative Spirit","description":"Khil work with others easily. They can Aid Another on Skill Checks made by adjacent allies as a Swift Action, and others can likewise aid Khil on Skill Checks as Swift Actions when adjacent to the Khil. This ability only applies to Climb, Endurance, Gather Information, Jump, Knowledge, Mechanics, Pilot, Ride, Survival, Swim, Treat Injury, or Use Computer skill checks."},{"id":"dependable-worker","name":"Dependable Worker","description":"Khil reliably achieve good results. Once per encounter, a Khil can treat one Skill Check with certain Skills (Climb, Endurance, Gather Information, Jump, Knowledge, Mechanics, Pilot, Ride, Survival, Swim, Treat Injury, or Use Computer) as though he or she had Taken 10, even after the roll has been made (but before the result of the check is known)."},{"id":"self-sustaining","name":"Self-Sustaining","description":"Khil are able to absorb nutrition through the tentacles on their faces, called hullepi, drawing nourishment from almost any environment. Khil do not suffer the effect of Starvation, except in sterile environments."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":624},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kiffar","name":"Kiffar","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kiffar.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Pilot"],"special":[],"languages":["Kiffar","Basic"],"source":"FU","description":"","tags":[],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Psychometric Insight: Touch object to gain vision of its past (once per day)"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Kiffar","suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-killik","name":"Killik","type":"species","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Climb","+2 Perception"],"special":["Hive Mind","Joiners","Low-Light Vision","Multiple Limbs","Natural Armor","Natural Weapons","Size","Additional Traits"],"languages":["Killik","Sy Bisti"],"source":"Legacy","description":"Killiks are a genetically diverse population of intelligent insects. Their society is composed of hives, also called nests. Members of each hive share the same physical characteristics and possess the ability to communicate with others through pheromones, electromagnetic transmissions, and long-distance telepathy. Multiple nests united under a hive-mind link can be considered a single organism. Its members always refer to themselves in the third person, and each is aware of anything that has been experienced by any other member.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Killik","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"hive-mind","name":"Hive Mind","description":"Killiks share a Hive Mind and use their antennae to communicate by telepathy with other members of their Species. A Killik within 1 kilometer of another Killik can communicate with it via Telepathy."},{"id":"joiners","name":"Joiners","description":"Whenever a Killik reduces a living creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher to 0 Hit Points, or the Killik knocks the creature unconscious by moving it down the Condition Track, the Killik can transform the target into a Joiner. The target must be Helpless for this to occur. The process takes 1 minute and exposes the target to mind-altering pheromones. Once the target becomes a Joiner, its Attitude shifts to Friendly to the Killik and its allies, and the target gains a +10 bonus to its Will Defense against attempts to use Persuasion to alter its perceptions of its new Killik friends. A target transformed into a Joiner in this manner can make a DC 20 Intelligence check once per day to remove the effect and return to its original Attitude. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Killiks ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"multiple-limbs","name":"Multiple Limbs","description":"Killiks have four limbs that are generally used as arms and hands. When making multiple attacks, a Killik reduces the penalty to its attack rolls by 2."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Killik's chitinous exoskeleton provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to its Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Killik has Natural Weapons, in the form of three-fingered claws. When a Killik makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Killiks are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"size","name":"Size","description":"Killik sizes typically range from Small to Huge, with a few reaching the extremes of Fine and Colossal. When creating a Killik, apply the appropriate size modifiers per the table below."},{"id":"additional-traits","name":"Additional Traits","description":"To include additional traits, see the Creature Generator. SIZE ABILITY MODIFIERS BASE SPEED REFLEX MODIFIER STEALTH MODIFIER DAMAGE THRESHOLD MODIFIER UNARMED DAMAGE Fine +8 Dex, -8 Str 4 Squares +10 +20 +0 1 Diminutive +6 Dex, -6 Str 4 Squares +5 +15 +0 1d2 Tiny +4 Dex, -4 Str 4 Squares +2 +10 +0 1d3 Small +2 Dex, -2 Str 4 Squares +1 +5 +0 1d4 Medium None 6 Squares +0 +0 +0 1d6 Large +8 Str, +8 Con, -2 Dex 6 Squares -1 -5 +5 1d8 Huge +16 Str, +16 Con, -4 Dex 4 Squares -2 -10 +10 2d6 Gargantuan +24 Str, +24 Con, -4 Dex 4 Squares -5 -15 +20 3d6 Colossal +32 Str, +32 Con, -4 Dex 4 Squares -10 -20 +50 4d6 Krevaaki Krevaaki are a peaceful, spiritual Species. With minimal interest in acquiring wealth, power, or fame, they seek wisdom through exploration and meditation. Although they are an ancient spacefaring Species, Krevaaki are rarely encountered in the galaxy at large. Even during The Old Republic Era- their most active period- groups of more than a few Krevaaki are seldom seen at any one location. Krevaaki In response to other Species' xenophobia, the Krevaaki cloak their tentacled bodies with heavy robes or similar garments, leaving only their two dominant tentacles exposed like humanoid arms. More than a few beings have been caught unaware by the sudden appearance of additional tentacles from beneath the folds of a Krevaaki's garments."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Killiks receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Intelligence. Killiks are a hardy but intensely focused Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Killik","Sy Bisti"],"special":["Hive Mind","Joiners","Low-Light Vision","Multiple Limbs","Natural Armor","Natural Weapons","Size","Additional Traits"],"traits":[{"id":"hive-mind","name":"Hive Mind","description":"Killiks share a Hive Mind and use their antennae to communicate by telepathy with other members of their Species. A Killik within 1 kilometer of another Killik can communicate with it via Telepathy."},{"id":"joiners","name":"Joiners","description":"Whenever a Killik reduces a living creature with an Intelligence score of 3 or higher to 0 Hit Points, or the Killik knocks the creature unconscious by moving it down the Condition Track, the Killik can transform the target into a Joiner. The target must be Helpless for this to occur. The process takes 1 minute and exposes the target to mind-altering pheromones. Once the target becomes a Joiner, its Attitude shifts to Friendly to the Killik and its allies, and the target gains a +10 bonus to its Will Defense against attempts to use Persuasion to alter its perceptions of its new Killik friends. A target transformed into a Joiner in this manner can make a DC 20 Intelligence check once per day to remove the effect and return to its original Attitude. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Killiks ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"multiple-limbs","name":"Multiple Limbs","description":"Killiks have four limbs that are generally used as arms and hands. When making multiple attacks, a Killik reduces the penalty to its attack rolls by 2."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Killik's chitinous exoskeleton provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to its Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Killik has Natural Weapons, in the form of three-fingered claws. When a Killik makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Killiks are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"size","name":"Size","description":"Killik sizes typically range from Small to Huge, with a few reaching the extremes of Fine and Colossal. When creating a Killik, apply the appropriate size modifiers per the table below."},{"id":"additional-traits","name":"Additional Traits","description":"To include additional traits, see the Creature Generator. SIZE ABILITY MODIFIERS BASE SPEED REFLEX MODIFIER STEALTH MODIFIER DAMAGE THRESHOLD MODIFIER UNARMED DAMAGE Fine +8 Dex, -8 Str 4 Squares +10 +20 +0 1 Diminutive +6 Dex, -6 Str 4 Squares +5 +15 +0 1d2 Tiny +4 Dex, -4 Str 4 Squares +2 +10 +0 1d3 Small +2 Dex, -2 Str 4 Squares +1 +5 +0 1d4 Medium None 6 Squares +0 +0 +0 1d6 Large +8 Str, +8 Con, -2 Dex 6 Squares -1 -5 +5 1d8 Huge +16 Str, +16 Con, -4 Dex 4 Squares -2 -10 +10 2d6 Gargantuan +24 Str, +24 Con, -4 Dex 4 Squares -5 -15 +20 3d6 Colossal +32 Str, +32 Con, -4 Dex 4 Squares -10 -20 +50 4d6 Krevaaki Krevaaki are a peaceful, spiritual Species. With minimal interest in acquiring wealth, power, or fame, they seek wisdom through exploration and meditation. Although they are an ancient spacefaring Species, Krevaaki are rarely encountered in the galaxy at large. Even during The Old Republic Era- their most active period- groups of more than a few Krevaaki are seldom seen at any one location. Krevaaki In response to other Species' xenophobia, the Krevaaki cloak their tentacled bodies with heavy robes or similar garments, leaving only their two dominant tentacles exposed like humanoid arms. More than a few beings have been caught unaware by the sudden appearance of additional tentacles from beneath the folds of a Krevaaki's garments."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2206},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kissai","name":"Kissai","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kissai.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"special":["Inspired","Warrior's Awareness","Weapon Familiarity"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"inspired","name":"Inspired","description":"Kissai make the best use of any inspiration or information provided to them. Whenever a Kissai receives a morale or insight bonus from any source, the bonus increases by +1."},{"id":"warrior-s-awareness","name":"Warrior's Awareness","description":"Kissai grow up in a violent and warlike society, so they constantly watch for threats. Once per encounter as a Reaction, a Kissai can gain the benefit of the Uncanny Dodge I and Uncanny Dodge II Talents until the beginning of the Kissai's next turn."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Kissai treat the Massassi Lanvarok as a Simple Weapon (Ranged) instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"languages":["Basic","Sith"],"description":"The Kissai are just as ruthless as the Massassi, but they are more intelligent and observant. Their strict cultural standards demand that they serve their masters well, a trait instilled in them by the Dark Jedi who first enslaved their Species. When the Massassi and Kissai flee Korriban (well before the arrival of the eventual Sith Lords) to resettle on Ziost, the Kissai oversee the rebuilding efforts. The Kissai serve The Sith directly, but the Sith Lord Naga Sadow has other ideas for the Massassi caste. The Kissai are largely left on Ziost as the servants of other Sith Lords, but Sadow uses Sith Alchemy to transform the Massassi into his hulking, brutish soldiers.","canonicalName":"Kissai","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Kissai receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Kissai are charming and pleasant, but their devotion to The Sith blinds them to the suffering that follows.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Sith"],"special":["Inspired","Warrior's Awareness","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"inspired","name":"Inspired","description":"Kissai make the best use of any inspiration or information provided to them. Whenever a Kissai receives a morale or insight bonus from any source, the bonus increases by +1."},{"id":"warrior-s-awareness","name":"Warrior's Awareness","description":"Kissai grow up in a violent and warlike society, so they constantly watch for threats. Once per encounter as a Reaction, a Kissai can gain the benefit of the Uncanny Dodge I and Uncanny Dodge II Talents until the beginning of the Kissai's next turn."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Kissai treat the Massassi Lanvarok as a Simple Weapon (Ranged) instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":644},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":7900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-klatooinian","name":"Klatooinian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Klatooinian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Iron Will"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Klatooinians are resolute individuals and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."}],"languages":["Huttese"],"description":"The ancient Klatooinians perceived the Hutts as demigods. The Hutts, never a kind to refuse the upper hand in any situation, used this false perception to their own advantage, convincing the Klatooinians to cast aside their ancient traditions, abandon their native language in favor of Huttese, and accept their place as indentured servants. Over the millennia, the Hutts have sheltered the Klatooinians and cultivated a society that is largely docile, obedient, illiterate, and isolated from the greater galactic community. Exposure to technology has not diminished the Klatooinian predilection for simplicity. However, youthful Klatooinians often chafe at the conventional \"Wisdom\" of their elders, and despite the Hutts' efforts to shield their Klatooinian subjects from progressive ideas, many Klatooinians strive to break away from their Hutt overlords.","canonicalName":"Klatooinian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Klatooinians receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Intelligence. Life on Klatooine has made the Klatooinians hardy, but they are slow to figure things out and often rely on others to guide them.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Huttese"],"special":["Iron Will"],"traits":[{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Klatooinians are resolute individuals and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1465},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-koorivar","name":"Koorivar","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Koorivar.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative"],"special":["Commercial Talent"],"languages":["Koorivar","Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Koorivar","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-krevaaki","name":"Krevaaki","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Krevaaki.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Carapace","Stoic","Grasping Tentacles"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Krevaaki's tentacles give it an advantage in climbing. A Krevaaki who has Climb as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Climb) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"carapace","name":"Carapace","description":"Krevaaki gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense and a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Fortitude Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"stoic","name":"Stoic","description":"Krevaaki physiology and their limited ability to use facial expressions make them difficult for other Species to read accurately. Any creature attempting to use the Sense Deception or Sense Influence applications of the Perception skill on a Krevaaki takes a -5 penalty to the skill check."},{"id":"grasping-tentacles","name":"Grasping Tentacles","description":"Krevaaki use their two dominant tentacles like the arms and hands of a humanoid. Krevaaki gain a +2 Species bonus to Climb checks and a +2 Species bonus to Grab and Grapple checks."}],"languages":["Basic","Kreva"],"description":"In response to other Species' xenophobia, the Krevaaki cloak their tentacled bodies with heavy robes or similar garments, leaving only their two dominant tentacles exposed like humanoid arms. More than a few beings have been caught unaware by the sudden appearance of additional tentacles from beneath the folds of a Krevaaki's garments.","canonicalName":"Krevaaki","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Krevaaki receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Krevaaki are kind-hearted and spiritual, but their unusual physiques tends to unnerve other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Kreva"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Carapace","Stoic","Grasping Tentacles"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Krevaaki's tentacles give it an advantage in climbing. A Krevaaki who has Climb as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Climb) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"carapace","name":"Carapace","description":"Krevaaki gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense and a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Fortitude Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"stoic","name":"Stoic","description":"Krevaaki physiology and their limited ability to use facial expressions make them difficult for other Species to read accurately. Any creature attempting to use the Sense Deception or Sense Influence applications of the Perception skill on a Krevaaki takes a -5 penalty to the skill check."},{"id":"grasping-tentacles","name":"Grasping Tentacles","description":"Krevaaki use their two dominant tentacles like the arms and hands of a humanoid. Krevaaki gain a +2 Species bonus to Climb checks and a +2 Species bonus to Grab and Grapple checks."}],"variants":[{"id":"krevaaki-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"wis":2,"cha":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Carapace","Stoic","Grasping Tentacles"],"languages":["Basic","Kreva"],"description":"Alternate Krevaaki trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"carapace","name":"Carapace","description":"Krevaaki gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense and a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Fortitude Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"stoic","name":"Stoic","description":"Krevaaki physiology and their limited ability to use facial expressions make them difficult for other Species to read accurately. Any creature attempting to use the Sense Deception or Sense Influence applications of the Perception skill on a Krevaaki takes a -5 penalty to the skill check."},{"id":"grasping-tentacles","name":"Grasping Tentacles","description":"Krevaaki use their two dominant tentacles like the arms and hands of a humanoid. Krevaaki gain a +2 Species bonus to Climb checks and a +2 Species bonus to Grab and Grapple checks."}]}],"sourceLine":2246},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[{"id":"krevaaki-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Carapace","Stoic","Grasping Tentacles"],"languages":["Basic","Kreva"],"description":"Alternate Krevaaki trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"carapace","name":"Carapace","description":"Krevaaki gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense and a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Fortitude Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"stoic","name":"Stoic","description":"Krevaaki physiology and their limited ability to use facial expressions make them difficult for other Species to read accurately. Any creature attempting to use the Sense Deception or Sense Influence applications of the Perception skill on a Krevaaki takes a -5 penalty to the skill check."},{"id":"grasping-tentacles","name":"Grasping Tentacles","description":"Krevaaki use their two dominant tentacles like the arms and hands of a humanoid. Krevaaki gain a +2 Species bonus to Climb checks and a +2 Species bonus to Grab and Grapple checks."}]}],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-kubaz","name":"Kubaz","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Kubaz.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth"],"special":["Insectivore"],"languages":["Kubaz","Basic"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Kubaz","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-lugubraa","name":"Lugubraa","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Lugubraa.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Accelerated Learning","Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Lockbite","Natural Weapons"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"accelerated-learning","name":"Accelerated Learning","description":"Before 50 years of age, a Lugubraa can have a maximum Intelligence score of 8. Around 50 years of age, a Lugubraa's Intelligence score naturally increases by 1d4+2 points."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"All Lugubraa gain the Improved Damage Threshold feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Although Lugubraa cannot see, their echolocation and heat detection abilities grant them the effects of Darkvision. Lugubraa ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"lockbite","name":"Lockbite","description":"A Lugubraa that makes a successful Grapple attack can automatically latch onto a target with its teeth, giving the Lugubraa a +5 bonus to subsequent Grapple checks against the target."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Lugubraa has Natural Weapons, in the form of barbed tentacles. When a Lugubraa makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Lugubraa are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."}],"languages":["Lugubraal"],"description":"From birth to six months, Lugubraa have the self-awareness of domesticated beasts, able to follow simple commands and steadfastly devoted to their horde or the owner that has purchased their services. After six months, their intelligence reaches that of simple-minded sentients, allowing them to communicate in short sentences but still rendering them hopeless when it comes to advanced calculations. It is rare for Lugubraa to survive more than a few decades, but those that do undergo a second cognitive kick-start at approximately age 50. These unusual geniuses become leaders and strategists for the Lugubraa hordes, plotting ways to acquire more resources and brokering the services of their species as mercenaries to interested galactic parties.","canonicalName":"Lugubraa","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Lugubraa receive a +2 bonus to both their Strength and Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Dexterity and Wisdom. Lugubraa are tough but lack the intelligence of most sentient Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Lugubraal"],"special":["Accelerated Learning","Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Lockbite","Natural Weapons"],"traits":[{"id":"accelerated-learning","name":"Accelerated Learning","description":"Before 50 years of age, a Lugubraa can have a maximum Intelligence score of 8. Around 50 years of age, a Lugubraa's Intelligence score naturally increases by 1d4+2 points."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"All Lugubraa gain the Improved Damage Threshold feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Although Lugubraa cannot see, their echolocation and heat detection abilities grant them the effects of Darkvision. Lugubraa ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"lockbite","name":"Lockbite","description":"A Lugubraa that makes a successful Grapple attack can automatically latch onto a target with its teeth, giving the Lugubraa a +5 bonus to subsequent Grapple checks against the target."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Lugubraa has Natural Weapons, in the form of barbed tentacles. When a Lugubraa makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Lugubraa are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2281},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-lurmen","name":"Lurmen","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Lurmen.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Acrobatics","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Expert Climber","Mender","Primitive","Roller"],"languages":["Basic","Lurmese"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Lurmen are small, furry humanoids with the ability to roll up in a ball faster overland travel. Their love of peace leads the Lurmen to avoid entanglements in galactic events. As a society, Lurmen eschew conflict of any kind, refusing to fight even in their own defense. During the Clone Wars, a colony of Lurmen on Maridun is nearly wiped out by a Separatist weapon, and only when several Lurmen break away from the wishes of their elders and join the fight are their people saved. Although the Lurmen seem stubborn in holding onto their ways, in truth they lead a lifestyle largely free of conflict, and have for eons.","tags":["primitive","small"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Lurmen","movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Lurmen are great climbers and may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"mender","name":"Mender","description":"Lurmen have learned to heal wounds rather than create them. A Lurmen Trained in Treat Injury reduces the Treat Injury DC for all applications of the skill by his or her Wisdom modifier."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Lurmen do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"roller","name":"Roller","description":"A Lurmen can curl into a ball and quickly roll along the ground. As a Swift Action, a Lurmen can increase his or her base Speed by 4 squares. In this form, the Lurmen can only take the Move, Withdraw, Catch a Second Wind, Drop an Item, Recover, and Run Actions. The Lurmen can also spend a Swift Action to emerge from their rolling form, losing the +4 Speed bonus and regaining access to all Actions he or she can normally take."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Lurmen receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Lurmen are pacifists and healers, lacking the physical strength of other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Lurmese"],"special":["Expert Climber","Mender","Primitive","Roller"],"traits":[{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Lurmen are great climbers and may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"mender","name":"Mender","description":"Lurmen have learned to heal wounds rather than create them. A Lurmen Trained in Treat Injury reduces the Treat Injury DC for all applications of the skill by his or her Wisdom modifier."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Lurmen do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"roller","name":"Roller","description":"A Lurmen can curl into a ball and quickly roll along the ground. As a Swift Action, a Lurmen can increase his or her base Speed by 4 squares. In this form, the Lurmen can only take the Move, Withdraw, Catch a Second Wind, Drop an Item, Recover, and Run Actions. The Lurmen can also spend a Swift Action to emerge from their rolling form, losing the +4 Speed bonus and regaining access to all Actions he or she can normally take."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1695},"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-mandalorian-human-variant","name":"Mandalorian (Human Variant)","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Mandalorian (Human Variant).webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Bonus Trained Skill"],"languages":["Basic"],"source":"Galaxy at War","description":"Humans dominate the Core Worlds and can be found in virtually every corner of the galaxy. They are the ancestors of early spacefaring pioneers, conquerors, traders, travelers, and refugees. Humans have always been people on the move. As a result, they can be found on almost every inhabited planet. As a Species, Humans are physically, culturally, and politically diverse.","tags":[],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":1,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Mandalorian (Human Variant)","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"None. Humans are wide spread across the galaxy, and each with their own strengths and weaknesses.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Bonus Trained Skill"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Humans gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Humans are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. A Human character chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":3},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Humans gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Humans are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. A Human character chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."}],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-mantellian-savrip","name":"Mantellian Savrip","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Mantellian Savrip.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":8,"movement":{"walk":8,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, +4 Con, -4 Int, -4 Wis, -4 Cha, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":4,"int":-4,"wis":-4,"cha":-4},"special":["Natural Armor","Natural Weapons","Poison","Primitive","Rage"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Mantellian Savrips have a tough hide that protects them from harm. They gain a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Mantellian Savrip has Natural Weapons, in the form of tough claws. When a Mantellian Savrip makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Mantellian Savrips are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"poison","name":"Poison","description":"If the Natural Weapons of a Mantellian Savrip can deal damage to a living target, the target is also Poisoned. If the Poison succeeds on an attack roll (1d20 + the Mantellian Savrip's Character Level) against the target's Fortitude Defense, the target moves -1 step along the Condition Track. A target moved to the end of the Condition Track by the Poison is Immobilized, but not Unconscious."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Mantellian Savrips do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Mantellian Savrip can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While Raging, the Mantellian Savrip temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Mantellian Savrip's Constitution modifier. At the end of its Rage, the Mantellian Savrip moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Mantellian Savrip takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Mantellian Savrip can't engage in any strenuous activity."}],"languages":["Savrip"],"description":"A reptilian Species of semi-sentient brutes native to the planet Ord Mantell, Mantellian Savrips' sentience was a contentious subject to xenobiologist from the Core Worlds. Often believed to be simply a very cunning non-sentient beast by many Mantellians, the Mantellian Savrips are technologically primitive, and have their own informal language. Preferring to wear clothing and wielding simple tools and Weapons, some Mantellian Savrips had learned to speak accented Basic. Mantellian Savrips are naturally inclined to combat, and this, coupled with their unusual language, only fostered the notion that they were unintelligent. Mantellian During the colonization of Ord Mantell, sanctioned killings of the Mantellian Savrip Species nearly drove the race to extinction.","canonicalName":"Mantellian Savrip","canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":8,"movement":{"walk":8,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, +4 Con, -4 Int, -4 Wis, -4 Cha, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":4,"int":-4,"wis":-4,"cha":-4},"abilityText":"All Mantellian Savrips receive a +4 bonus to both their Strength and Constitution, but suffer -4 penalties to their Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma, as well as a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Mantellian Savrips are solid walls of muscle and power, but are unsophisticated and quick to anger.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Savrip"],"special":["Natural Armor","Natural Weapons","Poison","Primitive","Rage"],"traits":[{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Mantellian Savrips have a tough hide that protects them from harm. They gain a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Mantellian Savrip has Natural Weapons, in the form of tough claws. When a Mantellian Savrip makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Mantellian Savrips are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"poison","name":"Poison","description":"If the Natural Weapons of a Mantellian Savrip can deal damage to a living target, the target is also Poisoned. If the Poison succeeds on an attack roll (1d20 + the Mantellian Savrip's Character Level) against the target's Fortitude Defense, the target moves -1 step along the Condition Track. A target moved to the end of the Condition Track by the Poison is Immobilized, but not Unconscious."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Mantellian Savrips do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Mantellian Savrip can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While Raging, the Mantellian Savrip temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Mantellian Savrip's Constitution modifier. At the end of its Rage, the Mantellian Savrip moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Mantellian Savrip takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Mantellian Savrip can't engage in any strenuous activity."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":473},"tags":["large","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-massassi","name":"Massassi","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Massassi.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Int, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Duty Bound","Primitive","Warrior's Awareness","Weapon Familiarity"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Massassi are skilled trackers. A Massassi with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"duty-bound","name":"Duty Bound","description":"Once per encounter when a Massassi receives a morale bonus of any kind from any source, the Massassi gains Bonus Hit Points equal to 4 x the Massassi's Character Level until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Massassi do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"warrior-s-awareness","name":"Warrior's Awareness","description":"Massassi grow up in a violent and warlike society, so they constantly watch for threats. Once per encounter as a Reaction, a Massassi can gain the benefit of the Uncanny Dodge I and Uncanny Dodge II Talents until the beginning of the Massassi's next turn."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Massassi treat the Massassi Lanvarok as a Simple Weapon (Ranged) instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"languages":["Sith","Sith as well"],"description":"A thousand years after Sadow and the Massassi arrive on Yavin 4, Exar Kun discovers the ancient Sith secrets in the temples. He uses the Massassi to fight the Jedi across the galaxy. Eventually, Kun consumes the life force of every Massassi on Yavin 4 in his transformation into a Dark Side Spirit. A few Massassi are taken offworld prior to Kun's final decimation of their society. Some remain loyal and find their way back to the new Sith Empire, but a few resentful individuals drift into the darker fringes of society, looking to live their own lives or seeking revenge against the Sith.","canonicalName":"Massassi","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Int, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Massassi receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to their Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma. Massassi are brawny and powerful, but lack the patience and mental strength of their Kissai cousins.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Sith","Sith as well"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Duty Bound","Primitive","Warrior's Awareness","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Massassi are skilled trackers. A Massassi with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"duty-bound","name":"Duty Bound","description":"Once per encounter when a Massassi receives a morale bonus of any kind from any source, the Massassi gains Bonus Hit Points equal to 4 x the Massassi's Character Level until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Massassi do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"warrior-s-awareness","name":"Warrior's Awareness","description":"Massassi grow up in a violent and warlike society, so they constantly watch for threats. Once per encounter as a Reaction, a Massassi can gain the benefit of the Uncanny Dodge I and Uncanny Dodge II Talents until the beginning of the Massassi's next turn."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Massassi treat the Massassi Lanvarok as a Simple Weapon (Ranged) instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":663},"tags":["medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-miraluka","name":"Miraluka","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Miraluka.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Use the Force"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Force Sight"],"languages":["Basic","Miralukese"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"Miraluka are remarkably similar to Humans, except for two important and distinctive differences. Miraluka have no eyes, but they have a natural ability to \"see\" by using The Force. Since they appear Human- including their speech and mannerisms- Miraluka attempt to blend with Humans when traveling throughout the galaxy. Thus, estimating how often they travel or how many live off their home planet of Alpheridies is difficult, but the number is relativity low. To make matters worse, the Sith Lord Darth Nihilus consumed the colony of Katarr after The Jedi Civil War.","tags":["force","medium"],"visionTraits":["Force Sight: Use Use the Force for all vision-based Perception checks"],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":["Force Sight: Can see through the Force, detects living beings"],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Miraluka","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Miraluka who has Use the Force as a Trained Skill gains Force Training as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"force-sight","name":"Force Sight","description":"Although blind, Miraluka can \"see\" by using The Force. They act normally, without taking any penalties for blindness when in the presence of living creatures, or life of any kind. This trait enables them to make Perception checks, and read and write as a sighted person. They can ignore the effect of darkness as if they had Darkvision. Miraluka cannot, however, detect creatures that are \"invisible\" to The Force such as the Yuuzhan Vong and the Ysalamiri. These creatures have Total Concealment from Miraluka, as do creatures in areas the dampen or suppress The Force. Additionally, Miraluka ignore all penalties to Perception checks from Cover and Concealment (but not Total Cover or Total Concealment). Miraluka do not increase the DC of Use the Force checks made to Sense Surroundings against targets with Total Cover."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Miraluka receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Miraluka have keen minds, but their reliance on The Force to perceive their surroundings prevents them from reacting as quickly as most.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Miralukese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Force Sight"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Miraluka who has Use the Force as a Trained Skill gains Force Training as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"force-sight","name":"Force Sight","description":"Although blind, Miraluka can \"see\" by using The Force. They act normally, without taking any penalties for blindness when in the presence of living creatures, or life of any kind. This trait enables them to make Perception checks, and read and write as a sighted person. They can ignore the effect of darkness as if they had Darkvision. Miraluka cannot, however, detect creatures that are \"invisible\" to The Force such as the Yuuzhan Vong and the Ysalamiri. These creatures have Total Concealment from Miraluka, as do creatures in areas the dampen or suppress The Force. Additionally, Miraluka ignore all penalties to Perception checks from Cover and Concealment (but not Total Cover or Total Concealment). Miraluka do not increase the DC of Use the Force checks made to Sense Surroundings against targets with Total Cover."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":685},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":8900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-mirialan","name":"Mirialan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Mirialan.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative","+2 Perception"],"special":[],"languages":["Mirialan","Basic"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"","tags":[],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Disciplined: +2 to resist mind-affecting effects"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Mirialan","suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-mon-calamari","name":"Mon Calamari","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Mon_Calamari.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Wis, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Survival"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Conditional Bonus Feat","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision"],"languages":["Basic","Mon Calamarian"],"source":"Core","description":"Amphibious land-dwellers, the Mon Calamari share their Outer Rim homeworld with the aquatic Quarren. They tend to be soft-spoken but vigorously defend causes that inspire them. Mon Calamari suffered under great oppression under The Galactic Empire; thus, it was one of the first worlds to declare support for The Rebel Alliance. Mon Calamari are widely recognized for their keen analytical and organizational abilities, and they have developed a reputation as being among the foremost ship designers in the galaxy. They see everything they create as a work of art, not just a tool or weapon.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":["Amphibious: Can breathe underwater and move normally in water"],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Mon Calamari","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Mon Calamari can't drown in water."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Keenly perceptive, a Mon Calamari with Perception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Mon Calamari may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Mon Calamari may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Mon Calamari ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Wis, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Mon Calamari receive +2 bonuses to their Intelligence and Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Mon Calamari are bright and prudent, but they have relatively frail physiques.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Mon Calamarian"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Conditional Bonus Feat","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Mon Calamari can't drown in water."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Keenly perceptive, a Mon Calamari with Perception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Mon Calamari may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Mon Calamari may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Mon Calamari ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":251},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-mrlssi","name":"Mrlssi","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Mrlssi.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Conditional Bonus Feat","Scholarly Inclination"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Mrlssi have a natural inclination for working with mechanical devices. Mechanics is always a Class Skill for Mrlssi."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Mrlssi love intellectual discussions. A Mrlssi with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"scholarly-inclination","name":"Scholarly Inclination","description":"At 1st level, a Mrlssi gains any one Knowledge skill as a bonus Trained Skill."}],"languages":["Basic","Mrlsstese"],"description":"The diminutive Mrlssi hail from The Colonies region world of Mrlsst, and they are the only sentient Species native to their star system. They evolved from flightless avians, and their faces are dominated by large black eyes and hooked beaks. Mrlssi are typically peaceful and scholarly. Their homeworld has long been home to some of the galaxy's most prestigious universities and research centers, including one of the leading institutions for applied sciences- the Mrlsst Trade and Science Academy. Out of Mrlssi schools grow a host of findings that ease the shipping of food and livestock between worlds, along with innovations that later become standard construction techniques for structures and vessels on planets and in space.","canonicalName":"Mrlssi","canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Mrlssi receive +2 bonuses to their Intelligence and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Mrlssi are small creatures, but they are quick-witted and very charismatic.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Mrlsstese"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Conditional Bonus Feat","Scholarly Inclination"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Mrlssi have a natural inclination for working with mechanical devices. Mechanics is always a Class Skill for Mrlssi."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Mrlssi love intellectual discussions. A Mrlssi with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"scholarly-inclination","name":"Scholarly Inclination","description":"At 1st level, a Mrlssi gains any one Knowledge skill as a bonus Trained Skill."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1963},"tags":["small"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
