{"_id":"species-nagai","name":"Nagai","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nagai.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Cha, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Deception","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Lightning Reflexes","Soothing Voice","Weapon Familiarity"],"languages":["Basic","Nagaian"],"source":"Legacy","description":"Honorable, mysterious, violent, and sinister. All these words and more describe the Nagai people. They first appeared to be galactic invaders, until it was revealed that the Nagai were escaping their long-time enemies, the Tofs. Initially hostile to The New Republic, the Nagai eventually formed an alliance of convenience with The New Republic in an attempt to achieve victory in their war against the Tofs. The Nagai are charismatic- a quality that is, by and large, a product of their enhanced vocal range, which allows them to tailor their speech to be more soothing.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":["Cold Resistance: +5 to Endurance vs cold"],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Nagai","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"lightning-reflexes","name":"Lightning Reflexes","description":"Nagai are fast on their feet and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense."},{"id":"soothing-voice","name":"Soothing Voice","description":"A Nagai may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Nagai treat Tehk'la Blades as Simple Weapons (Melee) instead of as Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Nagai receive a +2 bonus to both their Dexterity and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Nagai are charismatic and agile, but physically frail.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Nagaian"],"special":["Lightning Reflexes","Soothing Voice","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"lightning-reflexes","name":"Lightning Reflexes","description":"Nagai are fast on their feet and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense."},{"id":"soothing-voice","name":"Soothing Voice","description":"A Nagai may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Nagai treat Tehk'la Blades as Simple Weapons (Melee) instead of as Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1480},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nautolan","name":"Nautolan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nautolan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Swim"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Damage Reduction","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision","Pheromonal Sensor"],"languages":["communicate in Nautila","can Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Nautolans are one of the sentient Species native to the planet Glee Anselm. Their language, Nautila, evolved underwater and is heavily tied to pheromones. Out of water, Nautila loses much of its meaning. As a result, Nautolans learn another language, typically either Basic or Anselmian, the language of the Anselmi people, who are native to Glee Anselm's land masses. Even though they are aquatic, Nautolans have little difficulty living in climates that would be uncomfortable for other amphibians.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":["Aquatic: Can breathe underwater, move normally underwater"],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"variants":[{"id":"nautolan-variant","label":"Variant","source":"Legacy","size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Swim"],"special":[],"languages":["Nautila","Basic"],"description":"","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}}}],"canonicalName":"Nautolan","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Nautolans can't drown in water."},{"id":"damage-reduction","name":"Damage Reduction","description":"The rubbery hide of a Nautolan provides a Species bonus of Damage Reduction 2."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Nautolan may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Nautolan may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Nautolans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"pheromonal-sensor","name":"Pheromonal Sensor","description":"A Nautolan can reroll any Perception check made to Sense Deception or Sense Influence, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. If underwater, the Nautolan can take the better of the two results instead."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Nautolans receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Wisdom. Nautolan are tough, but also reckless and foolhardy.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["communicate in Nautila","can Basic"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Damage Reduction","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision","Pheromonal Sensor"],"traits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Nautolans can't drown in water."},{"id":"damage-reduction","name":"Damage Reduction","description":"The rubbery hide of a Nautolan provides a Species bonus of Damage Reduction 2."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Nautolan may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Nautolan may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Nautolans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"pheromonal-sensor","name":"Pheromonal Sensor","description":"A Nautolan can reroll any Perception check made to Sense Deception or Sense Influence, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. If underwater, the Nautolan can take the better of the two results instead."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1322},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nazren","name":"Nazren","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nazren.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Resilience"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"resilience","name":"Resilience","description":"Once per encounter, when a Nazren would be moved down the Condition Track by taking damage equal to or exceeding the Nazren's Damage Threshold, the Nazren may reduce the number of steps moved down the Condition Track by 1 (to a minimum of 0 steps)."}],"languages":["Basic","Nazren"],"description":"","canonicalName":"Nazren","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Nazren receive +2 bonuses to both their Strength and Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to their Dexterity and Charisma. Nazren are strong and hardy but taciturn and withdrawn; they shun the spotlight.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Nazren"],"special":["Resilience"],"traits":[{"id":"resilience","name":"Resilience","description":"Once per encounter, when a Nazren would be moved down the Condition Track by taking damage equal to or exceeding the Nazren's Damage Threshold, the Nazren may reduce the number of steps moved down the Condition Track by 1 (to a minimum of 0 steps)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2542},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-near-human","name":"Near-Human","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Near-Human.jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":[],"special":["Genetic Drift"],"languages":["Basic"],"source":"Multiple","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Near-Human","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-neimoidian","name":"Neimoidian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Neimoidian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feats"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feats","name":"Conditional Bonus Feats","description":"Neimoidians strive to slant deals in their favor, and they make agreements that they can break easily if they feel so inclined. A Neimoidian with Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat. A Neimoidian Trained in Persuasion gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."}],"languages":["speak","Basic","Neimoidian"],"description":"The Neimoidians quickly find a place in galactic civilization, excited by the prospect of markets beyond their own worlds. For several centuries, they are among the leading forces behind the construction of new starports and the upgrade of existing ones. They trade with everyone- Republic or Sith, Hutt or Herglic- because to the Neimoidians, all that matters is a market for their goods. They help found the Trade Federation, a cartel of mercantile interests that, driven by Neimoidian greed, becomes so powerful that it threatens the very interstellar commerce it exists to protect. When the organization attempts to become the sole conduit for trade in certain parts of space, the Senate and the Jedi intervene.","canonicalName":"Neimoidian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"Neimoidians receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Neimoidians avoid physical activity and confrontation, preferring instead to rely on the power of their personalities to achieve success.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["speak","Basic","Neimoidian"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feats"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feats","name":"Conditional Bonus Feats","description":"Neimoidians strive to slant deals in their favor, and they make agreements that they can break easily if they feel so inclined. A Neimoidian with Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat. A Neimoidian Trained in Persuasion gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."}],"variants":[{"id":"neimoidian-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"int":2,"cha":2,"str":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feats","Deceptive"],"languages":["speak","Basic","Neimoidian","Pak Pak"],"description":"Alternate Neimoidian trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feats","name":"Conditional Bonus Feats","description":"A Neimoidian with Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"A Neimoidians may choose to reroll any Deception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}]}],"sourceLine":1984},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[{"id":"neimoidian-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feats","Deceptive"],"languages":["speak","Basic","Neimoidian","Pak Pak"],"description":"Alternate Neimoidian trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feats","name":"Conditional Bonus Feats","description":"A Neimoidian with Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"A Neimoidians may choose to reroll any Deception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}]}],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":9900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nelvaanian","name":"Nelvaanian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nelvaanian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"special":["Low-Light Vision","Primitive","Scent","Shadow Swiftness"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Nelvaanians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Nelvaanians do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Nelvaanians have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Nelvaanians ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."},{"id":"shadow-swiftness","name":"Shadow Swiftness","description":"If a Nelvaanian begins its turn with Concealment from a target or with the target unaware of it, the Nelvaanian does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity when moving through the target's threatened space until the end of the Nelvaanian's turn."}],"languages":["Nelvaanese"],"description":"Nelvaanians, also referred to as Nelvaans, are a Species of tribal humanoids from the planet Nelvaan. They are a primitive Species, using only crude technology. Male Nelvaanians are responsible for hunting game and protecting the tribe, while females are responsible for the day-to-day affairs of their tribe, which includes raising cubs. At the top of the Nelvaanian tribe is the chief, who rules with the help of his mate and a shaman. A tribal chief is not chosen by trial, nor is he elected to his position.","canonicalName":"Nelvaanian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Nelvaanians receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Intelligence. Nelvaanians are thoughtful and patient, but are primitive and rooted in tradition.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Nelvaanese"],"special":["Low-Light Vision","Primitive","Scent","Shadow Swiftness"],"traits":[{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Nelvaanians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Nelvaanians do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Nelvaanians have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Nelvaanians ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."},{"id":"shadow-swiftness","name":"Shadow Swiftness","description":"If a Nelvaanian begins its turn with Concealment from a target or with the target unaware of it, the Nelvaanian does not provoke Attacks of Opportunity when moving through the target's threatened space until the end of the Nelvaanian's turn."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1343},"tags":["medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nerf-uplifted","name":"Nerf (Uplifted)","type":"species","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Horns"],"languages":["Binary"],"source":"Scavenger","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Nerf (Uplifted)","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nikto","name":"Nikto","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nikto.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Great Fortitude","Natural Armor","Survival Instinct"],"languages":["Nikto"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Widely recognized as a slave species of the Hutts, the Nikto have served their masters since before the founding of The Old Republic, proving to be cunning warriors in the Hutts' battle with the legendary conqueror Xim the Despot. Wherever the Hutts are, the Nikto are never far behind. Because of their homeworld's radioactive atmosphere, the Nikto have five distinct subspecies, each adapted to a specific type of terrain (see Nikto Survival feat).","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Nikto","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Nikto gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense, having evolved to survive the harsh environment of their homeworld."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Nikto's tough hide provides a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"A Nikto can choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Nikto receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Charisma. Nikto are tough and hardened, but their subservient status stunts their willpower and creativity.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Nikto"],"special":["Great Fortitude","Natural Armor","Survival Instinct"],"traits":[{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Nikto gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense, having evolved to survive the harsh environment of their homeworld."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Nikto's tough hide provides a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"A Nikto can choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2297},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-noghri","name":"Noghri","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Noghri.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Wis, -4 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth","+2 Survival"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Primitive","Scent"],"languages":["Honoghran"],"source":"Threats","description":"The Noghri culture is built around clans (among them Kihm'bar, Bakh'tor, Eikh'mir, and Hakh'khar) with a long history of bloody rivalry. By the time of the Clone Wars, the clans had put aside their differences and learned to coexist, unaware of other intelligent Species in the galaxy. A space battle in orbit over their world led to a starship crash that contaminated the planet with toxic chemicals. The Noghri faced famine and extinction when a black-garbed visitor from the stars arrived: Darth Vader. He promised to save their dying homeworld; in return, the Noghri pledged to serve him and the Empire.","tags":["primitive","small"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[{"name":"Claws","damage":"1d4","type":"slashing"}],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Scent: Can track by smell, detect adjacent hidden creatures","Toxic Resistance: +5 to Fortitude vs poisons"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Noghri","variants":[{"id":"noghri-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -4 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-4},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Scent","Primitive","Bonus Feat","Quick Reflexes"],"languages":["Honoghran"],"description":"Alternate Noghri trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Noghri have an extremely strong sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Noghri ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Noghri do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"All Noghri gain the Martial Arts I feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"quick-reflexes","name":"Quick Reflexes","description":"A Noghri may choose to reroll any Initiative check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}]}],"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-4},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Noghri are quick and agile fighters. A Noghri gains Running Attack as a bonus Feat at 1st level, provided he or she meets the prerequisites of the Feat (minimum Dexterity of 13)."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Noghri do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Noghri have an extremely strong sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Noghri ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Wis, -4 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-4},"abilityText":"All Noghri receive a +2 bonus to both their Dexterity and Wisdom, but suffer a -4 penalty to their Charisma. Noghri are quick and wise, but serious and not very personable.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Honoghran"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Primitive","Scent"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Noghri are quick and agile fighters. A Noghri gains Running Attack as a bonus Feat at 1st level, provided he or she meets the prerequisites of the Feat (minimum Dexterity of 13)."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Noghri do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Noghri have an extremely strong sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Noghri ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"variants":[{"id":"noghri-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -4 Cha","abilityMods":{"dex":2,"cha":-4},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Scent","Primitive","Bonus Feat","Quick Reflexes"],"languages":["Honoghran"],"description":"Alternate Noghri trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Noghri have an extremely strong sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Noghri ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Noghri do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"All Noghri gain the Martial Arts I feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"quick-reflexes","name":"Quick Reflexes","description":"A Noghri may choose to reroll any Initiative check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}]}],"sourceLine":852},"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nosaurian","name":"Nosaurian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nosaurian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Natural Weapons","Survival Instinct"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"A Nosaurian treats the Climb skill as a Class Skill, regardless of Heroic Class."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Nosaurians has a Natural Weapon, in the form of sharp horns. When a Nosaurian makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapon, dealing 1d6 points of piercing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Nosaurians are always considered armed with their Natural Weapon."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"A Nosaurian can choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"languages":["Basic","Nosaurian"],"description":"The Nosaurians are bipedal reptilian creatures native to New Plympto. They are a proud but embattled Species. A crumbling economy unaided by Republic restrictions forced the Nosaurians to join The Confederacy of Independent Systems. After the defeat of the CIS, the Nosaurians tried to carry on the fight, only to be crushed by Darth Vader's Stormtrooper contingent, the 501st. The Dark Times brought the Nosaurians defeat, enslavement, and the systematic exploitation of their world by their new Imperial masters.","canonicalName":"Nosaurian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Nosaurians receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Nosaurian reflexes are quick, but their demeanor is abrasive toward other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Nosaurian"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Natural Weapons","Survival Instinct"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"A Nosaurian treats the Climb skill as a Class Skill, regardless of Heroic Class."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Nosaurians has a Natural Weapon, in the form of sharp horns. When a Nosaurian makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapon, dealing 1d6 points of piercing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Nosaurians are always considered armed with their Natural Weapon."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"A Nosaurian can choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":882},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-nyriaanan","name":"Nyriaanan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Nyriaanan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Survival is always considered a Class Skill for Nyriaanans."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Like their Human ancestors, Nyriaanans are versatile and gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Nyriaanans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"languages":["Nyriaanan"],"description":"Nyriaanans are a group of Near-Humans native to the rich mineral world of Nyriaan. Nyriaanans divide themselves along family lines into hundreds of different clans. Some are nomadic, wandering the waterlogged plains of their homeworld, while others inhabit the same groves of Meadlin's Trees that their ancestors settled centuries, or even millennia, before. They are a peaceful people, but the natives are easily angered by offworlders that care more for turning a profit than for honor or integrity. Although they are not technological in nature, Nyriaan's natives foster the technology of their ancestors as well as adopt newer technology as they acquire it.","canonicalName":"Nyriaanan","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Nyriaanans receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Nyriaanans are calm and thoughtful, but rarely interact with outsiders.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Nyriaanan"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Survival is always considered a Class Skill for Nyriaanans."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Like their Human ancestors, Nyriaanans are versatile and gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Nyriaanans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2009},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-o-reenian","name":"O'reenian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/O'reenian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Heightened Awareness","Persistent"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"An O'reenian may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"persistent","name":"Persistent","description":"An O'reenian can reroll any Endurance check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"languages":["O'reenian"],"description":"The people of O'reen take the defense of their world very seriously. Despite this fact, there are many strange and powerful races throughout The Unknown Regions that have technology that is unfamiliar to the O'reenians, making it difficult for them to sense threats from the outside until it is too late. As a result, the O'reenians have created a network of Orbital Defense Mines that detect, move toward, and attack any Starship approaching O'reen without proper transponder identifiers.","canonicalName":"O'reenian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"None. O'reenians are trained both in mind and in body, adapting to all circumstances.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["O'reenian"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Persistent"],"traits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"An O'reenian may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"persistent","name":"Persistent","description":"An O'reenian can reroll any Endurance check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2320},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ortolan","name":"Ortolan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ortolan.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception"],"special":["Cold Resistance"],"languages":["Ortolese","Basic"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Ortolan","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-pa-lowick","name":"Pa'lowick","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Pa'lowick.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"special":["Expert Swimmer","Hold Breath","Primitive"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Pa'lowicks may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Pa'lowicks may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"hold-breath","name":"Hold Breath","description":"Pa'lowicks are at home either in air or in water. A Pa'lowick can hold his or her breath for a number of rounds equal to 25 times his or her Constitution score before needing to make Endurance checks to hold his or her breath."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Pa'lowicks do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."}],"languages":["Basic","Lowickese"],"description":"A mining expedition discovered the Pa'lowick homeworld about ten years before the Battle of Endor, making Pa'lowicks one of the newer Species to join galactic society. Though technologically primitive, Pa'lowicks have a sophisticated and highly adaptive feudal society (ruled by noble families). They welcome contact with other Species and enjoy trading foodstuffs and primitive wares for useful technological devices they cannot build themselves. Regular trade with other Species has done little to change the way Pa'lowicks live. Although they like to collect high-tech items, most are content to \"Nest\" on their homeworld, enjoying the simple life of farming, fishing, hunting, and storytelling.","canonicalName":"Pa'lowick","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Pa'lowicks receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Pa'lowicks are a contemplative Species, but their lack of muscle mass hampers their physical prowess.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Lowickese"],"special":["Expert Swimmer","Hold Breath","Primitive"],"traits":[{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Pa'lowicks may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Pa'lowicks may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"hold-breath","name":"Hold Breath","description":"Pa'lowicks are at home either in air or in water. A Pa'lowick can hold his or her breath for a number of rounds equal to 25 times his or her Constitution score before needing to make Endurance checks to hold his or her breath."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Pa'lowicks do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2027},"tags":["medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-pau-an","name":"Pau'an","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Pau'an.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Authority","Conditional Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision"],"languages":["Basic","Utapese"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Xenobiologists from the University of Sanbra have uncovered connections between the Pau'ans and the Utai, the smaller Species with whom they share the planet of Utapau. Genetic sampling has confirmed a few tenuous biological links, though the exact evolutionary process by which the Pau'an Species developed separately from the Utai is still a mystery. Xenoanthropologists date the first Pau'an civilizations back almost 57,000 years before the Battle of Yavin, making theirs one of the youngest known civilizations. Though no written history of this time exists, scientists currently theorize that the long-lived Pau'ans are genetically closer to their progenitor Species, and that as a result of their longevity the Pau'ans have likely only evolved a little since the planet was settled. Some time in the last ten thousand years, Utapau underwent a climate change that caused winds on the surface of the world to reach and maintain constant bursts at destructive speeds.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"variants":[{"id":"pau-an-variant","label":"Variant","source":"Rebellion","size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Heightened Hearing"],"languages":["Utapaun","Basic"],"description":"","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}}}],"canonicalName":"Pau'an","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"authority","name":"Authority","description":"As a Species accustomed to being in authority, Pau'ans add a +1 bonus to any insight or morale bonuses they grant to themselves or other characters."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Pau'an with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Pau'ans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Pau'ans receive +2 bonuses to both their Wisdom and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Pau'ans leave most of the manual labor to their Utai neighbors, but they are capable leaders.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Utapese"],"special":["Authority","Conditional Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"authority","name":"Authority","description":"As a Species accustomed to being in authority, Pau'ans add a +1 bonus to any insight or morale bonuses they grant to themselves or other characters."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Pau'an with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Pau'ans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2561},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":10900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-phindian","name":"Phindian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Phindian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Bonus Feat","Conditional Bonus Feat"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"All Phindians gain Skill Training (Knowledge (Technology)) as a bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Phindians that have Mechanics as a Trained Skill gain Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."}],"languages":["Basic","Phindian"],"description":"Phindians are technologically advanced sentients known for creating a variety of technical wonders, including devices capable of erasing one's memory. Before the rise of the Empire, a criminal organization called The Syndicat ruled the Phindian homeworld. The Phindian leaders of The Syndicat used their control over the distribution of food and other provisions to keep the general population in line. Any who resisted The Syndicat had their memories erased and were exiled to other worlds. The Jedi helped the Phindian population overthrow The Syndicat and install a democratic government, which remained in place until the formation of the Emperor's New Order.","canonicalName":"Phindian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Phindians receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Phindians are sharp-minded, but typically anti-social.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Phindian"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Conditional Bonus Feat"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"All Phindians gain Skill Training (Knowledge (Technology)) as a bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Phindians that have Mechanics as a Trained Skill gain Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2577},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-polis-massan","name":"Polis Massan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Polis Massan.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Limited Telepathy","Mute"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Polis Massans are known across the galaxy for their skill with medicine. A Polis Massan with Treat Injury as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Treat Injury) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Polis Massans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"limited-telepathy","name":"Limited Telepathy","description":"In conjunction with their sign language and technological methods of communication, Polis Massans are able to employ a weak form Telepathy that allows them to convey simple feelings and thoughts to any willing recipient within 10 squares. Polis Massans can use the Telepathy aspect of the Use the Force skill Untrained (even if not Force-sensitive). If the target of the Telepathy is within 10 squares, no skill check is required to initiate the telepathic contact."},{"id":"mute","name":"Mute","description":"Polis Massans have no vocal cords, and must rely on a combination of sign language, computers, and Telepathy in order to communicate with others. When they learn new Languages, they can understand but not speak them."}],"languages":["Basic","Massan"],"description":"The small asteroid mining colony of Polis Massa in The Outer Rim is the current homeworld of the Polis Massans. Though the Polis Massans evolved on another world in the Subterrel sector, they have been away from their homeworld for so long that they have no living memory of their origins. Instead, they have dedicated themselves to researching a lost civilization, once native to Polis Massa, known as the Eellayin. The planet once inhabited by the Eellayin was subject to a great and mysterious cataclysm which caused it to break apart into several million fragments. The Polis Massa asteroid is one of the largest fragments to survive, and many artifacts and traces of the fallen civilization are hidden within its depths.","canonicalName":"Polis Massan","canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Polis Massans receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Polis Massans are thoughtful and ponderous, but their physique is largely lackluster.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Massan"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Limited Telepathy","Mute"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Polis Massans are known across the galaxy for their skill with medicine. A Polis Massan with Treat Injury as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Treat Injury) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Polis Massans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"limited-telepathy","name":"Limited Telepathy","description":"In conjunction with their sign language and technological methods of communication, Polis Massans are able to employ a weak form Telepathy that allows them to convey simple feelings and thoughts to any willing recipient within 10 squares. Polis Massans can use the Telepathy aspect of the Use the Force skill Untrained (even if not Force-sensitive). If the target of the Telepathy is within 10 squares, no skill check is required to initiate the telepathic contact."},{"id":"mute","name":"Mute","description":"Polis Massans have no vocal cords, and must rely on a combination of sign language, computers, and Telepathy in order to communicate with others. When they learn new Languages, they can understand but not speak them."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2595},"tags":["small"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-quarren","name":"Quarren","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Quarren.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Swim"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Conditional Bonus Feat","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision"],"languages":["Basic","Quarrenese"],"source":"Core","description":"The Quarren hail from the distant Outer Rim planet of Mon Calamari, sharing the world with the sentient humanoid Species of the same name. The Mon Calamari live on the surface of the world, while the more isolationist Quarren dwell in oxygen-filled cities in the deep recesses of the oceans. Offworld, Quarren generally stay clear of galactic politics. Instead, they often become involved with shadowy occupations such as pirates, smugglers, and spy networks. Many Quarren blame both the Empire and the Rebels (even more than the Mon Calamari) for their homeworld's devastation during the Galactic Civil War.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":["Amphibious: Can breathe underwater and move normally in water"],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"variants":[{"id":"quarren-variant","label":"Variant","source":"Legacy","size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Swim"],"special":["Deep Water Adaptation"],"languages":["Quarren","Basic"],"description":"","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}}}],"canonicalName":"Quarren","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Quarren can't drown in water."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Adept traders and negotiators, Quarren with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Quarren may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Quarren may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Quarren ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Quarren receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but take -2 penalties to both Wisdom and Charisma. Quarren are extremely resilient and physically tough, though they tend toward deficiencies in wisdom and social graces.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Quarrenese"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Conditional Bonus Feat","Expert Swimmer","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Quarren can't drown in water."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Adept traders and negotiators, Quarren with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Quarren may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Quarren may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Quarren ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":276},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-quermian","name":"Quermian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Quermian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, +2 Wis, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Knowledge"],"special":["Four Arms","Sensitive Smell"],"languages":["Quermian","Basic"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":2,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Quermian","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-rakata","name":"Rakata","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Rakata.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Use the Force"],"special":["Ancient Knowledge","Conditional Bonus Feat","Force Blind","Primitive","Rage","Weapon Familiarity"],"languages":["Rakata"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"The Rakata and their planet became lost to history, perhaps purposefully erased by the newly freed societies. Their former subjects eliminated their former masters, or forced them to leave. Rakata civilization on their homeworld of Lehon deteriorated until all that remained were small, primitive tribes. Eventually, the Rakata are rediscovered by Darth Revan, who learns the secret of The Star Forge and uses it to build a massive military force to attack the Republic. Darth Revan and the Republic are also responsible for the destruction of The Star Forge.","tags":["force","medium","primitive"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Rakata","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"ancient-knowledge","name":"Ancient Knowledge","description":"Rakata retain many of the qualities that led their ancestors to create great technological works in the distant past. Rakata reduce the penalty for not being proficient in a weapon from -5 to -2, and reduce the Armor Check Penalty for Armor they are not proficient in by one step (-5 for Heavy Armor, -2 for Medium Armor, and no penalty for Light Armor). All other penalties for not being proficient still apply. Additionally, once per encounter the Rakata can use a Trained-only application of the Mechanics, Pilot, Treat Injury, or Use Computer skills, even if Untrained in that skill."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Rakata with Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons) or proficient with any Exotic Weapon (Melee) gain the Weapon Focus feat (for Simple Weapons or a chosen Exotic Weapon (Melee)) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"force-blind","name":"Force Blind","description":"For reasons unknown, the Rakata have lost their connection to The Force. Rakata cannot take the Force Sensitivity feat. They can still increase their Dark Side Score and are still affected by Force Powers, Force Talents, and the Use the Force skill as normal."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Rakata do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Rakata can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While raging, the Rakata temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Rakata's Constitution modifier. At the end of its rage, the Rakata moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Rakata takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Rakata can't engage in any strenuous activity."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Rakata do not treat Rakatan Weapons as Exotic Weapons, instead treating them as a base item (for instance, a Rakatan Blaster Rifle would still be treated as a Rifle)."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Rakata receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Rakata are crafty and intelligent, but their pride can blind them to their mistakes.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Rakata"],"special":["Ancient Knowledge","Conditional Bonus Feat","Force Blind","Primitive","Rage","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"ancient-knowledge","name":"Ancient Knowledge","description":"Rakata retain many of the qualities that led their ancestors to create great technological works in the distant past. Rakata reduce the penalty for not being proficient in a weapon from -5 to -2, and reduce the Armor Check Penalty for Armor they are not proficient in by one step (-5 for Heavy Armor, -2 for Medium Armor, and no penalty for Light Armor). All other penalties for not being proficient still apply. Additionally, once per encounter the Rakata can use a Trained-only application of the Mechanics, Pilot, Treat Injury, or Use Computer skills, even if Untrained in that skill."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Rakata with Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons) or proficient with any Exotic Weapon (Melee) gain the Weapon Focus feat (for Simple Weapons or a chosen Exotic Weapon (Melee)) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"force-blind","name":"Force Blind","description":"For reasons unknown, the Rakata have lost their connection to The Force. Rakata cannot take the Force Sensitivity feat. They can still increase their Dark Side Score and are still affected by Force Powers, Force Talents, and the Use the Force skill as normal."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Rakata do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Rakata can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While raging, the Rakata temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Rakata's Constitution modifier. At the end of its rage, the Rakata moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Rakata takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Rakata can't engage in any strenuous activity."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Rakata do not treat Rakatan Weapons as Exotic Weapons, instead treating them as a base item (for instance, a Rakatan Blaster Rifle would still be treated as a Rifle)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":703},"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-replica-droid","name":"Replica Droid","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Replica Droid.webp","system":{"size":"Variable","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{"Small":{"walk":4},"Medium":{"walk":6}}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"noConstitution":true,"special":["Bonus Equipment","Conditional Bonus Feat","Droid Traits"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-equipment","name":"Bonus Equipment","description":"Replica Droids can be constructed with two of the following Droid Systems installed: Internal Comlink, Darkvision, Diagnostics Package, Improved Sensor Package, Internal Storage (subject to size limitations), Translator Unit (DC 15)."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Seeking to perfectly imitate organic creatures, a Replica Droid that has Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"droid-traits","name":"Droid Traits","description":"Replica Droids operate as if they are 4th-Degree Droids, except that they ignore the Maintenance requirement. Replica Droids have all Droid Immunities and normal Droid Traits."}],"languages":["Binary","Replicated species native language"],"description":"These Replica Droids were originally designed by the Alliance to Restore the Republic to infiltrate and replace Imperial personnel, but their funding ultimately ran out, causing them to abandon the project. Ironically enough, The Empire completed and perfected the Replica Droid's design, through they were never put into any major use.","canonicalName":"Replica Droid","canonicalStats":{"size":"Variable","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{"Small":{"walk":4},"Medium":{"walk":6}}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Replica Droids receive a +2 bonus to both their Strength and Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Replica Droids are built to be physically strong, but have to work to fit in seamlessly with organic beings. Additionally, like other Droids, Replica Droids have no Constitution score.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Binary","Replicated species native language"],"special":["Bonus Equipment","Conditional Bonus Feat","Droid Traits"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-equipment","name":"Bonus Equipment","description":"Replica Droids can be constructed with two of the following Droid Systems installed: Internal Comlink, Darkvision, Diagnostics Package, Improved Sensor Package, Internal Storage (subject to size limitations), Translator Unit (DC 15)."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Seeking to perfectly imitate organic creatures, a Replica Droid that has Deception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"droid-traits","name":"Droid Traits","description":"Replica Droids operate as if they are 4th-Degree Droids, except that they ignore the Maintenance requirement. Replica Droids have all Droid Immunities and normal Droid Traits."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":494},"tags":["droid","variable","droid-builder","replica-droid"],"variants":[],"droidBuilder":{"required":true,"mode":"replica-droid","label":"Replica Droid Chassis","noConstitution":true,"retainsConstitution":false,"speciesActsAsDroid":true,"fixedDegree":"4th-degree","defaultDegree":"4th-degree","allowedSizes":["small","medium"],"defaultSize":"medium","bonusEquipmentChoices":2,"allowedCategories":["communications","sensors","translators","miscellaneous"],"allowedAccessorySubcategories":["communications","sensors","translators","miscellaneous"],"allowedAccessoryIds":["internal-comlink","darkvision","diagnostics-package","improved-sensor-package","internal-storage","basic-translator","advanced-translator","universal-translator"],"notes":"Replica Droid characters use the droid builder as a constrained HRD chassis. They operate as 4th-degree droids, have no Constitution score, ignore the normal droid maintenance requirement, and choose two listed installed systems."},"speciesActsAsDroid":true,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-republic-clone","name":"Republic Clone","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Republic Clone.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"Republic Clones begin play with the following Ability Score array: Strength 15, Dexterity 13, Constitution 10, Intelligence 12, Wisdom 10, and Charisma 8. Additionally, a Republic Clone player can choose one Ability Score to increase by 2 at the time of Character Creation.","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityChoice":{"type":"fixedArray","label":"Republic Clone Training Emphasis","fixedScores":{"str":15,"dex":13,"con":10,"int":12,"wis":10,"cha":8},"bonusChoices":["str","dex","con","int","wis","cha"],"bonusValue":2,"description":"Republic Clones begin play with the following Ability Score array: Strength 15, Dexterity 13, Constitution 10, Intelligence 12, Wisdom 10, and Charisma 8. Additionally, a Republic Clone player can choose one Ability Score to increase by 2 at the time of Character Creation.","allocationPoints":2,"maxPerAbility":1,"allocationMode":"level-4-two-abilities","requiresGmApprovalOnOverride":true,"helpText":"Republic Clones start with STR 15, DEX 13, CON 10, INT 12, WIS 10, CHA 8, then distribute two +1 attribute increases as if using the level 4 attribute increase step."},"special":["Bonus Feat","Bonus Trained Skill"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Republic Clones gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Republic Clones are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. A Republic Clone character chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."}],"languages":["Basic"],"description":"Given the prominence of Clones in the story of the Clone Wars, Gamemasters should not be surprised if players wish to play Clone characters. Clone Trooper heroes can be interesting and present exciting story opportunities, especially for a Gamemaster who plans to use Order 66 in the campaign finale. Gamemasters should allow players to play Clone Trooper heroes who stand out from the rank-and-file Clone Troopers. The basic Republic Clone is bred for obedience and military discipline. This can stifle players who want more free will.","canonicalName":"Republic Clone","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"Republic Clones begin play with the following Ability Score array: Strength 15, Dexterity 13, Constitution 10, Intelligence 12, Wisdom 10, and Charisma 8. Additionally, a Republic Clone player can choose one Ability Score to increase by 2 at the time of Character Creation.","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Republic Clones begin play with the following Ability Score array: Strength 15, Dexterity 13, Constitution 10, Intelligence 12, Wisdom 10, and Charisma 8. Additionally, a Republic Clone player can choose one Ability Score to increase by 2 at the time of Character Creation.","abilityChoice":{"type":"fixedArray","description":"Republic Clones begin play with the following Ability Score array: Strength 15, Dexterity 13, Constitution 10, Intelligence 12, Wisdom 10, and Charisma 8. Additionally, a Republic Clone player can choose one Ability Score to increase by 2 at the time of Character Creation."},"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Bonus Trained Skill"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Republic Clones gain one bonus Feat at 1st level."},{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Republic Clones are versatile and accomplished at many tasks. A Republic Clone character chooses one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the character's list of Class Skills."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1365},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"fixedAbilityScores":{"str":15,"dex":13,"con":10,"int":12,"wis":10,"cha":8},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-rodian","name":"Rodian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Rodian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Survival"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Heightened Awareness","Low-Light Vision"],"languages":["Basic","Rodese"],"source":"Core","description":"Rodians hail from the Tyrius System of The Mid Rim, their homeworld humid and choked with heavy rain forests teeming with dangerous life forms. In this hostile environment, the Rodians evolved into brutal hunters and killers to survive. As a result, Rodian culture centers around the concept of \"The Hunt.\" Their art glorifies violence and the art of stalking prey. The more intelligent and dangerous a hunter's prey, the more honorable the hunt. Rodians have numerous annual festivals that exists solely to honor such activities.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":["Low-Light Vision"],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Rodian","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Rodians are taught how to track and survive in the wilderness of Rodia from a very young age. A Rodian with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Rodian may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Rodians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Rodians receive a +2 bonus to Dexterity, but they suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Charisma. Rodians are quick and well coordinated, but often act before thinking things through, and are often rude and try to bully others.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Rodese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Heightened Awareness","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Rodians are taught how to track and survive in the wilderness of Rodia from a very young age. A Rodian with Survival as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Survival) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Rodian may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Rodians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":303},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ryn","name":"Ryn","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ryn.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Deception","+2 Use Computer"],"special":["Connections","Musical Obfuscation","Prehensile Tail"],"languages":["Basic","Ryn"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Ubiquitous in spaceports throughout the galaxy, Ryn are a Species of nomads and adventurers, scoundrels, strels, and rogues. No one is certain where the Ryn come from; no record of a homeworld exists, and Ryn culture, such as it is, requires them to never sleep in the same place twice. Some speculate that the Ryn were a race of warriors, dispatched to Core Worlds ages ago to contend with some threat, while others suggest that the Ryn were a tribe of ten thousand musicians gifted to a world that had no artists of their own. Either could be true, for the Ryn are as fearless in battle as they are skilled in music. For all their talents, Ryn find the galaxy largely inhospitable.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Ryn","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"connections","name":"Connections","description":"Ryn benefit from an extensive information network that spans the galaxy. Whenever they travel, they can contact other Ryn to learn rumors and guarded information more easily than other races. Whenever a Ryn makes a Gather Information check to Learn Secret Information, they can forgo the credit cost. If this check fails, the Ryn can try again, but must spend the credits as normal."},{"id":"musical-obfuscation","name":"Musical Obfuscation","description":"Ryn can move air through their beaks to create pleasant tunes and notes. A Ryn can reroll any Deception check to convey Deceptive Information, keeping the better of the two results. A Ryn can project their sounds out to a range of 10 squares. As a Swift Action, a Ryn can Create a Diversion to Hide."},{"id":"prehensile-tail","name":"Prehensile Tail","description":"Ryn have long tails nearly as strong and flexible as their hands. A Ryn can effectively hold (but not wield) a Small or smaller item with its tail. When holding a Medium or larger item with its tail, the Ryn is Encumbered and considered to be carrying a Heavy Load."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Ryn receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma. Ryn are gifted entertainers and performers.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Ryn"],"special":["Connections","Musical Obfuscation","Prehensile Tail"],"traits":[{"id":"connections","name":"Connections","description":"Ryn benefit from an extensive information network that spans the galaxy. Whenever they travel, they can contact other Ryn to learn rumors and guarded information more easily than other races. Whenever a Ryn makes a Gather Information check to Learn Secret Information, they can forgo the credit cost. If this check fails, the Ryn can try again, but must spend the credits as normal."},{"id":"musical-obfuscation","name":"Musical Obfuscation","description":"Ryn can move air through their beaks to create pleasant tunes and notes. A Ryn can reroll any Deception check to convey Deceptive Information, keeping the better of the two results. A Ryn can project their sounds out to a range of 10 squares. As a Swift Action, a Ryn can Create a Diversion to Hide."},{"id":"prehensile-tail","name":"Prehensile Tail","description":"Ryn have long tails nearly as strong and flexible as their hands. A Ryn can effectively hold (but not wield) a Small or smaller item with its tail. When holding a Medium or larger item with its tail, the Ryn is Encumbered and considered to be carrying a Heavy Load."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1117},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-sakiyan","name":"Sakiyan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Sakiyan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception"],"special":["Darkvision","Conditional Bonus Feat","Lightning Reflexes"],"languages":["Basic","Sakiyan"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Sakiyans rarely venture far from their home system, showing little interest in traveling or trading with the galaxy at large. During the days of the Old Republic, there was some dispute among xenobiologists as to whether the Sakiyans should be classified as a Near-Human Species. The unusual structure of their brain led Imperial xenobiologists to conclude that they were a distinctly alien Species. The highly evolved Sakiyan brain is nearly twice the size of the average Human brain. While the Bith brain remains one of the most advanced among common alien Species, the parts of the Sakiyan brain that process sensory input are superior even to the Bith.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Sakiyan","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Sakiyans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Sakiyan with Perception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"lightning-reflexes","name":"Lightning Reflexes","description":"Sakiyans gain a +2 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Sakiyans are notable versatile for a Species, and as such receive no bonuses or penalties to their Ability Scores.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Sakiyan"],"special":["Darkvision","Conditional Bonus Feat","Lightning Reflexes"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Sakiyans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Sakiyan with Perception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"lightning-reflexes","name":"Lightning Reflexes","description":"Sakiyans gain a +2 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1505},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":11900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-selkath","name":"Selkath","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Selkath.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Swim"],"special":["Able Healers","Breathe Underwater","Expert Swimmer"],"languages":["Selkath"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"Few Selkath travel offworld, preferring the habitat of their homeworld. They have never joined the Republic, or any galactic organization, so most have little reason to leave. They enjoy the technology and wealth produced by the sale of Kolto. All contact with offworlders occurs in Ahto; the Selkath live in underwater cities and settlements scattered around the planet. As amphibious creatures, they are equally at home in either locale.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Selkath","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"able-healers","name":"Able Healers","description":"Whenever a Selkath restores Hit Points to another character by any means, or Aids Another who is doing so, the target regains an additional 5 Hit Points. Additionally, once per encounter as a Swift Action, the Selkath can grant an adjacent ally Bonus Hit Points equal to 10 + the Selkath's Character Level, which last until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Selkath can't drown in water."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Selkath may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Selkath may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Selkath receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma. Most Selkath tend to be skilled in talking their way out of an argument, without taking a side.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Selkath"],"special":["Able Healers","Breathe Underwater","Expert Swimmer"],"traits":[{"id":"able-healers","name":"Able Healers","description":"Whenever a Selkath restores Hit Points to another character by any means, or Aids Another who is doing so, the target regains an additional 5 Hit Points. Additionally, once per encounter as a Swift Action, the Selkath can grant an adjacent ally Bonus Hit Points equal to 10 + the Selkath's Character Level, which last until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Selkath can't drown in water."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Selkath may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Selkath may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":724},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-shard","name":"Shard","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Shard.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"retainsConstitution":true,"special":["Bonus Trained Skill","Droid Shell"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Shards gain Use Computer as a bonus Trained Skill, regardless of their Class."},{"id":"droid-shell","name":"Droid Shell","description":"Shards must inhabit Droid Bodies to travel and function in the galaxy at large. In this form, they gain the following traits: Shards must undergo Maintenance, as per a Droid. Shards are immune to Poison, Radiation, noncorrosive Atmospheric Hazards, and Vacuum. They can regain Hit Points only through the Repair Droid application of the Mechanics skill. They do not benefit from Natural Healing, unless they have the Force Repair Talent. Shards are considered cybernetic creatures for the purposes of Ion Damage. Shards can make use of Droid systems and accessories, subject to some limitations. Shards can have the following Droid Systems, with a Cost Modifier of x1: Appendages Droid Armor Communications Systems Compartment Space Sensor Systems Translator Units"}],"languages":["Basic","Binary"],"description":"Shards are crystalline beings native to the planet Orax. Although immobile and silicone-based, Shards are sentient and can communicate with others through computers and other electronic receivers. Some Shards, like The Iron Knights, have themselves placed inside Droid Bodies that they can manipulate telepathically. Many, if not all, Shards are Force-sensitive. Shards in Droid Bodies, disconnected from their group-mind, became insatiably curious, and almost intoxicated by the new sensory experiences.","canonicalName":"Shard","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Shards receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Shards have powerful minds, but must rely on somewhat clumsy Droid Bodies. A Shard retains its Constitution score, even when inside a Droid Body.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Binary"],"special":["Bonus Trained Skill","Droid Shell"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"Shards gain Use Computer as a bonus Trained Skill, regardless of their Class."},{"id":"droid-shell","name":"Droid Shell","description":"Shards must inhabit Droid Bodies to travel and function in the galaxy at large. In this form, they gain the following traits: Shards must undergo Maintenance, as per a Droid. Shards are immune to Poison, Radiation, noncorrosive Atmospheric Hazards, and Vacuum. They can regain Hit Points only through the Repair Droid application of the Mechanics skill. They do not benefit from Natural Healing, unless they have the Force Repair Talent. Shards are considered cybernetic creatures for the purposes of Ion Damage. Shards can make use of Droid systems and accessories, subject to some limitations. Shards can have the following Droid Systems, with a Cost Modifier of x1: Appendages Droid Armor Communications Systems Compartment Space Sensor Systems Translator Units"}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1619},"tags":["droid","medium","droid-shell","droid-builder","cybernetic"],"variants":[],"droidBuilder":{"required":true,"mode":"species-droid-shell","label":"Shard Droid Shell","retainsConstitution":true,"noConstitution":false,"speciesActsAsDroid":true,"fixedSize":"Medium","defaultSize":"medium","allowedCategories":["locomotion","appendage","armor","communications","compartment","sensors","translators"],"allowedAccessorySubcategories":["armor","communications","sensors","translators","miscellaneous"],"allowedAccessoryIds":["plasteel-shell","quadanium-shell","durasteel-shell","quadanium-plating","durasteel-plating","duravlex-shell","laminanium-plating","internal-comlink","vocabulator","improved-sensor-package","darkvision","sensor-booster","basic-translator","advanced-translator","universal-translator","manipulator-arm"],"notes":"Shard characters must inhabit a droid body. They retain Constitution, undergo droid maintenance, are treated as cybernetic creatures for ion damage, and may use droid systems/accessories subject to Shard shell limits."},"speciesActsAsDroid":true,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-shistavanen","name":"Shistavanen","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Shistavanen.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Survival"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Conditional Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision","Natural Weapons","Quick Reflexes"],"languages":["Shistavanen"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"More commonly known to the galactic populace by the nickname Wolfmen, the Shistavanen are an isolationist Species that originates in the Uvena System. Having evolved from predators, Shistavanen excel at hunting and can track prey through crowded urban streets and across desolate plains with equal ease. Although the vast majority of Shistavanen prefer to remain within their home system, a growing minority choose to travel the galaxy's Hyperlanes. Even during the height of the First Galactic Empire's discrimination against non-Humans, Imperial Intelligence made frequent use of those Shistavanen it could recruit; other Shistavanen joined The Rebel Alliance.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Shistavanen","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Survival is always a Class Skill for a Shistavanen."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Shistavanen Trained in Perception gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Shistavanen ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Shistavanen has Natural Weapons, in the form of sharp claws. When a Shistavanen makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. A Shistavanen is always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"quick-reflexes","name":"Quick Reflexes","description":"A Shistavanen may choose to reroll any Initiative check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Shistavanen receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Charisma. Shistavanen are lithe and agile, but their gruff demeanor isolates them from other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Shistavanen"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Conditional Bonus Feat","Low-Light Vision","Natural Weapons","Quick Reflexes"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Survival is always a Class Skill for a Shistavanen."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Shistavanen Trained in Perception gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Shistavanen ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Shistavanen has Natural Weapons, in the form of sharp claws. When a Shistavanen makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. A Shistavanen is always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"quick-reflexes","name":"Quick Reflexes","description":"A Shistavanen may choose to reroll any Initiative check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2335},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-sith-pureblood","name":"Sith (Pureblood)","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Sith (Pureblood).jpg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Persuasion"],"special":[],"languages":["Sith","Basic"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"","tags":[],"visionTraits":["Darkvision"],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Sith (Pureblood)","suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-skakoan","name":"Skakoan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Skakoan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Feat","Conditional Bonus Feat","Mechanical Savant","Special Equipment"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Skakoans receive the Armor Proficiency (Light) feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Skakoans with Mechanics as a Trained Skill gain Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"mechanical-savant","name":"Mechanical Savant","description":"Once per encounter, a Skakoan can make a Standard Action Mechanics or Use Computer check as a Swift Action."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Skakoans suffer limitations outside their native atmosphere. Without a Pressure Suit, a Skakoan takes 1d6 points of damage each round and begins to Suffocate. Skakoan characters begin play with a Light Pressure Suit at no cost."}],"languages":["Skakoverbal","Skakoform","Basic"],"description":"Skakoans are a technologically advanced Species that specializes in microelectronics, Starship engineering, and cutting-edge manufacturing techniques. During the time of the Republic, Skakoans were among the most influential Species in the Techno Union, a galaxy-spanning consortium of megacorporations with representation in the Galactic Senate. Despite the misgivings of other high-ranking members of the Techno Union, Skakoan foreman Wat Tambor pledged to support the Separatists under Count Dooku. The Senate responded by expelling their Techno Union representatives. This contributed to the Skakoan homeworld breaking away from the Republic and joining the Separatist Movement.","canonicalName":"Skakoan","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Skakoans receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Skakoans lack agility but have a rigidly logical, almost computerlike mind.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Skakoverbal","Skakoform","Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Conditional Bonus Feat","Mechanical Savant","Special Equipment"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Skakoans receive the Armor Proficiency (Light) feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Skakoans with Mechanics as a Trained Skill gain Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"mechanical-savant","name":"Mechanical Savant","description":"Once per encounter, a Skakoan can make a Standard Action Mechanics or Use Computer check as a Swift Action."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Skakoans suffer limitations outside their native atmosphere. Without a Pressure Suit, a Skakoan takes 1d6 points of damage each round and begins to Suffocate. Skakoan characters begin play with a Light Pressure Suit at no cost."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2619},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-sluissi","name":"Sluissi","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Sluissi.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Careful Worker","Conditional Bonus Feat","Serpentine"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"careful-worker","name":"Careful Worker","description":"A Sluissi who takes twice the normal amount of time required to use the Mechanics skill gains a +10 circumstance bonus to the Mechanics check."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Sluissi quickly learn to tinker with technology. A Sluissi who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains the Tech Specialist Feat as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"serpentine","name":"Serpentine","description":"By coiling their serpentine bodies, Sluissi are able to make long jumps without getting a running start. Sluissi are always considered to have a Running Start for Jump checks. They also gain a +5 stability bonus when making Grapple checks against the Trip feat."}],"languages":["Basic","Sluiussese"],"description":"Sluissi Technicians are renowned for Starship construction and modification. Although Sluissi methods are slower than others, customers are willing to wait to own the best Starship technology available. The Sluissi consider Starship construction to be an art form. So respected are Sluissi shipyards that the slow pace of construction is tolerated by even the Empire, albeit impatiently.","canonicalName":"Sluissi","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Sluissi receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Sluissi are slow and methodical, choosing to take their time with their work.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Sluiussese"],"special":["Careful Worker","Conditional Bonus Feat","Serpentine"],"traits":[{"id":"careful-worker","name":"Careful Worker","description":"A Sluissi who takes twice the normal amount of time required to use the Mechanics skill gains a +10 circumstance bonus to the Mechanics check."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Sluissi quickly learn to tinker with technology. A Sluissi who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains the Tech Specialist Feat as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"serpentine","name":"Serpentine","description":"By coiling their serpentine bodies, Sluissi are able to make long jumps without getting a running start. Sluissi are always considered to have a Running Start for Jump checks. They also gain a +5 stability bonus when making Grapple checks against the Trip feat."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2354},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-snivvian","name":"Snivvian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Snivvian.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Negotiation"],"special":["Cold Resistance","Observant"],"languages":["Snivvian"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Historically, Snivvians have withstood numerous hardships that they channel into their impressive artistic works. After gaining the ability to travel between the stars, the Snivvians attracted the brutal attention of The Thalassian Slavers. Snivvian culture was nearly destroyed before the Republic discovered the practice and stepped in to protect the Snivvians. This protection has been reduced during eras of warfare, but combined Republic and Snivvian forces remain sufficient to hold off lesser threats. During The Old Republic Era, the Snivvians were still rebuilding the damage done to their society by the slavers and other threats.","tags":["small"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Snivvian","movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"cold-resistance","name":"Cold Resistance","description":"The Snivvians' thick skin provides protection from extreme cold. Snivvians gain a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense to resist Extreme Cold."},{"id":"observant","name":"Observant","description":"Snivvians are highly aware of their surroundings, giving them an advantage when dealing with others. Once per encounter, a Snivvian can use their Perception skill modifier in place of their Deception or Persuasion skill modifier."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Snivvians receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom. Snivvians tend to be thoughtful and observant of their surroundings.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Snivvian"],"special":["Cold Resistance","Observant"],"traits":[{"id":"cold-resistance","name":"Cold Resistance","description":"The Snivvians' thick skin provides protection from extreme cold. Snivvians gain a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense to resist Extreme Cold."},{"id":"observant","name":"Observant","description":"Snivvians are highly aware of their surroundings, giving them an advantage when dealing with others. Once per encounter, a Snivvian can use their Perception skill modifier in place of their Deception or Persuasion skill modifier."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":743},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-sorcerer-of-rhand","name":"Sorcerer of Rhand","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Sorcerer of Rhand.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Int, +2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":4,"wis":2,"cha":0},"special":["Beastly Traits","Bonus Feat","Dark-Infused","Repulsive Appearance"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"beastly-traits","name":"Beastly Traits","description":"A Sorcerer gains two Beastly Traits unique to his or her relationship with The Dark Side. Create these qualities (with approval from your Gamemaster), or select two using the Creature Generator."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Sorcerers of Rhand receive the Force Sensitivity feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"dark-infused","name":"Dark-Infused","description":"Sorcerers of Rhand gain the Force Training feat as a bonus Feat, but half of the Force Powers selected with this bonus Feat must have the [Dark Side] descriptor, and none can have the [Light Side] descriptor."},{"id":"repulsive-appearance","name":"Repulsive Appearance","description":"The Sorcerers of Rhand's repulsive physical appearances allow them to reroll Persuasion checks to Intimidate, and may keep the better result. They also gain a +5 bonus to their Will Defense when others attempt to use the Persuasion skill against them."}],"languages":["Basic"],"description":"The Sorcerers of Rhand live deep in The Unknown Regions, hidden by the red flow of the Perann Nebula from any disciples of The Dark who wish to tap their knowledge. Their reclusiveness is a blessing, for if the Sorcerers of Rhand were to unleash the full entropic power of what they call The Dark, the entire galaxy might come to ruin. The Sorcerers or Rhand are realists. They understand that the power of destruction, coupled with time, has more ability to change the universe than any effort of creation. They devote their efforts to understanding its purpose and ultimately divining a way to become agents of The Dark.","canonicalName":"Sorcerer of Rhand","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Int, +2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":4,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Sorcerers of Rhand receive a +4 bonus to their Intelligence, as well as a +2 bonus to their Wisdom. But they suffer -2 penalties to their Strength, Dexterity, and Charisma. Sorcerers lose their physical attributes in exchange for increased mental abilities.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Beastly Traits","Bonus Feat","Dark-Infused","Repulsive Appearance"],"traits":[{"id":"beastly-traits","name":"Beastly Traits","description":"A Sorcerer gains two Beastly Traits unique to his or her relationship with The Dark Side. Create these qualities (with approval from your Gamemaster), or select two using the Creature Generator."},{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Sorcerers of Rhand receive the Force Sensitivity feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"dark-infused","name":"Dark-Infused","description":"Sorcerers of Rhand gain the Force Training feat as a bonus Feat, but half of the Force Powers selected with this bonus Feat must have the [Dark Side] descriptor, and none can have the [Light Side] descriptor."},{"id":"repulsive-appearance","name":"Repulsive Appearance","description":"The Sorcerers of Rhand's repulsive physical appearances allow them to reroll Persuasion checks to Intimidate, and may keep the better result. They also gain a +5 bonus to their Will Defense when others attempt to use the Persuasion skill against them."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2373},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-squib","name":"Squib","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Squib.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Natural Diplomat","Tech Savvy","Weapon Familiarity"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"natural-diplomat","name":"Natural Diplomat","description":"A Squib gains a +5 Species bonus to Persuasion checks made to Haggle. Additionally, Persuasion is always a Class Skill for Squibs."},{"id":"tech-savvy","name":"Tech Savvy","description":"A Squib can reroll any Knowledge (Technology) check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. Additionally, a Squib is not limited to Common Knowledge when making an Untrained Knowledge (Technology) check."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Squibs treat the Squib Tensor Rifle as a Rifle, rather than as an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"languages":["Basic","Squibbian"],"description":"Squibs are known throughout the galaxy for their talents at collecting, trading, and haggling. The uneven distribution of natural resources on their homeworld led early Squibs to compulsively collect and stockpile goods, and to develop a maddeningly complex system of barter. But in spite of their penchant for needless complexities when negotiating, Squibs are surprisingly honest in their dealings, following a specific set of rules whenever they bargain with someone. For Squibs, the process of haggling is more important than the end result.","canonicalName":"Squib","canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Squibs receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Squibs are flexible and light on their feet, but generally lack physical strength.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Squibbian"],"special":["Natural Diplomat","Tech Savvy","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"natural-diplomat","name":"Natural Diplomat","description":"A Squib gains a +5 Species bonus to Persuasion checks made to Haggle. Additionally, Persuasion is always a Class Skill for Squibs."},{"id":"tech-savvy","name":"Tech Savvy","description":"A Squib can reroll any Knowledge (Technology) check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. Additionally, a Squib is not limited to Common Knowledge when making an Untrained Knowledge (Technology) check."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Squibs treat the Squib Tensor Rifle as a Rifle, rather than as an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2388},"tags":["small"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ssi-ruuk","name":"Ssi-Ruuk","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ssi-Ruuk.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Force Blind","Natural Armor","Silver Tongued","The Tofs come from the darkest and most obscure portion of The Unknown Regions"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ssi-Ruuk Trained in the Persuasion skill gain Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"force-blind","name":"Force Blind","description":"Ssi-Ruuk cannot take the Force Sensitivity feat, cannot make Use the Force checks, and never gain Force Points. They can still increase their Dark Side Score and are still affected by Force Powers, Force Talents, and the Use the Force skill as normal."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"The naturally tough scales of the Ssi-Ruuk grant them a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"silver-tongued","name":"Silver Tongued","description":"Ssi-Ruuk use their keen sense of smell to detect changes in a target's emotional state. A Ssi-Ruuk may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"the-tofs-come-from-the-darkest-and-most-obscure-portion-of-the-unknown-regions","name":"The Tofs come from the darkest and most obscure portion of The Unknown Regions","description":"the peripheral halo. Far removed from The Chiss Ascendancy, The Vagaari Empire, and The Ssi-Ruuvi Imperium in the galactic disk, the Tofs and others in the satellite galaxy they call Firefist (and named \"Companion Besh\" by Republic cartographers) have little understanding of, or sympathy for, traditional galactic power plays- with the exception of their aborted invasion shortly after the Battle of Endor. Tof-0 Their culture is intentionally anachronistic. Violently opposed to streamlined functionality, the Tofs have instead embraced elaborate dress and foppish ritual. Their interstellar vessels resemble traditional sailing ships and sport curved hulls and energy- radiating sails. Their royals wear tailored greatcoats and powdered wigs. Their soldiers carry cutlasses and cudgels and collect battle scars. Attire becomes more ornate as Tofs climb the military hierarchies that make up their society. Low-ranking deckhands wear simple cloth shirts, leather vests, and head-scarves. Ship's captains are outfitted with heavy buccaneer's boots, sparkling rings on nearly every finger, and a waist sash that holds a Blaster Pistol and a carved Club. Tofs do not bathe, covering their stink with perfumed bows on their tunics and boots. Males dominate Tof society. Females are seldom seen and generally kept on-planet where they are visited only when Tof vessels return to port. During long star voyages, Tof males exhibit reckless lust for humanoid females and often make unwanted moves on attractive targets (Or prove vulnerable to feminine flattery)."}],"languages":["Ssi-Ruuvi"],"description":"The Ssi-Ruuk are warm-blooded reptilian humanoids who command a stellar empire in The Unknown Regions, well beyond the edges of explored space. Before The Rebellion Era, the existence of the Ssi-Ruuk was unknown to the general galactic population. An escalating war with the competing empire of the Chiss forced the Ssi-Ruuk to look toward the galactic Core for \"Recruits\" for their space fleet. The Ssi-Ruuvi forces consisted mostly of self-propelled Battle Droids powered by the life energies and enslaved consciousness of captured humanoids subjected to a process \"Entechment.\" The Ssi-Ruuk attacked and subjected the citizens of a number of isolated Outer Rim settlements before clashing directly with the Empire's fleet. Rather than bringing the full might of the Imperial Navy to bear on the Ssi-Ruuk invaders, the Emperor negotiated to a secret treaty with them.","canonicalName":"Ssi-Ruuk","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Ssi-Ruuk receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Ssi-Ruuk are physically powerful but prone to panic and delay when faced with mortal danger, especially in space or on worlds that have not been consecrated.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Ssi-Ruuvi"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Force Blind","Natural Armor","Silver Tongued","The Tofs come from the darkest and most obscure portion of The Unknown Regions"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ssi-Ruuk Trained in the Persuasion skill gain Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"force-blind","name":"Force Blind","description":"Ssi-Ruuk cannot take the Force Sensitivity feat, cannot make Use the Force checks, and never gain Force Points. They can still increase their Dark Side Score and are still affected by Force Powers, Force Talents, and the Use the Force skill as normal."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"The naturally tough scales of the Ssi-Ruuk grant them a +2 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"silver-tongued","name":"Silver Tongued","description":"Ssi-Ruuk use their keen sense of smell to detect changes in a target's emotional state. A Ssi-Ruuk may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, keeping the better of the two results."},{"id":"the-tofs-come-from-the-darkest-and-most-obscure-portion-of-the-unknown-regions","name":"The Tofs come from the darkest and most obscure portion of The Unknown Regions","description":"the peripheral halo. Far removed from The Chiss Ascendancy, The Vagaari Empire, and The Ssi-Ruuvi Imperium in the galactic disk, the Tofs and others in the satellite galaxy they call Firefist (and named \"Companion Besh\" by Republic cartographers) have little understanding of, or sympathy for, traditional galactic power plays- with the exception of their aborted invasion shortly after the Battle of Endor. Tof-0 Their culture is intentionally anachronistic. Violently opposed to streamlined functionality, the Tofs have instead embraced elaborate dress and foppish ritual. Their interstellar vessels resemble traditional sailing ships and sport curved hulls and energy- radiating sails. Their royals wear tailored greatcoats and powdered wigs. Their soldiers carry cutlasses and cudgels and collect battle scars. Attire becomes more ornate as Tofs climb the military hierarchies that make up their society. Low-ranking deckhands wear simple cloth shirts, leather vests, and head-scarves. Ship's captains are outfitted with heavy buccaneer's boots, sparkling rings on nearly every finger, and a waist sash that holds a Blaster Pistol and a carved Club. Tofs do not bathe, covering their stink with perfumed bows on their tunics and boots. Males dominate Tof society. Females are seldom seen and generally kept on-planet where they are visited only when Tof vessels return to port. During long star voyages, Tof males exhibit reckless lust for humanoid females and often make unwanted moves on attractive targets (Or prove vulnerable to feminine flattery)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2415},"tags":["force","medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":12900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-stereb","name":"Stereb","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Stereb.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Primitive","Subterranean","Tough"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Stereb are very adept when working with stone. A Stereb who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat. However, this bonus applies only when the Stereb character is working with stone."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Stereb ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Stereb do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"subterranean","name":"Subterranean","description":"Stereb are adapted to a subterranean life and can Take 10 on Survival checks when in an underground environment, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"tough","name":"Tough","description":"Like the stone they work with, Stereb are physically hardened, gaining a +5 Species bonus to their Damage Threshold and a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense."}],"languages":["Stereb"],"description":"Jokingly called \"Hairless Wookiees\" by the few who have seen them, Stereb have been found on a number of worlds with rocky crusts. Not technologically adept, the Stereb live in harmony with the surfaces of a planet, working elaborate stone passages underground in the belief that they're part of the world's circulatory system.","canonicalName":"Stereb","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Stereb receive a +4 bonus to their Strength and a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to their Dexterity, Intelligence, and Charisma. Stereb are strong and hardy. They are not aggressive, and they might take time to reach a decision, but once they choose a course of action, they are deliberate and steadfast.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Stereb"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Primitive","Subterranean","Tough"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Stereb are very adept when working with stone. A Stereb who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat. However, this bonus applies only when the Stereb character is working with stone."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Stereb ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Stereb do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles) as starting Feats at first level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"subterranean","name":"Subterranean","description":"Stereb are adapted to a subterranean life and can Take 10 on Survival checks when in an underground environment, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"tough","name":"Tough","description":"Like the stone they work with, Stereb are physically hardened, gaining a +5 Species bonus to their Damage Threshold and a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2635},"tags":["medium","primitive"],"variants":[],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-sullustan","name":"Sullustan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Sullustan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative","+2 Perception"],"special":["Darkvision","Expert Climber","Heightened Awareness"],"languages":["Basic","Sullustese"],"source":"Core","description":"To survive the natural perils of their harsh, volcanic homeworld, the Sullustans evolved in the planet's numerous caves. They prefer to dwell underground, constructing highly advanced cities of such great beauty that wealthy sightseers come from all over the galaxy to visit them. Living underground helped the Sullustans to develop acute senses, and they are renowned for their navigational and piloting skills. This friendly, gregarious species enjoys interacting with unique, unusual, and interesting beings. When Old Republic scouts first visited their homeworld, the Sullustans quickly embraced galactic civilization.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Sullustan","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Sullustans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Sullustans are adept at climbing in their underground homes. A Sullustan may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Sullustan may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Sullustans receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Sullustans are quick, agile, and good with ranged weapons, but they are not as hardy as other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Sullustese"],"special":["Darkvision","Expert Climber","Heightened Awareness"],"traits":[{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Sullustans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Sullustans are adept at climbing in their underground homes. A Sullustan may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Sullustan may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":328},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-talz","name":"Talz","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Talz.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival","+2 Perception"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Natural Weapons"],"languages":["Talz"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"The Empire subjugates the Talz very early in The Dark Times. The New Order wasted no time in secretly enslaving the race and forcing them to mine the mineral wealth of Alzoc III. The Talz do not understand the motives of their new masters, but they can do little but comply. Those few Talz who escape must hide themselves along the fringes of the galaxy, lest the Imperials send them back to their homeworld. During this time, almost no one in the galaxy knows that the Talz even exist.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Talz","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Talz learn how to use technology very quickly. A Talz who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Talz ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Talz has Natural Weapons, in the form of sharp claws. When a Talz makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Talz are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Talz receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Intelligence. Winters of Alzoc III make the Talz strong and resilient, but they have had little chance to learn and develop intellectually.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Talz"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Natural Weapons"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Talz learn how to use technology very quickly. A Talz who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Talz ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Talz has Natural Weapons, in the form of sharp claws. When a Talz makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Talz are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":897},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-taung","name":"Taung","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Taung.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Armor Training","Superior Defenses","Warrior Culture"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"armor-training","name":"Armor Training","description":"Taung characters increase the Maximum Dexterity bonus from worn Armor by +1."},{"id":"superior-defenses","name":"Superior Defenses","description":"Because they constantly test themselves both physically and mentally in combat well before reaching adulthood, Taung gain a +1 Species bonus to all their Defenses."},{"id":"warrior-culture","name":"Warrior Culture","description":"Taung can reroll any Knowledge (Tactics) check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"languages":["Basic","Mando'a"],"description":"The Taung are warriors first and foremost, having battled the native Human nations for control of Coruscant before being driven off and forced to flee to the Outer Rim world of Roon, where they remain for millennia until the legendary Mandalore the First leads them to conquer another world. Taung rename both the world and themselves in his honor, becoming The Mandalorians. With a clan-based nomadic culture, Taung view battle and war as both a source of personal honor and a way to show pride in their community. Veterans of successful battles are held in high regard, to such an extent that they are the de facto leaders of their communities. Only the leader of all The Mandalorians, known simply as Mandalore, holds greater sway with the clans.","canonicalName":"Taung","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Taung receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Taung are physically resilient, able to endure when others would give up.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Mando'a"],"special":["Armor Training","Superior Defenses","Warrior Culture"],"traits":[{"id":"armor-training","name":"Armor Training","description":"Taung characters increase the Maximum Dexterity bonus from worn Armor by +1."},{"id":"superior-defenses","name":"Superior Defenses","description":"Because they constantly test themselves both physically and mentally in combat well before reaching adulthood, Taung gain a +1 Species bonus to all their Defenses."},{"id":"warrior-culture","name":"Warrior Culture","description":"Taung can reroll any Knowledge (Tactics) check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1713},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-thakwaash","name":"Thakwaash","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Thakwaash.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Irrepressible Mind","Natural Armor"],"languages":["Thakwaashi"],"source":"Scum & Villainy","description":"Possessed of great strength, these large bipeds are best known for their uniquely non-Human mindset. A Thakwaash has multiple separate personalities, each specializing in a certain function or area of expertise. Interacting with Thakwaash can be difficult for other Species, particularly for Humans, who view such behavior among their own kind as a mental disorder. The maximum number of personalities that a single Thakwaash can develop is unknown, as is the means by which such personalities form in the first place. No reliable reports of Thakwaash exist prior to the Empire's defeat at The Forest Moon of Endor.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Thakwaash","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"irrepressible-mind","name":"Irrepressible Mind","description":"Once per encounter, as a Free Action at the start of his or her turn, a Thakwaash can negate or remove any Mind-Affecting effects."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Thakwaash gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Dex, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Thakwaash receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Dexterity and Charisma. Thakwaash have large, powerful builds, but their multiple personalities make relations with other Species difficult.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Thakwaashi"],"special":["Irrepressible Mind","Natural Armor"],"traits":[{"id":"irrepressible-mind","name":"Irrepressible Mind","description":"Once per encounter, as a Free Action at the start of his or her turn, a Thakwaash can negate or remove any Mind-Affecting effects."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Thakwaash gain a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1728},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-theelin","name":"Theelin","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Theelin.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Colorful Appearance"],"languages":["Theelin","Basic"],"source":"Legacy","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Theelin","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-tof","name":"Tof","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Tof.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Cha, -2 Dex, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"special":["Bonus Feat","Conditional Bonus Feat","Fearless"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Tofs are aggressive and chaotic combatants, firing and swinging wildly. A Tof can take either Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Tof gains Mighty Swing as a bonus Feat at 1st level, provided he or she meets the prerequisites of the feat (minimum Strength of 13)."},{"id":"fearless","name":"Fearless","description":"Tofs are fearless on the battlefield. Tofs gain a +5 Species bonus to their Will Defense to resist Fear effects, as well as against the Intimidate application of the Persuasion skill."}],"languages":["Tof"],"description":"The Tofs come from the darkest and most obscure portion of The Unknown Regions: the peripheral halo. Far removed from The Chiss Ascendancy, The Vagaari Empire, and The Ssi-Ruuvi Imperium in the galactic disk, the Tofs and others in the satellite galaxy they call Firefist (and named \"Companion Besh\" by Republic cartographers) have little understanding of, or sympathy for, traditional galactic power plays- with the exception of their aborted invasion shortly after the Battle of Endor. Tof-0 Their culture is intentionally anachronistic. Violently opposed to streamlined functionality, the Tofs have instead embraced elaborate dress and foppish ritual. Their interstellar vessels resemble traditional sailing ships and sport curved hulls and energy- radiating sails.","canonicalName":"Tof","canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, +2 Cha, -2 Dex, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Tofs receive a +2 bonus to their Strength and Charisma, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Dexterity and Wisdom. Tofs are big, strong, and boisterous, but they often make poor choices in the name of sport and adventure.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Tof"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Conditional Bonus Feat","Fearless"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Tofs are aggressive and chaotic combatants, firing and swinging wildly. A Tof can take either Rapid Shot or Rapid Strike at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Tof gains Mighty Swing as a bonus Feat at 1st level, provided he or she meets the prerequisites of the feat (minimum Strength of 13)."},{"id":"fearless","name":"Fearless","description":"Tofs are fearless on the battlefield. Tofs gain a +5 Species bonus to their Will Defense to resist Fear effects, as well as against the Intimidate application of the Persuasion skill."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2437},"tags":["large"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-togorian","name":"Togorian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Togorian.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Int, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Feline Reflexes","Low-Light Vision","Physically Intimidating"],"languages":["Basic","Togorian"],"source":"Threats","description":"Togorians in a group are led by the largest, most aggressive, and most ruthless individual among them. They have little honor, but prefer fights against other Togorians to be face-to-face combat. Males and females have little contact with each other. The males are nomadic, often using domesticated Mosgoth as mounts. The females live in the cities, tending animals and seeing to the Togorians' limited technological pursuits.","tags":["large"],"visionTraits":["Low-Light Vision"],"naturalWeapons":[{"name":"Claws","damage":"1d4","type":"slashing"}],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Togorian","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"feline-reflexes","name":"Feline Reflexes","description":"Togorians gain a +1 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Togorians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"physically-intimidating","name":"Physically Intimidating","description":"When using the Persuasion skill to Intimidate, Togorians use their Strength bonus instead of their Charisma bonus when determining the check modifier."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Togorians receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Wisdom. Togorians are strong and tough, but not terribly bright or learned.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Togorian"],"special":["Feline Reflexes","Low-Light Vision","Physically Intimidating"],"traits":[{"id":"feline-reflexes","name":"Feline Reflexes","description":"Togorians gain a +1 Species bonus to their Reflex Defense."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Togorians ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"physically-intimidating","name":"Physically Intimidating","description":"When using the Persuasion skill to Intimidate, Togorians use their Strength bonus instead of their Charisma bonus when determining the check modifier."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":914},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-togruta","name":"Togruta","type":"species","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Stealth"],"special":["Pack Hunter","Sneaky","Spatial Awareness"],"languages":["Basic","Togruti"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Togrutas are natives of the planet Shili, a world of dense forests, wild scublands, and ever-growing urban areas. The most striking features of Togruta are their brightly colored horns, head, head-tails, and skin. These patterns serve as a sort of camouflage that helps them stalk prey through the red and white, meter-tall turu-grass of the scrublands. Togrutas are natural pack hunters and work effectively in large groups. Individualism is generally discouraged, but despite this fact, most Togruta leaders gain power and prestige through expressions of individuality.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Echolocation: +2 to Perception in enclosed spaces"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Togruta","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"pack-hunter","name":"Pack Hunter","description":"Togrutas deal an additional 2 points of damage on melee attacks against opponents they Flank."},{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"A Togruta can choose to reroll any Stealth check to Sneak, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"spatial-awareness","name":"Spatial Awareness","description":"Togrutas can sense their surroundings using passive echolocation. Togrutas ignore all Cover and Concealment when making Perception checks to Notice Targets within 10 squares."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Togrutas receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Togrutas are quick on the hunt, but more delicate than some Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Togruti"],"special":["Pack Hunter","Sneaky","Spatial Awareness"],"traits":[{"id":"pack-hunter","name":"Pack Hunter","description":"Togrutas deal an additional 2 points of damage on melee attacks against opponents they Flank."},{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"A Togruta can choose to reroll any Stealth check to Sneak, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"spatial-awareness","name":"Spatial Awareness","description":"Togrutas can sense their surroundings using passive echolocation. Togrutas ignore all Cover and Concealment when making Perception checks to Notice Targets within 10 squares."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":931},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-toydarian","name":"Toydarian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Toydarian.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","skillBonuses":["+2 Will","+2 Deception"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Flight","Force Resistance"],"languages":["Huttese","Toydarian"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Toydarians are small, winged aliens from the planet Toydaria. They are known as shrewd merchants and able con artists, even though many lead reputable lives. Because their homeworld is located within Hutt Space, many Toydarians who leave Toydaria find themselves either unemployed or indentured to Hutt criminal interests. Toydarians easily resist Mind-Affecting Force Powers and are even more resilient to such abilities than their Hutt overlords. Toydarian1 Toydarians have an unsavory reputation, but not all Toydarians are criminals.","tags":["force","small"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Toydarian","movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":6,"climb":null,"hover":6,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"flySpeed":6,"hoverSpeed":6,"abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Toydarians that have Deception as a Trained Skill gain the Skill Focus (Deception) feat as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","description":"Toydarians are capable of flight, but cannot do so if they are carrying a Heavy Load."},{"id":"force-resistance","name":"Force Resistance","description":"Toydarians receive a +5 bonus to their Will Defense against any use of the Use the Force skill."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":6,"climb":null,"hover":6,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, -2 Str","abilityMods":{"str":-2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Toydarians receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Strength. Toydarians are weaker than Humans, but they are shrewd and accustomed to moving quickly to seal the deal.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Huttese","Toydarian"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Flight","Force Resistance"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Toydarians that have Deception as a Trained Skill gain the Skill Focus (Deception) feat as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","description":"Toydarians are capable of flight, but cannot do so if they are carrying a Heavy Load."},{"id":"force-resistance","name":"Force Resistance","description":"Toydarians receive a +5 bonus to their Will Defense against any use of the Use the Force skill."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1139},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":13900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-trandoshan","name":"Trandoshan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Trandoshan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Perception","+2 Survival"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Limb Regeneration","Natural Armor"],"languages":["Basic","Dosh"],"source":"Core","description":"The reptilian Trandoshans are known for their great strength, and warlike natures. Many of these beings dedicate themselves to martial training, and some follow the path of the hunter on their native world. A few have even become renowned (or infamous) bounty hunters in galactic society. Trandoshans have a long-standing enmity with Wookiees, and the two Species have fought often over the centuries. Trandoshans (who refer to themselves as \"T'doshok\") have supersensitive eyes that can see into the infrared range.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[{"name":"Claws","damage":"1d4","type":"slashing"}],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":1,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":["Regeneration: Heal additional HP when resting"]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Trandoshan","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Rugged and resilient, Trandoshans receive the Toughness feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Trandoshans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"limb-regeneration","name":"Limb Regeneration","description":"A Trandoshan regrows a lost limb in 1d10 days. At the end of that time, all Persistent Conditions associated with the loss of the limb are removed."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Trandoshans have thick scales that provide a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Trandoshans receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Trandoshans are powerful but lack agility.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Dosh"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Limb Regeneration","Natural Armor"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Rugged and resilient, Trandoshans receive the Toughness feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Trandoshans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"limb-regeneration","name":"Limb Regeneration","description":"A Trandoshan regrows a lost limb in 1d10 days. At the end of that time, all Persistent Conditions associated with the loss of the limb are removed."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Trandoshans have thick scales that provide a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":354},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-trianii","name":"Trianii","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Trianii.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"special":["Heightened Agility","Natural Weapons","Prehensile Tail"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"heightened-agility","name":"Heightened Agility","description":"A Trianii can reroll any Acrobatics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Trianii's sharp claws serve as Natural Weapons. When a Trianii makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Trianii are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"prehensile-tail","name":"Prehensile Tail","description":"A Trianii's long, flexible tail is dexterous and strong. A Trianii's tail can effectively hold (but not wield) a Small or smaller item. When holding a Medium or larger item with his or her tail, a Trianii is encumbered and is considered to be carrying a Heavy Load."}],"languages":["Trianii"],"description":"The Trianii are a feline race of intrepid explorers, but unlike other technologically advanced Species of the galaxy, they express no interest in becoming a part of the greater galactic community. The Trianii use impressive displays of force to drive away interlopers so that they are left alone to explore their region of the galaxy. Their homeworld is located on the edge of the region of space controlled by The Corporate Sector Authority. An attempt by the CSA to expand its area of control into Trianii territories is met with a display of Trianii determination as the Species expel the invaders, proving that the ships and weapons of The Trianii Rangers are as formidable as those of other galactic forces. Trianii society is a matriarchy- partly because females of the Species are taller and slightly stronger than the males- ruled by tribunals of females known as yu'nar.","canonicalName":"Trianii","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Trianii receive a +2 bonus to their Wisdom. Trianii have excellent vision and, because of their curious nature, are very aware of their surroundings.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Trianii"],"special":["Heightened Agility","Natural Weapons","Prehensile Tail"],"traits":[{"id":"heightened-agility","name":"Heightened Agility","description":"A Trianii can reroll any Acrobatics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Trianii's sharp claws serve as Natural Weapons. When a Trianii makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. Trianii are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"prehensile-tail","name":"Prehensile Tail","description":"A Trianii's long, flexible tail is dexterous and strong. A Trianii's tail can effectively hold (but not wield) a Small or smaller item. When holding a Medium or larger item with his or her tail, a Trianii is encumbered and is considered to be carrying a Heavy Load."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1746},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-tusken-raider","name":"Tusken Raider","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Tusken Raider.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Sneaky","Survival Instinct"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"A Tusken Raider can choose to reroll any Stealth check to sneak, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"A Tusken Raider may choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"languages":["Tusken"],"description":"Although technologically primitive by galactic standards, Tusken Raiders make good use of whatever technological items they can salvage from slain offworlders or Jawa. Tusken Raiders use Banthas, large herd animals native to Tatooine, as mounts during scouting missions and hunting expeditions. Some Tusken villages also use domesticated Massiffs as watchdogs. Tusken Hunters typically arm themselves with Gaffi Sticks and Slugthrower Rifles.","canonicalName":"Tusken Raider","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Tusken Raiders receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Wisdom. Tusken Raiders are hardy and fit, but are simple and quick to anger.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Tusken"],"special":["Sneaky","Survival Instinct"],"traits":[{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"A Tusken Raider can choose to reroll any Stealth check to sneak, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"A Tusken Raider may choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2660},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-twi-lek","name":"Twi'lek","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Twi'Lek.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion","+2 Deception"],"special":["Deceptive","Great Fortitude","Low-Light Vision"],"languages":["Basic","Ryl"],"source":"Core","description":"From the dry, rocky world of Ryloth, Twi'leks have made a place for themselves along the Galaxy. These tall, thin humanoids include a variety of distinct subraces, but all are instantly recognizable by the tentacular \"Head-Tails\" (called Lekku) that protrude from the backs of their heads. Sly, calculating beings, Twi'leks prefer to avoid trouble and stick to the shadows until an opportunity to act without undue danger to themselves presents itself. Their entrepreneurial spirit frequently leads them to positions of influence, and Twi'lek corporate executives and ambassadors are no less common than unscrupulous Twi'lek freighter captains and crime lords.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Lekku Sensory: +2 to Perception for nearby movement detection"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Twi'lek","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"Naturally gifted at manipulation, a Twi'lek may choose to reroll any Deception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Twi'leks gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense. Twi'leks have great health with a natural resistance to toxins and illnesses."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Twi'leks ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Twi'leks receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Twi'leks make convincing diplomats, but are relatively weak-willed.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Ryl"],"special":["Deceptive","Great Fortitude","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"Naturally gifted at manipulation, a Twi'lek may choose to reroll any Deception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"great-fortitude","name":"Great Fortitude","description":"Twi'leks gain a +2 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense. Twi'leks have great health with a natural resistance to toxins and illnesses."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Twi'leks ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":380},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-ubese","name":"Ubese","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Ubese.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Stealth","+2 Survival"],"special":["Aggressive","Conditional Bonus Feat","Survival Instinct","Special Equipment"],"languages":["Basic","Ubese"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Long ago, the Ubese were a peaceful Species, content in the paradise of their garden planets. This changes when they encounter Old Republic scouts who seduce them with the power and might of advanced technology. Obsessed by these wonders, the Ubese devote their resources to the development of these technologies. As they succeed, they became worried about aggression from rival systems, so they develop weapon technology, dipping into dangerous devices banned throughout the galaxy. Fearing these weapons in the hands of a decidedly unstable population, The Old Republic makes a preemptive strike against the Ubese to destroy weapons facilities and halt their aggression.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Ubese","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"aggressive","name":"Aggressive","description":"If an Ubese hits with a Charge attack, the +2 bonus on attack rolls against the target persists for the duration of the encounter."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ubese do not trust other cultures, so they are more suspicious of aliens. An Ubese with Perception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"Ubese are tough and resilient, capable of withstanding the perils of even hostile worlds. An Ubese can reroll Survival checks, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Ubese cannot tolerate the atmospheres of other worlds and must rely on breath masks to survive. Without a breath mask, an Ubese begins to Suffocate. When not on their homeworld, Ubese wear environmental suits to stave of the Hazards found on other planets as well as to hide their appearance. An environmental suit functions as a Combat Jumpsuit that also grants a +2 Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense. The suit also includes a voice modulator to emulate the voice of a male or female or to mask the Ubese's gender. An Ubese environmental suit with a breath mask and voice modulator costs 2000 credits, and a year's supply of breathing filters costs 200 credits (50 credits on Ubese). Ubese characters begin play with these items at no cost."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Ubese receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Ubese have slight build, and they are quick and agile.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Ubese"],"special":["Aggressive","Conditional Bonus Feat","Survival Instinct","Special Equipment"],"traits":[{"id":"aggressive","name":"Aggressive","description":"If an Ubese hits with a Charge attack, the +2 bonus on attack rolls against the target persists for the duration of the encounter."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Ubese do not trust other cultures, so they are more suspicious of aliens. An Ubese with Perception as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Perception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"Ubese are tough and resilient, capable of withstanding the perils of even hostile worlds. An Ubese can reroll Survival checks, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"special-equipment","name":"Special Equipment","description":"Ubese cannot tolerate the atmospheres of other worlds and must rely on breath masks to survive. Without a breath mask, an Ubese begins to Suffocate. When not on their homeworld, Ubese wear environmental suits to stave of the Hazards found on other planets as well as to hide their appearance. An environmental suit functions as a Combat Jumpsuit that also grants a +2 Equipment bonus to Fortitude Defense. The suit also includes a voice modulator to emulate the voice of a male or female or to mask the Ubese's gender. An Ubese environmental suit with a breath mask and voice modulator costs 2000 credits, and a year's supply of breathing filters costs 200 credits (50 credits on Ubese). Ubese characters begin play with these items at no cost."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1157},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-umbaran","name":"Umbaran","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Umbaran.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Wis, -2 Con","skillBonuses":["+2 Deception","+2 Perception"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Sneaky"],"languages":["Basic","Umbarese"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"As Palpatine's New Order becomes increasingly biased toward Humans, Moore vanishes from the Emperor's side and moves into more shadowy roles within his government. From deep within the intelligence apparatus, she and other Umbarans lead efforts to root out anyone who is not unquestionably loyal to Emperor Palpatine, and they answer only to the Emperor. They are so effective that even Emperor Palpatine's most dedicated followers grow to fear them, something that strengthens the antialien sentiment among many of the Emperor's closest advisers. The Umbarans are particularly disliked by officers of Imperial Intelligence, who resent the fact that they are subject to Umbaran scrutiny- a resentment that grows every time the Umbarans unmask a Rebel double agent in their ranks. After the death of Emperor Palpatine and the collapse of his government, the Umbarans find themselves under threat from the Rebels they had hunted and the New Order supporters they had intimidated.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":["Light Sensitivity: –1 to attacks in bright light"],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Umbaran","variants":[{"id":"umbaran-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Low-Light Vision","Conditional Bonus Feat","Soothing Voice","Light Sensitivity"],"languages":["Basic","Umbarese"],"description":"Alternate Umbaran trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Umbarans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"An Umbaran with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"soothing-voice","name":"Soothing Voice","description":"An Umbaran may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"light-sensitivity","name":"Light Sensitivity","description":"An Umbaran exposed to bright light (such as sunlight) is Blinded for 1 round."}]}],"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Umbarans are born observers, and they enjoy watching events from hidden vantage points. An Umbaran with Gather Information as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Gather Information) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Umbarans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"An Umbaran can choose to reroll any Stealth check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, +2 Wis, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Umbarans receive a +2 bonus to both their Dexterity and Wisdom, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Umbarans are not as sturdy as many Species, but they are naturally stealthy and observant.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Umbarese"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Darkvision","Sneaky"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Umbarans are born observers, and they enjoy watching events from hidden vantage points. An Umbaran with Gather Information as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Gather Information) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","description":"Umbarans ignore Concealment (including Total Concealment) from darkness. However, they cannot perceive colors in total darkness."},{"id":"sneaky","name":"Sneaky","description":"An Umbaran can choose to reroll any Stealth check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[{"id":"umbaran-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"wis":2,"cha":2,"con":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Low-Light Vision","Conditional Bonus Feat","Soothing Voice","Light Sensitivity"],"languages":["Basic","Umbarese"],"description":"Alternate Umbaran trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Umbarans ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"An Umbaran with Persuasion as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Persuasion) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"soothing-voice","name":"Soothing Voice","description":"An Umbaran may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"light-sensitivity","name":"Light Sensitivity","description":"An Umbaran exposed to bright light (such as sunlight) is Blinded for 1 round."}]}],"sourceLine":2052},"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-utai","name":"Utai","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Utai.webp","system":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Animal Handler","Cooperative","Low-Light Vision"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"animal-handler","name":"Animal Handler","description":"The Utai are naturally gifted when it comes to dealing with Beasts and wild creatures. An Utai can choose to reroll any Ride check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. Additionally, an Utai can make Persuasion checks to change the Attitude of an undomesticated creature that has an Intelligence score of 2 or lower."},{"id":"cooperative","name":"Cooperative","description":"An Utai automatically succeeds when attempting to Aid Another on a Skill Check, as long as the target is adjacent to, and can hear and understand, the Utai."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Utai ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"languages":["Utapese"],"description":"An ancient race of diminutive humanoids evolving on the Outer Rim planet of Utapau, the Utai make their homes in tunnels and caves amid the sinkholes that pockmarked their homeworld, colonizing them long before the surface dwelling Pau'ans were forced to take refuge in the sinkholes after hyperwinds made life on the surface unbearable. Working together, the Utai allowed the Pau'ans to take the lead in all societal matters, although the Utai make up more than seventy percent of the population on Utapau. Introducing the Utai to wind power, the Pau'ans took over governmental work in the sinkholes and relegated the Utai to a labor class. Despite their role as laborers in Utapaun society, the Utai are not mistreated and prefer their worker status. Many Utai work as Varactyl wranglers and Dactillion tamers, as they possess an innate ability to commune with animals.","canonicalName":"Utai","canonicalStats":{"size":"Small","speed":4,"movement":{"walk":4,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Utai receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Utai are sturdy and hard-working, but they do not make good leaders.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Utapese"],"special":["Animal Handler","Cooperative","Low-Light Vision"],"traits":[{"id":"animal-handler","name":"Animal Handler","description":"The Utai are naturally gifted when it comes to dealing with Beasts and wild creatures. An Utai can choose to reroll any Ride check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. Additionally, an Utai can make Persuasion checks to change the Attitude of an undomesticated creature that has an Intelligence score of 2 or lower."},{"id":"cooperative","name":"Cooperative","description":"An Utai automatically succeeds when attempting to Aid Another on a Skill Check, as long as the target is adjacent to, and can hear and understand, the Utai."},{"id":"low-light-vision","name":"Low-Light Vision","description":"Utai ignore Concealment (but not Total Concealment) from darkness."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":512},"tags":["small"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-vaathkree","name":"Vaathkree","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Vaathkree.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance","+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Living Stone"],"languages":["Vaathkree","Basic"],"source":"Unknown Regions","description":"","tags":[],"costNumeric":null,"abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"canonicalName":"Vaathkree","visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-vagaari","name":"Vagaari","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Vagaari.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Bioknowledge","Conditional Bonus Feat","Frightening Visage"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bioknowledge","name":"Bioknowledge","description":"Vagaari have great working knowledge of biology throughout their sphere of influence in The Unknown Regions. A Vagaari may choose to reroll any Knowledge (Life Science) or Treat Injury check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Vagaari are accomplished actors and deceivers. A Vagaari that is Trained in the Deception skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"frightening-visage","name":"Frightening Visage","description":"Vagaari spend most of their lives trying to intimidate others by presenting a threatening appearance. A Vagaari may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate, keeping the better of the two results."}],"languages":["Sy Bisti","Vagaari"],"description":"The Vagaari Empire thrives on cruelty and terror. It is so effective at spreading fear that even other Unknown Regions Threats, such as the Ebruchi and the Rakata, flee from its forces. Arrogant speciesists, the Vagaari believe that all non-Vagaari are idiotic cowards who exist only as resources to be farmed. The Vagaari have separate digestive and respiratory tracts. The upper mouth is used for breathing and speaking, and the lower mouth is used for eating.","canonicalName":"Vagaari","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Vagaari receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Vagaari are strong, but self-centered and hostile.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Sy Bisti","Vagaari"],"special":["Bioknowledge","Conditional Bonus Feat","Frightening Visage"],"traits":[{"id":"bioknowledge","name":"Bioknowledge","description":"Vagaari have great working knowledge of biology throughout their sphere of influence in The Unknown Regions. A Vagaari may choose to reroll any Knowledge (Life Science) or Treat Injury check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Vagaari are accomplished actors and deceivers. A Vagaari that is Trained in the Deception skill gains Skill Focus (Deception) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"frightening-visage","name":"Frightening Visage","description":"Vagaari spend most of their lives trying to intimidate others by presenting a threatening appearance. A Vagaari may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate, keeping the better of the two results."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2457},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-vahla","name":"Vahla","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Vahla.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Feat","Dark Side Stigma","Heightened Agility"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Vahla receive the Force Sensitivity feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"dark-side-stigma","name":"Dark Side Stigma","description":"Whether they know it or not, each member of the Vahla Species is forever bound to The Dark Side of The Force. Vahla must spend 2 Force Points to reduce their Dark Side Score by 1 (instead of just 1 Force Point)."},{"id":"heightened-agility","name":"Heightened Agility","description":"Vahla skeletons are primarily made of cartilage instead of bone, giving them a more flexible physique. A Vahla can choose to reroll any Acrobatics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"languages":["Basic","Vahla"],"description":"The Vahla are a nomadic, Near-Human Species who roamed the galaxy in search of their homeworld, and are generally regarded as a naturally bright and shrewd people. Their small economy is fueled by petty theft and limited-scale piracy, and, following the Great Jedi Purge, by bounty hunting. All Vahla are Force-sensitive, and whether aware or not, have ties to The Dark Side of The Force. Most Vahla become members of The Ember of Vahl, a Dark Side cult that worships Vahl, a goddess of fire and destruction. Though not all Vahla are members, they are all expected to follow the orders of a six-priest central coven believed to have been \"Chosen\" by the goddess.","canonicalName":"Vahla","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":-2,"int":2,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Vahla receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. The Vahla are naturally bright and shrewd, but they are physically frail.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Vahla"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Dark Side Stigma","Heightened Agility"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Vahla receive the Force Sensitivity feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"dark-side-stigma","name":"Dark Side Stigma","description":"Whether they know it or not, each member of the Vahla Species is forever bound to The Dark Side of The Force. Vahla must spend 2 Force Points to reduce their Dark Side Score by 1 (instead of just 1 Force Point)."},{"id":"heightened-agility","name":"Heightened Agility","description":"Vahla skeletons are primarily made of cartilage instead of bone, giving them a more flexible physique. A Vahla can choose to reroll any Acrobatics check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1521},"tags":["force","medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":14900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-verpine","name":"Verpine","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Verpine.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":["+2 Mechanics","+2 Perception"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Heightened Awareness","Hive Mind","Natural Armor","Weapon Familiarity"],"languages":["Basic","Verpine"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"The Verpine have been spacefarers for all their recorded history, long before they had contact with other Species. Verpine have traveled for so long that the name and location of their homeworld have been lost to antiquity. They are fascinated with technology in all its forms, and consider themselves to be experts in all technological fields. Any device that falls into Verpine hands is prone to being taken apart, reassembled, and improved with astounding speed and skill. The asteroid field that the Verpine have transformed into a thriving colony is a testament to their mastery of technology.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Verpine","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Verpine who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Verpine can choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"hive-mind","name":"Hive Mind","description":"A Verpine can mentally communicate with any Verpine within a 1-kilometer range."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Verpine's carapace provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Verpine treat the Verpine Shattergun as a Pistol instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Verpine are notably versatile for a Species, and as such receive no bonuses or penalties to their Ability Scores.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Verpine"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Heightened Awareness","Hive Mind","Natural Armor","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Verpine who has Mechanics as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Mechanics) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"A Verpine can choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"hive-mind","name":"Hive Mind","description":"A Verpine can mentally communicate with any Verpine within a 1-kilometer range."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"A Verpine's carapace provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to their Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Verpine treat the Verpine Shattergun as a Pistol instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":2473},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-vultan","name":"Vultan","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Vultan.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Trained Skill","Conditional Bonus Feat"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"A Vultan can choose one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the Vultan's list of Class Skills."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Vultan with one or more Knowledge skills as Trained Skills gains a bonus Skill Focus feat for one Knowledge skill in which they are Trained."}],"languages":["Basic","Dromnyr"],"description":"Vultans are a technologically advanced Near-Human Species native to the planet Vulta, located at the spinward edge of The Mid Rim. The Vultan culture was already five millennia old at the time of the Great Hyperspace War. As citizens of an old and curious culture, Vultans tend to go through waves of fads and technological growth. Many Old Republic corporations have a few Vultans on their board of directors. Even during the time of the Empire, Vultans commonly worked as programmers for holovid entertainment companies.","canonicalName":"Vultan","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Vultans receive a +2 bonus to their Intelligence, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Vultans are creative and inquisitive, but their whimsical tendencies can often get the better of them.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Dromnyr"],"special":["Bonus Trained Skill","Conditional Bonus Feat"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-trained-skill","name":"Bonus Trained Skill","description":"A Vultan can choose one additional Trained Skill at 1st level. The Skill must be chosen from the Vultan's list of Class Skills."},{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"A Vultan with one or more Knowledge skills as Trained Skills gains a bonus Skill Focus feat for one Knowledge skill in which they are Trained."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1643},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-vurk","name":"Vurk","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Vurk.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, +2 Cha, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Expert Swimmer","Placid","Survival Instinct"],"languages":["Basic","Semblan"],"source":"Clone Wars","description":"Originally considered a primitive Species by galactic survey teams, Vurks are intelligent and philosophically advanced. From birth, they are taught to honor personal integrity, individual freedom, and honesty. Because of these tenants, Vurks make excellent diplomats and negotiators.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Vurk","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"swimSpeed":4,"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Vurks can't drown in water."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Vurk may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Vurk may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"placid","name":"Placid","description":"Vurks are renowned for their ability to remain calm and collected, even in the face of danger. Once per encounter, as a Free Action, a Vurk can remove one Fear effect currently affecting it."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"As nomads, Vurks are accustomed to moving around, even through dangerous places. A Vurk may choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":4,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, +2 Cha, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Vurks receive +2 bonuses to both their Constitution and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Vurks are resilient and reliable, but their thick fingers lack fine motor movement.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Semblan"],"special":["Breathe Underwater","Expert Swimmer","Placid","Survival Instinct"],"traits":[{"id":"breathe-underwater","name":"Breathe Underwater","description":"As amphibious creatures, Vurks can't drown in water."},{"id":"expert-swimmer","name":"Expert Swimmer","description":"A Vurk may choose to reroll any Swim check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse. In addition, a Vurk may choose to Take 10 on Swim checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"placid","name":"Placid","description":"Vurks are renowned for their ability to remain calm and collected, even in the face of danger. Once per encounter, as a Free Action, a Vurk can remove one Fear effect currently affecting it."},{"id":"survival-instinct","name":"Survival Instinct","description":"As nomads, Vurks are accustomed to moving around, even through dangerous places. A Vurk may choose to reroll any Survival check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1383},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-weequay","name":"Weequay","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Weequay.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Endurance"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Expressive Pheromones","Natural Armor"],"languages":["Sriluurian"],"source":"KOTOR","description":"The Weequay are well-known throughout the galaxy for their violent tendencies and lack of individuality. Deeply spiritual, they worship a broad pantheon of deities, the most senior of which is known as Quay. Zealous Weequay perform ritual sacrifices in Quay's honor, at times resorting to murder. Such incidents have done little to dispel their violent reputation. Each Weequay carries a spherical totem through which Quay allegedly speaks.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":["Desert Adaptation: +2 to Endurance vs desert heat"],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Weequay","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Weequay have learned to survive the harsh conditions on Sriluur. A Weequay with Endurance as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Endurance) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"expressive-pheromones","name":"Expressive Pheromones","description":"Weequay communicate silently with other members of their tribe by emitting complex pheromones. This form of communication has a maximum range of 20 squares. Species with the Scent Species Trait can detect Weequay pheromones by smell, but this does not allow them to understand what the Weequay are communicating."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Weequay posses a thick, leathery hide that provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to his or her Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Int, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":-2,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"Weequay receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Charisma. Weequay are resilient but not particularly bright, and they don't relate well to others.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Sriluurian"],"special":["Conditional Bonus Feat","Expressive Pheromones","Natural Armor"],"traits":[{"id":"conditional-bonus-feat","name":"Conditional Bonus Feat","description":"Weequay have learned to survive the harsh conditions on Sriluur. A Weequay with Endurance as a Trained Skill gains Skill Focus (Endurance) as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"expressive-pheromones","name":"Expressive Pheromones","description":"Weequay communicate silently with other members of their tribe by emitting complex pheromones. This form of communication has a maximum range of 20 squares. Species with the Scent Species Trait can detect Weequay pheromones by smell, but this does not allow them to understand what the Weequay are communicating."},{"id":"natural-armor","name":"Natural Armor","description":"Weequay posses a thick, leathery hide that provides a +1 Natural Armor bonus to his or her Reflex Defense. A Natural Armor bonus stacks with an Armor bonus."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1539},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-whiphid","name":"Whiphid","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Whiphid.webp","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Int, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Survival","+2 Perception"],"special":["Cold Resistance","Natural Weapons","Scent"],"languages":["Whiphid"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"Whiphids are nomadic hunters, living on and making seasonal migrations across the vast tundra of their homeworld. Whiphid society is primitive and tribal, with each tribe led by a Spearmaster. They live for the hunt and the thrill of the kill. When they were discovered by traders during The Old Republic Era, the Whiphids were quite taken with the traders' technology. Since that time, numerous Whiphids have left their tribes behind in search of a lucrative and more comfortable life elsewhere in the galaxy.","tags":["large"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Whiphid","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"cold-resistance","name":"Cold Resistance","description":"Their thick fur gives allows Whiphids to add a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense to resist Extreme Cold."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Whiphid has Natural Weapons, in the form of sharp claws. When a Whiphid makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with that attack, instead of normal Unarmed damage. Whiphid are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Whiphids have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Whiphids ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Int, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":-2,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Whiphids receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Intelligence and Wisdom. Whiphids are typically strong, but many lack experience in the wider galaxy.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Whiphid"],"special":["Cold Resistance","Natural Weapons","Scent"],"traits":[{"id":"cold-resistance","name":"Cold Resistance","description":"Their thick fur gives allows Whiphids to add a +5 Species bonus to their Fortitude Defense to resist Extreme Cold."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Whiphid has Natural Weapons, in the form of sharp claws. When a Whiphid makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of slashing damage with that attack, instead of normal Unarmed damage. Whiphid are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"Whiphids have a keen sense of smell. At close range (within 10 squares), Whiphids ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and take no penalty from poor visibility while Tracking."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":944},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15400,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-wookiee","name":"Wookiee","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Wookiee.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Climb","+2 Survival"],"special":["Expert Climber","Extraordinary Recuperation","Intimidating Presence","Rage","Weapon Familiarity (Bowcaster and Ryyk Blade)"],"languages":["Shyriiwook","Basic"],"source":"Core","description":"Wookiees are widely recognized as one of the strongest and fiercest intelligent Species in the galaxy. Wookiees have many customs and traditions that revolve around honor and loyalty, including the special bond called the honor family and the sacred pledge called the Life Debt. A Wookiee never uses his or her climbing claws in combat; doing this is considered dishonorable and a sign of madness.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[{"name":"Claws","damage":"1d6","type":"slashing"}],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":["Bowcaster"],"otherTraits":["Rage: Swift action, +2 Str, +2 Con, –2 Defenses, then fatigued"]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Wookiee","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Wookiees are great climbers and may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"extraordinary-recuperation","name":"Extraordinary Recuperation","description":"A Wookiee regains Hit Points at double the normal rate (see Natural Healing)."},{"id":"intimidating-presence","name":"Intimidating Presence","description":"Known to pull off the ears of Gundarks, Wookiees may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate others, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Wookiee can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While Raging, the Wookiee temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Wookiee's Constitution modifier. At the end of its Rage, the Wookiee moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Wookiee takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Wookiee can't engage in any strenuous activity."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity-bowcaster-and-ryyk-blade","name":"Weapon Familiarity (Bowcaster and Ryyk Blade)","description":"Wookiees treat the Bowcaster as a Rifle instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged). They additionally treat the Ryyk Blade as an Advanced Melee Weapon instead of an Exotic Weapon (Melee)."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, +2 Con, -2 Dex, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":-2,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Wookiees receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, and +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer -2 penalties to their Dexterity, Wisdom, and Charisma. Wookiees are powerful and hardy, but they aren't agile, tend to be impulsive, and have little patience for diplomacy.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Shyriiwook","Basic"],"special":["Expert Climber","Extraordinary Recuperation","Intimidating Presence","Rage","Weapon Familiarity (Bowcaster and Ryyk Blade)"],"traits":[{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"Wookiees are great climbers and may choose to Take 10 on Climb checks, even when distracted or threatened."},{"id":"extraordinary-recuperation","name":"Extraordinary Recuperation","description":"A Wookiee regains Hit Points at double the normal rate (see Natural Healing)."},{"id":"intimidating-presence","name":"Intimidating Presence","description":"Known to pull off the ears of Gundarks, Wookiees may choose to reroll any Persuasion check made to Intimidate others, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"rage","name":"Rage","description":"Once per day, a Wookiee can fly into a Rage as a Swift Action. While Raging, the Wookiee temporarily gains a +2 Rage bonus on melee attack rolls and melee damage rolls, but cannot use Skills that require patience and concentration, such as Mechanics, Stealth, or Use the Force. A fit of Rage lasts for a number of rounds equal to 5 + the Wookiee's Constitution modifier. At the end of its Rage, the Wookiee moves -1 Persistent step along the Condition Track. The penalties imposed by this Persistent Condition persist until the Wookiee takes at least 10 minutes to recuperate, during which time the Wookiee can't engage in any strenuous activity."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity-bowcaster-and-ryyk-blade","name":"Weapon Familiarity (Bowcaster and Ryyk Blade)","description":"Wookiees treat the Bowcaster as a Rifle instead of an Exotic Weapon (Ranged). They additionally treat the Ryyk Blade as an Advanced Melee Weapon instead of an Exotic Weapon (Melee)."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":403},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15500,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-wroonian","name":"Wroonian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Wroonian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"special":["Iron Will","Soothing Voice"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Wroonians are stubborn and hard to be deterred, giving them a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"soothing-voice","name":"Soothing Voice","description":"A Wroonian may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"languages":["Basic","Wroonian"],"description":"Wroonians are a blue-skinned Species of Near-Humans from the planet Wroona in The Inner Rim, a world in the same sector as the Bestine System. Wroonian society is wealthy, fun-loving, and deeply spiritual; as a result, Wroonians often wear ornate clothing and tattoos. Wroonians love travel both at sea and in space, often fancying themselves as skilled navigators and explorers. A well-traveled Species, they were represented in The Galactic Republic by the blue-skinned Pantoran Senator Chi Eekway Papanoida and later became part of The Galactic Empire. There are numerous Wroonian colonies spread throughout the Mid and Outer Rim, such as on Saleucami.","canonicalName":"Wroonian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Dex, -2 Con","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":2,"con":-2,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Wroonians receive a +2 bonus to their Dexterity, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Constitution. Wroonians are graceful and swift, but often their physical prowess lags behind other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Wroonian"],"special":["Iron Will","Soothing Voice"],"traits":[{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Wroonians are stubborn and hard to be deterred, giving them a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"soothing-voice","name":"Soothing Voice","description":"A Wroonian may choose to reroll any Persuasion check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1176},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15600,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-yarkora","name":"Yarkora","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Yarkora.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Dex","skillBonuses":["+2 Deception","+2 Persuasion"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Confusion","Deceptive"],"languages":["Basic","Yarkora"],"source":"Threats","description":"Yarkora are adept at gathering information, aided by their acute senses of sight and hearing. Most Yarkora try to keep a low profile by acting alone. However, those who find a ship or gang useful have no trouble gathering the needed henchmen, thanks to their natural charisma.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Yarkora","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Yarkora are adept at collecting information from a variety of sources. Gather Information is always a Class Skill for Yarkora."},{"id":"confusion","name":"Confusion","description":"Once per encounter as a Standard Action, a Yarkora can make a Deception check against the Will Defense of all targets within 6 squares. If the Deception check result equals or exceeds a target's Will Defense, that target does not Threaten any squares until the end of the Yarkora's next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"Naturally gifted at manipulation, a Yarkora can choose to reroll any Deception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Wis, +2 Cha, -2 Dex","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":-2,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"All Yarkora receive +2 bonuses to both their Wisdom and Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Dexterity. Yarkora are charismatic and street smart.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Yarkora"],"special":["Bonus Class Skill","Confusion","Deceptive"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-class-skill","name":"Bonus Class Skill","description":"Yarkora are adept at collecting information from a variety of sources. Gather Information is always a Class Skill for Yarkora."},{"id":"confusion","name":"Confusion","description":"Once per encounter as a Standard Action, a Yarkora can make a Deception check against the Will Defense of all targets within 6 squares. If the Deception check result equals or exceeds a target's Will Defense, that target does not Threaten any squares until the end of the Yarkora's next turn. This is a Mind-Affecting effect."},{"id":"deceptive","name":"Deceptive","description":"Naturally gifted at manipulation, a Yarkora can choose to reroll any Deception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":960},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15700,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-yevetha","name":"Yevetha","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Yevetha.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"special":["Mechanical Aptitude","Natural Weapons","Xenophobia"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"mechanical-aptitude","name":"Mechanical Aptitude","description":"Yevetha have a knack for technology. Once per encounter, a Yevetha can treat any single Mechanics check as if the die roll is a Natural 20."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Yevetha's retractable claws are Natural Weapons. When a Yevetha makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. A Yevetha is always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"xenophobia","name":"Xenophobia","description":"Yevetha have an intense distrust of all Species other than their own, and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Persuasion checks made to improve their Attitude by any creature of a different Species."}],"languages":["Yevethan"],"description":"A tall, skeletal Species with lithe builds, the Yevetha have little impact on the galaxy until after the fall of the Empire, but even that slight influence makes them known for their intense xenophobia and a culture heavily centered upon death. During Emperor Palpatine's reign, the Yevetha's homeworld, N'zoth, is seized and made the site of an Imperial shipyard. When the Yevetha revolt against their Imperial masters shortly after the Battle of Yavin, they seize control of the shipyards and over the following decade proceed to refine their technological capabilities, devising new Starships and Weapons that enable them to seize and forcibly colonize over a dozen worlds in the Koornacht Cluster. They then embark on an ambitious campaign against the New Republic military, suffering a crushing defeat because of the influence of members of The Fallanassi sect of Force-users- a defeat that leaves many Yevetha dead because of their inborn refusal to accept surrender. The New Republic keeps the Species under watch until active patrols are removed close to a decade after the bloody battle, during which time the Yevetha build an even larger force than their original fleet.","canonicalName":"Yevetha","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Yevetha receive a +2 bonus to their Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Charisma. Yevetha are strong despite their gaunt physiques, but their fatalistic culture and violent xenophobia color their outlook.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Yevethan"],"special":["Mechanical Aptitude","Natural Weapons","Xenophobia"],"traits":[{"id":"mechanical-aptitude","name":"Mechanical Aptitude","description":"Yevetha have a knack for technology. Once per encounter, a Yevetha can treat any single Mechanics check as if the die roll is a Natural 20."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Yevetha's retractable claws are Natural Weapons. When a Yevetha makes an Unarmed attack, it may choose to use its Natural Weapons, dealing 1d6 points of Slashing damage with the attack instead of normal Unarmed damage. A Yevetha is always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"xenophobia","name":"Xenophobia","description":"Yevetha have an intense distrust of all Species other than their own, and gain a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense against Persuasion checks made to improve their Attitude by any creature of a different Species."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1764},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15800,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-yuuzhan-vong","name":"Yuuzhan Vong","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Yuuzhan Vong.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Biotech Proficiency","Force Immunity","Primitive","Weapon Familiarity"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"biotech-proficiency","name":"Biotech Proficiency","description":"Yuuzhan Vong suffer no penalties while wielding Yuuzhan Vong Biotech."},{"id":"force-immunity","name":"Force Immunity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong can't take the Force Sensitivity feat, can't make Use the Force checks, and never gain Force Points. In addition, they are immune to any Force effect that targets their Will Defense (including Force Powers and aspects of the Use the Force skill)."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Yuuzhan Vong do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles), as starting Feats at 1st level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong treat Amphistaffs as a Simple Weapon (Melee) instead of as an Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"languages":["Yuuzhan Vong"],"description":"The Yuuzhan Vong come from the unknown reaches of space, entering the galaxy as invaders fueled by religious conviction. They have no connection to The Force, and regard mechanical technology as blasphemous. Their Starships, weapons, armor, and tools are genetically engineered lifeforms or created from the byproducts of such creatures. After laying waste to many New Republic worlds, the invading Yuuzhan Vong are eventually overcome by The Galactic Alliance. Peace is restored, even though some Yuuzhan Vong remain behind in isolated corners of the galaxy.","canonicalName":"Yuuzhan Vong","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Yuuzhan Vong receive a +2 bonus to Strength, but suffer a -2 penalty to Wisdom. Yuuzhan Vong are powerfully built, but rash and quick to pass judgment.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Yuuzhan Vong"],"special":["Biotech Proficiency","Force Immunity","Primitive","Weapon Familiarity"],"traits":[{"id":"biotech-proficiency","name":"Biotech Proficiency","description":"Yuuzhan Vong suffer no penalties while wielding Yuuzhan Vong Biotech."},{"id":"force-immunity","name":"Force Immunity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong can't take the Force Sensitivity feat, can't make Use the Force checks, and never gain Force Points. In addition, they are immune to any Force effect that targets their Will Defense (including Force Powers and aspects of the Use the Force skill)."},{"id":"primitive","name":"Primitive","description":"Yuuzhan Vong do not gain Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons), Weapon Proficiency (Pistols), or Weapon Proficiency (Rifles), as starting Feats at 1st level, even if their Class normally grants them."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong treat Amphistaffs as a Simple Weapon (Melee) instead of as an Exotic Weapons (Melee)."}],"variants":[{"id":"yuuzhan-vong-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"bySize":null},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"wis":-2},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Force Immunity","Technophobic","Weapon Familiarity"],"languages":["Yuuzhan Vong"],"description":"Alternate Yuuzhan Vong trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"force-immunity","name":"Force Immunity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong can't take the Force Sensitivity feat, can't make Use the Force checks, and never gain Force Points. In addition, they are immune to any Force effect that targets their Will Defense (including Force Powers and aspects of the Use the Force skill)."},{"id":"technophobic","name":"Technophobic","description":"Yuuzhan Vong take a -5 penalty on attack rolls and skill checks made when using mechanical weapons or tools."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong with the Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons) feat are considered proficient with the Amphistaff."}]}],"sourceLine":1557},"tags":["force","medium","primitive"],"variants":[{"id":"yuuzhan-vong-alternate","label":"Alternate","source":"Canonical alternate species traits","size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Str, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":2,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityChoice":null,"skillBonuses":[],"special":["Force Immunity","Technophobic","Weapon Familiarity"],"languages":["Yuuzhan Vong"],"description":"Alternate Yuuzhan Vong trait profile from the canonical species text.","traits":[{"id":"force-immunity","name":"Force Immunity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong can't take the Force Sensitivity feat, can't make Use the Force checks, and never gain Force Points. In addition, they are immune to any Force effect that targets their Will Defense (including Force Powers and aspects of the Use the Force skill)."},{"id":"technophobic","name":"Technophobic","description":"Yuuzhan Vong take a -5 penalty on attack rolls and skill checks made when using mechanical weapons or tools."},{"id":"weapon-familiarity","name":"Weapon Familiarity","description":"Yuuzhan Vong with the Weapon Proficiency (Simple Weapons) feat are considered proficient with the Amphistaff."}]}],"primitive":true,"suppressedClassProficiencies":["Weapon Proficiency (Heavy Weapons)","Weapon Proficiency (Pistols)","Weapon Proficiency (Rifles)"],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":15900,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-yuzzem","name":"Yuzzem","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Yuzzem.jpg","system":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","skillBonuses":["+2 Climb","+2 Endurance"],"special":["Expert Climber","Natural Weapons","Physically Intimidating","Scent"],"languages":["Yuzz"],"source":"Rebellion","description":"In spite of a well-deserved reputation as temperamental brutes, Yuzzem are cunning and intelligent, and their resourcefulness gives them as much of an advantage as their physically powerful frames. The Empire has learned this the hard way after they declared the Yuzzem a slave Species, rounding up large numbers of them, and putting them to work in heavy-labor operations. The Yuzzem have frequently revolted against their Imperial masters, showing that they can be as ferocious as Wookiees, with no reservations about using their claws and tusks in a fight.","tags":["large"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Yuzzem","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"A Yuzzem can reroll Climb checks, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Yuzzem's large tusks and sharp claws serve as Natural Weapons. When making an Unarmed attack, a Yuzzem can use Natural Weapons, dealing 1d8 points of piercing damage (Bite), or slashing damage (Claws), instead of normal Unarmed damage. Yuzzem are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"physically-intimidating","name":"Physically Intimidating","description":"Yuzzem use their Strength modifier instead of their Charisma modifier for Persuasion checks made to Intimidate others."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"At close range (within 10 squares), Yuzzem ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and they take no penalty from poor visibility when Tracking."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Large","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+4 Str, -2 Wis, -2 Cha","abilityMods":{"str":4,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":-2},"abilityText":"All Yuzzem receive a +4 bonus to their Strength, but suffer -2 penalties to both their Wisdom and Charisma. Yuzzem are physically powerful, but their volatile nature earns them few allies.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Yuzz"],"special":["Expert Climber","Natural Weapons","Physically Intimidating","Scent"],"traits":[{"id":"expert-climber","name":"Expert Climber","description":"A Yuzzem can reroll Climb checks, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"natural-weapons","name":"Natural Weapons","description":"A Yuzzem's large tusks and sharp claws serve as Natural Weapons. When making an Unarmed attack, a Yuzzem can use Natural Weapons, dealing 1d8 points of piercing damage (Bite), or slashing damage (Claws), instead of normal Unarmed damage. Yuzzem are always considered armed with their Natural Weapons."},{"id":"physically-intimidating","name":"Physically Intimidating","description":"Yuzzem use their Strength modifier instead of their Charisma modifier for Persuasion checks made to Intimidate others."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","description":"At close range (within 10 squares), Yuzzem ignore Concealment and Cover for purposes of Perception checks, and they take no penalty from poor visibility when Tracking."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1781},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":16000,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-zabrak","name":"Zabrak","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Zabrak.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"None","skillBonuses":["+2 Initiative"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Superior Defenses"],"languages":["Basic","Zabrak"],"source":"Core","description":"The Zabrak are an early spacefaring race distinguished by patterns of vestigial horns on their heads. Zabrak hail from many worlds and have been spacefarers for so long that they define themselves and each other according to their colony of origin. The harshness of Iridonia, their homeworld, forged in the Zabrak an iron will to survive. Driven to escape their world, they sought to obtain the knowledge of space flight. When Duros scouts began exploring The Mid Rim, they encountered Zabrak in eight sovereign colonies in five different systems.","tags":["medium"],"visionTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]},"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"bonusFeats":1,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Zabrak","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"Having strong survival instincts and quick reactions, a Zabrak may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"superior-defenses","name":"Superior Defenses","description":"Adapted to a very tough and trying environment, Zabrak gain a +1 Species bonus to all their Defenses."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"None","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":0,"cha":0},"abilityText":"Zabrak have no Ability Score adjustments.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic","Zabrak"],"special":["Heightened Awareness","Superior Defenses"],"traits":[{"id":"heightened-awareness","name":"Heightened Awareness","description":"Having strong survival instincts and quick reactions, a Zabrak may choose to reroll any Perception check, but the result of the reroll must be accepted, even if it is worse."},{"id":"superior-defenses","name":"Superior Defenses","description":"Adapted to a very tough and trying environment, Zabrak gain a +1 Species bonus to all their Defenses."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":434},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":16100,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-zeltron","name":"Zeltron","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Zeltron.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","skillBonuses":["+2 Persuasion","+2 Deception"],"special":["Empathy","Soothing Pheromones"],"languages":["Basic"],"source":"Legacy","description":"Zeltrons are known throughout the galaxy for their hedonistic nature. Experiencing pleasure in its myriad forms is the lifetime pursuit of all Zeltrons. They are a fun-loving species, placing recreation before other, less worldly interests. Members of the Species are found throughout the galaxy, for they enjoy traveling, meeting new people, indulging in their passions, and experiencing new things. Zeltrons are born with a latent empathy that allows them to sense the emotions of others.","tags":["medium"],"costNumeric":null,"canonicalName":"Zeltron","movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"empathy","name":"Empathy","description":"Zeltrons add their Charisma bonus (if any) to Perception checks made to Sense Deception or Sense Influence."},{"id":"soothing-pheromones","name":"Soothing Pheromones","description":"A Zeltron gains a +5 Species bonus on Persuasion checks made to Change Attitude. This bonus does not apply to other Zeltrons, as Zeltrons are acclimated to each other's pheromones."}],"canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Cha, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":0,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":2},"abilityText":"Zeltrons receive a +2 bonus to their Charisma, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Zeltrons get along well with others, yet they are prone to fits of passion.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Empathy","Soothing Pheromones"],"traits":[{"id":"empathy","name":"Empathy","description":"Zeltrons add their Charisma bonus (if any) to Perception checks made to Sense Deception or Sense Influence."},{"id":"soothing-pheromones","name":"Soothing Pheromones","description":"A Zeltron gains a +5 Species bonus on Persuasion checks made to Change Attitude. This bonus does not apply to other Zeltrons, as Zeltrons are acclimated to each other's pheromones."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1586},"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":16200,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"species-zygerrian","name":"Zygerrian","type":"species","img":"assets/species/Zygerrian.webp","system":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"special":["Bonus Feat","Iron Will","Strength of Conviction"],"canonicalTraits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Zygerrians receive the Martial Arts I feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Zygerrians have above-average willpower, gaining a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"strength-of-conviction","name":"Strength of Conviction","description":"Zygerrians can use their Charisma modifier in place of their Wisdom modifier when calculating their Will Defense."}],"languages":["Basic"],"description":"A violent Species from the distant corners of The Outer Rim, Zygerrians are known for their history of piracy and war. As a Species that earns its fame through slavery, piracy, and violence, Zygerrians are feared in spaceports throughout the galaxy. Raised in a culture where weakness can mean death or enslavement, Zygerrians cultivate a dangerous, unpredictable image to deter others from challenging their dominance. Those who do must contend with the Zygerrians' natural combat prowess, since Zygerrians are excellent fighters with or without weapons. Zygerrian society is built on the principle that strength leads to authority, and for Zygerrians, strength can mean many things- physical strength, and also strength of will, or conviction, and of bravery.","canonicalName":"Zygerrian","canonicalStats":{"size":"Medium","speed":6,"movement":{"walk":6,"swim":null,"fly":null,"climb":null,"hover":null,"glide":null,"burrow":null,"bySize":{}},"abilities":"+2 Con, -2 Wis","abilityMods":{"str":0,"dex":0,"con":2,"int":0,"wis":-2,"cha":0},"abilityText":"All Zygerrians receive a +2 bonus to their Constitution, but suffer a -2 penalty to their Wisdom. Zygerrians are durable, but are considered reckless by other Species.","abilityChoice":null,"languages":["Basic"],"special":["Bonus Feat","Iron Will","Strength of Conviction"],"traits":[{"id":"bonus-feat","name":"Bonus Feat","description":"Zygerrians receive the Martial Arts I feat at 1st level as a bonus Feat."},{"id":"iron-will","name":"Iron Will","description":"Zygerrians have above-average willpower, gaining a +2 Species bonus to their Will Defense."},{"id":"strength-of-conviction","name":"Strength of Conviction","description":"Zygerrians can use their Charisma modifier in place of their Wisdom modifier when calculating their Will Defense."}],"variants":[],"sourceLine":1798},"tags":["medium"],"variants":[],"speciesActsAsDroid":false,"costNumeric":null,"visionTraits":[],"movementTraits":[],"environmentalTraits":[],"techTraits":[],"forceTraits":[],"socialTraits":[],"naturalWeapons":[],"bonusFeats":0,"bonusTrainedSkills":0,"suppressedClassProficiencies":[],"combatTraits":{"naturalArmor":0,"weaponProficiencies":[],"otherTraits":[]}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":16300,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}
